02:25:01.940 --> 02:25:04.020
[Guest]: So I just want to end with, I mean, we've talked a lot about this.

02:25:04.020 --> 02:25:08.340
[Guest]: But one thought which I learned very recently on this whole luck thing.

02:25:09.540 --> 02:25:12.740
[Guest]: Have you read The Blind Watchmaker by Richard Dawkins?

02:25:12.740 --> 02:25:14.020
[Guest]: Brilliant book, I've read.

02:25:14.020 --> 02:25:16.580
[Guest]: So I was connecting to this whole frame.

02:25:16.580 --> 02:25:19.300
[Guest]: Because, you know, once you get into a probabilistic mindset,

02:25:19.300 --> 02:25:20.900
[Guest]: you see randomness everywhere, right?

02:25:20.900 --> 02:25:24.500
[Guest]: So one thing he says, right, in the book that in evolution,

02:25:25.060 --> 02:25:28.100
[Guest]: creationists who don't believe in the science of evolution,

02:25:28.660 --> 02:25:32.260
[Guest]: they think natural selection is random, right?

02:25:32.260 --> 02:25:33.540
[Guest]: Things are happening randomly.

02:25:33.540 --> 02:25:39.300
[Guest]: So how is it possible that randomness can create complex species like humans?

02:25:39.300 --> 02:25:41.540
[Guest]: So Dawkins says in the book, that is wrong.

02:25:41.540 --> 02:25:43.460
[Guest]: Natural selection is not random.

02:25:43.460 --> 02:25:45.860
[Guest]: It's opposite of random, because what is happening,

02:25:46.980 --> 02:25:50.020
[Guest]: every step of a mutation, that is random.

02:25:50.020 --> 02:25:50.580
[Amit Varma]: Yeah.

02:25:50.580 --> 02:25:54.260
[Guest]: But when you cumulatively collect everything together,

02:25:54.980 --> 02:25:58.100
[Guest]: that is far from random, because after every mutation,

02:25:58.900 --> 02:26:02.660
[Guest]: what stays, what dies, what propagates,

02:26:03.540 --> 02:26:07.780
[Guest]: that is operating on principles of natural selection, which is not random, right?

02:26:08.500 --> 02:26:10.580
[Guest]: So there is randomness at every step.

02:26:10.580 --> 02:26:14.900
[Guest]: But in the larger collective, like what ultimately becomes, that is not random.

02:26:14.900 --> 02:26:17.300
[Amit Varma]: Events versus systems, as you might put it.

02:26:17.300 --> 02:26:21.380
[Guest]: But no, even there's difference here, that if you think about careers, right?

02:26:22.740 --> 02:26:24.500
[Guest]: Like I, my theory is clear.

02:26:24.500 --> 02:26:28.500
[Guest]: My entire career is built on some random events.

02:26:28.500 --> 02:26:28.820
[Guest]: Okay.

02:26:32.100 --> 02:26:35.620
[Guest]: But then in retrospect, I feel that randomness is there.

02:26:36.180 --> 02:26:38.580
[Guest]: But there is some, if you take that frame,

02:26:38.580 --> 02:26:41.220
[Guest]: at what point, so many random things are happening.

02:26:41.220 --> 02:26:43.300
[Guest]: And then in those random things, you pick one.

02:26:43.300 --> 02:26:45.860
[Guest]: And in retrospect, you attribute everything.

02:26:45.860 --> 02:26:47.860
[Guest]: And I have done it to that one random incident.

02:26:48.580 --> 02:26:52.900
[Guest]: But I'm saying that if you take one layer above it, that in cumulative, right?

02:26:54.980 --> 02:26:58.260
[Guest]: Random plus that, what you, you know, like you chose something,

02:26:58.260 --> 02:26:59.060
[Guest]: you didn't choose something.

02:26:59.700 --> 02:27:04.340
[Guest]: So everything is not just happening by itself.

02:27:04.340 --> 02:27:07.140
[Guest]: There is some, some layer to it.

02:27:07.140 --> 02:27:09.220
[Guest]: Some layer to it, just like evolution.

02:27:09.220 --> 02:27:15.060
[Guest]: So if you, as a person say, if everything goes right, I live till 80, right?

02:27:15.060 --> 02:27:18.820
[Guest]: And whatever I become, so it's luck.

02:27:18.820 --> 02:27:22.900
[Guest]: A lot of things like right from birth, but then there's also a design.

02:27:22.900 --> 02:27:23.860
[Guest]: What do you think about that?

02:27:23.860 --> 02:27:28.740
[Guest]: Do you think that framework of evolution and natural selection applies to our lives?

02:27:30.500 --> 02:27:33.780
[Amit Varma]: Two things, I mean, one, of course, and I'm not an expert on either of these,

02:27:33.780 --> 02:27:39.220
[Amit Varma]: but you know, when Dawkins is talking about that larger process that is playing out,

02:27:39.220 --> 02:27:41.620
[Amit Varma]: it is a particular process that mutations are random,

02:27:41.620 --> 02:27:46.740
[Amit Varma]: but whether those mutations, you know, help you propagate your genes is not random.

02:27:46.740 --> 02:27:49.060
[Amit Varma]: Whatever is most suited to the environment will help you.

02:27:49.060 --> 02:27:54.820
[Amit Varma]: And in that sense that there is, you know, that process playing itself out in human affairs.

02:27:54.820 --> 02:28:00.260
[Amit Varma]: I think the danger is of looking back in hindsight and ascribing narratives.

02:28:00.260 --> 02:28:04.820
[Amit Varma]: Yes. And I think that's, and you know, that danger better than anybody else, obviously.

02:28:04.820 --> 02:28:05.620
[Guest]: That's not true.

02:28:05.620 --> 02:28:10.580
[Amit Varma]: But I mean, you know, with all your writings about journalism and data journalism and,

02:28:10.580 --> 02:28:13.460
[Amit Varma]: and yeah, and I think we need to kind of watch out for that.

02:28:13.460 --> 02:28:15.860
[Amit Varma]: Like at one, at one level, there is no free will.

02:28:15.860 --> 02:28:20.420
[Amit Varma]: And all our talk of probabilities are just because we don't, we are not omniscient.

02:28:20.420 --> 02:28:21.780
[Amit Varma]: Otherwise we would not talk of them.

02:28:22.340 --> 02:28:27.700
[Amit Varma]: But anyway, leaving that self-indulgent aside, you know, we are the way we are.

02:28:27.700 --> 02:28:31.700
[Amit Varma]: So maybe, so it's again, you know,

02:28:31.700 --> 02:28:34.980
[Amit Varma]: you could say that there are particular events which are completely accidental

02:28:34.980 --> 02:28:38.020
[Amit Varma]: and they take us in directions we wouldn't have gone in otherwise.

02:28:38.020 --> 02:28:40.100
[Amit Varma]: But you could also say that we are who we are.

02:28:40.100 --> 02:28:41.620
[Amit Varma]: Maybe some other way.

02:28:48.260 --> 02:28:49.940
[Amit Varma]: It's, it's like, you know,

02:28:49.940 --> 02:28:54.020
[Amit Varma]: there are a million parallel universes with a million asses and who knows where we are.

02:28:54.020 --> 02:28:57.860
[Amit Varma]: And this is perhaps the only one where you and I are sitting and talking right now.

02:28:57.860 --> 02:28:58.340
[Guest]: Yeah.

02:28:58.340 --> 02:29:00.580
[Guest]: And you know, this way, I absolutely love the book.

02:29:00.580 --> 02:29:01.140
[Guest]: But I'm like,

02:29:05.060 --> 02:29:07.460
[Guest]: And when I read this, I was like, come on, man.

02:29:08.580 --> 02:29:12.660
[Guest]: So now when you create these narratives, random, random, random.

02:29:16.820 --> 02:29:19.460
[Guest]: But that's why, you know, I think it's just interesting to, you know,

02:29:19.460 --> 02:29:26.420
[Guest]: you know, link that the way biological evolution works, if that has parallels to.

02:29:26.420 --> 02:29:27.540
[Guest]: So I'm still thinking about it.

02:29:27.540 --> 02:29:31.220
[Guest]: I think it's an interesting layer to add over everything is random.

02:29:31.220 --> 02:29:36.340
[Amit Varma]: So many layers, so many frames and, and it's, and it's time to take a break.

02:29:36.340 --> 02:29:50.180
[Amit Varma]: So we'll come back after the break and continue this conversation.

02:30:36.980 --> 02:30:40.100
[Amit Varma]: in your email inbox, you don't need to go anywhere.

02:30:40.100 --> 02:30:42.180
[Amit Varma]: So subscribe now for free.

02:30:42.180 --> 02:30:46.420
[Amit Varma]: The India Uncut newsletter at indiancut.substack.com.

02:30:46.420 --> 02:30:46.900
[Amit Varma]: Thank you.

02:30:49.620 --> 02:30:51.140
[Amit Varma]: Welcome back to the scene in the unseen.

02:30:51.140 --> 02:30:53.780
[Amit Varma]: I'm chatting with Samarth Bansal about his life.

02:30:53.780 --> 02:30:59.620
[Amit Varma]: And we I think spoke for two and a half hours and we just barely, you know, reached your school years.

02:30:59.620 --> 02:31:03.380
[Amit Varma]: But you did mention while you were briefly mentioning your college years as well,

02:31:03.380 --> 02:31:05.220
[Amit Varma]: you mentioned that IIT shaped you.

02:31:05.220 --> 02:31:10.020
[Amit Varma]: So tell me a little bit about that, that how did it shape you in the sense that

02:31:10.020 --> 02:31:14.660
[Amit Varma]: what was your conception of yourself before that and what you want to do in your life and

02:31:14.660 --> 02:31:15.780
[Amit Varma]: so on and so forth?

02:31:15.780 --> 02:31:17.780
[Amit Varma]: And how did IIT sharpen that?

02:31:17.780 --> 02:31:21.300
[Amit Varma]: And how did the sort of the wider social world that you were suddenly in?

02:31:21.300 --> 02:31:22.580
[Amit Varma]: How did, how did that change you?

02:31:23.620 --> 02:31:26.420
[Guest]: I mean, that's such a broad question.

02:31:26.420 --> 02:31:30.260
[Guest]: So I'll start, but please you direct as it goes, because I have like so

02:31:30.260 --> 02:31:36.260
[Guest]: fond and conflicted memories of that brilliant institute that it can go for forever.

02:31:36.260 --> 02:31:39.620
[Guest]: But anyway, so I, so IIT happened, this is 2011.

02:31:40.580 --> 02:31:46.260
[Guest]: Before I was going to IIT, I saw this, actually, when I was preparing for JEE,

02:31:47.060 --> 02:31:49.540
[Guest]: there was this show on CBS 60 Minutes.

02:31:49.540 --> 02:31:52.180
[Guest]: I think Leslie Stahl was the anchor.

02:31:52.980 --> 02:31:58.180
[Guest]: And it opened by something, you know, something like, I'm forgetting the exact words, but

02:31:58.180 --> 02:32:02.100
[Guest]: you know, X country exports something, Y country exports something.

02:32:02.100 --> 02:32:06.500
[Guest]: India exports engineers, and not just any engineers, engineers from

02:32:07.140 --> 02:32:09.380
[Guest]: the Indian Institute of Technology, right?

02:32:09.380 --> 02:32:10.020
[Guest]: Something, something.

02:32:10.020 --> 02:32:13.780
[Guest]: And then she made the comparison between Princeton, Harvard.

02:32:13.780 --> 02:32:17.620
[Guest]: Basically, that whole segment on that show was something like

02:32:18.660 --> 02:32:22.820
[Guest]: these folks at IIT, and it was set up at IIT Bombay, are like best in the world.

02:32:22.820 --> 02:32:27.460
[Guest]: Ivy League se bhi tough hai yahaan pe enter karna, these guys are different.

02:32:27.460 --> 02:32:30.500
[Guest]: And then Vinod Khosla comes in, all of these people are talking about.

02:32:30.500 --> 02:32:34.100
[Guest]: And I saw it as a 16-year-old kid.

02:32:34.100 --> 02:32:40.660
[Guest]: And that impression left, you know, the impression in my head was that, oh boy, you know, what

02:32:40.660 --> 02:32:42.660
[Guest]: world you are going to enter, right?

02:32:42.660 --> 02:32:44.340
[Guest]: And you work hard, you hate everything.

02:32:45.140 --> 02:32:50.820
[Guest]: So I had this image in my head, and I told you, like, my dream to become a software engineer

02:32:50.820 --> 02:32:56.260
[Guest]: was back when I was in seventh grade, when I started creating websites, you know, do

02:32:56.260 --> 02:32:57.300
[Guest]: you remember Geocities?

02:32:57.300 --> 02:32:58.340
[Guest]: Yeah, of course.

02:32:58.340 --> 02:33:01.380
[Unknown]: So I had all those pages, Flash, and I was doing all of those things.

02:33:02.420 --> 02:33:08.020
[Guest]: So I had this impression that main IIT jaunga, and waha pe everyone, you know, in dorm rooms

02:33:08.020 --> 02:33:11.620
[Guest]: will be writing code, you know, kuch kuch hora hoga waha pe.

02:33:11.620 --> 02:33:18.020
[Guest]: And like, it was going to be this massive burst of scientific exploration, technological

02:33:18.020 --> 02:33:18.580
[Guest]: innovation.

02:33:18.580 --> 02:33:22.820
[Guest]: And the other thing happened in, I'm giving context because of what I expected.

02:33:22.820 --> 02:33:28.100
[Guest]: I heard the speech, you know, the Steve Jobs 2005 Convocation at Stanford.

02:33:28.100 --> 02:33:29.140
[Guest]: Have you, do you know?

02:33:29.140 --> 02:33:31.140
[Amit Varma]: Incredible speech, stay hungry, stay foolish.

02:33:31.140 --> 02:33:34.580
[Guest]: Wo pandra minute ka jo hai na, I've heard it repeatedly during college also.

02:33:34.580 --> 02:33:39.060
[Guest]: Har 6 maine mein main sunta tha ek baar, just to, so that many eleventh mein sun liya tha.

02:33:39.060 --> 02:33:45.940
[Guest]: So in twelfth grade, I was like, okay, I had this conviction that I was destined to become

02:33:45.940 --> 02:33:46.980
[Guest]: the next Steve Jobs.

02:33:46.980 --> 02:33:50.180
[Guest]: I mean, that's a 17-year-old me.

02:33:50.180 --> 02:33:53.300
[Guest]: I find that guy a bit obnoxious, but that was who I was.

02:33:53.300 --> 02:33:54.980
[Amit Varma]: But every 17-year-old should dream.

02:33:54.980 --> 02:33:55.780
[Amit Varma]: Should dream, right?

02:33:55.780 --> 02:33:56.340
[Guest]: Yeah.

02:33:56.340 --> 02:34:00.420
[Guest]: So waise tha, and I was like, code bhi karenge, company banayenge, entrepreneur banna hai,

02:34:00.420 --> 02:34:01.700
[Guest]: all of those dreams were there.

02:34:01.700 --> 02:34:03.940
[Guest]: And I, so that is what I went in.

02:34:03.940 --> 02:34:08.260
[Guest]: And I go, and there's nothing like that.

02:34:08.260 --> 02:34:13.700
[Guest]: Although, it's, you know, you get a culture shock because you don't, you're not fine.

02:34:13.700 --> 02:34:19.140
[Guest]: Like first, mein ragging ho rahi hai, you know, all kinds of things are happening.

02:34:19.140 --> 02:34:21.940
[Guest]: You don't find this energy that I was expecting.

02:34:21.940 --> 02:34:25.300
[Guest]: So it was a, for whatever reason, misleading expectation.

02:34:25.300 --> 02:34:30.260
[Guest]: Toh wo starting mein toh I just had to accept the fact that that is not what this institute

02:34:30.260 --> 02:34:31.060
[Guest]: is.

02:34:31.060 --> 02:34:35.220
[Guest]: But I had, despite that, so after that shock, you adjust.

02:34:35.220 --> 02:34:38.660
[Guest]: I also, because that was the first time I left home, like a lot of my friends had been

02:34:38.660 --> 02:34:40.420
[Guest]: to Kota and other places.

02:34:40.420 --> 02:34:45.700
[Guest]: Merle toh naya tha to adjust, so many different people, like we had this hostel wing, 13 rooms,

02:34:45.700 --> 02:34:48.980
[Guest]: 3 people each, all from different backgrounds.

02:34:48.980 --> 02:34:52.740
[Guest]: In fact, interestingly, people talk about, like one of the best things about IIT Kanpur

02:34:52.740 --> 02:34:55.380
[Guest]: is that our hostel allocation is random.

02:34:55.380 --> 02:34:58.180
[Guest]: So, you know, the caste, class, all of that is mixed.

02:34:58.180 --> 02:34:59.780
[Guest]: You don't pick that way, right?

02:34:59.780 --> 02:35:00.900
[Guest]: So brilliant.

02:35:00.900 --> 02:35:03.380
[Guest]: So I settled in, made comfort with what was happening.

02:35:04.260 --> 02:35:06.100
[Guest]: And, you know, starting everyone is excited.

02:35:06.100 --> 02:35:07.300
[Guest]: My first semester was great.

02:35:08.020 --> 02:35:08.580
[Guest]: Okay.

02:35:08.580 --> 02:35:10.340
[Guest]: I did excellent at exams.

02:35:10.340 --> 02:35:15.620
[Guest]: I was participating in extra extracurricular activities, dance, you know, played guitar

02:35:15.620 --> 02:35:17.380
[Guest]: at my, you know, hostel day.

02:35:17.380 --> 02:35:18.180
[Guest]: All of those things are happening.

02:35:18.180 --> 02:35:20.500
[Guest]: I'm having the best of my time.

02:35:20.500 --> 02:35:21.620
[Guest]: Everything is fine.

02:35:21.620 --> 02:35:23.380
[Guest]: And I'm also just adjusting ki maze bhi karne hain.

02:35:23.380 --> 02:35:24.100
[Guest]: You know, we have come.

02:35:24.900 --> 02:35:26.260
[Guest]: So things are going fine.

02:35:26.260 --> 02:35:29.140
[Guest]: I think second semester onwards, things started changing.

02:35:29.940 --> 02:35:30.260
[Guest]: Okay.

02:35:30.260 --> 02:35:36.500
[Guest]: I started realizing that, you know, for some reason, not actually for some reason, there

02:35:36.500 --> 02:35:42.500
[Guest]: was a clear reason I went, I would go to classes and I could not get the big picture that why

02:35:42.500 --> 02:35:43.380
[Guest]: I'm studying this.

02:35:43.380 --> 02:35:45.460
[Guest]: So usfak deta ki mujhe pata hona chahiye na main kyu padh rahon.

02:35:46.180 --> 02:35:48.260
[Guest]: Toh that was not happening.

02:35:49.300 --> 02:35:53.780
[Guest]: And I started feeling a bit disoriented, but still that was in the back of my head.

02:35:53.780 --> 02:35:54.980
[Guest]: It was not dominant.

02:35:54.980 --> 02:35:59.700
[Guest]: So I was very active in student politics for elections, you know, in our student community,

02:35:59.700 --> 02:36:00.660
[Guest]: all of those things are happening.

02:36:01.220 --> 02:36:01.780
[Guest]: Maze aa rahe hain.

02:36:01.780 --> 02:36:03.060
[Guest]: Things are going fine.

02:36:03.060 --> 02:36:09.860
[Guest]: So fast forward, I think then third semester onwards, you know, things started making much

02:36:09.860 --> 02:36:13.780
[Guest]: more sense where I see that, look, yeh wo jaga toh hain nahi jo main nahi imagine kari

02:36:13.780 --> 02:36:14.260
[Guest]: thi.

02:36:14.260 --> 02:36:14.820
[Guest]: Okay.

02:36:14.820 --> 02:36:18.420
[Guest]: But still, it's a wonderful place because ample opportunity.

02:36:18.420 --> 02:36:22.340
[Guest]: If you look at the infrastructure of IIT, you know, the kind of people you meet, you

02:36:22.340 --> 02:36:27.700
[Guest]: know, starting mein jaa ke agar aapke andar thoda sa bhi ego hain about ki bhai hum toh

02:36:27.700 --> 02:36:28.900
[Guest]: apne school ke raja the.

02:36:28.900 --> 02:36:30.660
[Guest]: Pehle din jaa ke, you know, that bubble is burst.

02:36:30.660 --> 02:36:34.820
[Guest]: Because you see, boss, everyone around you is great.

02:36:34.820 --> 02:36:39.220
[Guest]: Aap physics ka problem kar rahe ho, that other person, your friend, he'll do it faster

02:36:39.220 --> 02:36:39.540
[Guest]: than you.

02:36:39.540 --> 02:36:42.900
[Guest]: So, you know, IIT makes you humble in many ways.

02:36:42.900 --> 02:36:46.260
[Guest]: Wo kabhi jaata nahi hai because you always know ki yaar, you were in that space.

02:36:47.060 --> 02:36:49.220
[Guest]: So that was first year, nice.

02:36:49.220 --> 02:36:52.500
[Guest]: But third semester onwards, I think my frame started changing.

02:36:52.500 --> 02:36:55.460
[Guest]: One big thing that happened was that I read an essay by Paul Graham.

02:36:56.740 --> 02:36:57.460
[Guest]: Paul Graham, right?

02:36:57.460 --> 02:36:58.260
[Guest]: The VC.

02:36:58.260 --> 02:36:59.220
[Guest]: Brilliant essays.

02:36:59.220 --> 02:37:04.420
[Guest]: Uska ek line tha in one of his essays where he says that if you want to be an entrepreneur,

02:37:05.060 --> 02:37:06.020
[Guest]: don't work at Google.

02:37:07.140 --> 02:37:08.900
[Guest]: Because Google is so good.

02:37:08.900 --> 02:37:11.380
[Guest]: It's such a great company that you would never want to leave.

02:37:12.420 --> 02:37:14.500
[Guest]: I read that line and it touched me.

02:37:14.500 --> 02:37:18.820
[Guest]: And Amit, in my third semester, I decided I will not sit for campus placements.

02:37:20.020 --> 02:37:20.340
[Guest]: Okay?

02:37:21.380 --> 02:37:27.700
[Guest]: And that was so liberating because once you decide ki bhai placement mein toh betna hi

02:37:27.700 --> 02:37:28.580
[Guest]: nahi.

02:37:28.580 --> 02:37:34.500
[Guest]: So everything that is happening around you, which is optimized for that big job,

02:37:34.500 --> 02:37:35.860
[Guest]: wo aapka chala gaya.

02:37:35.860 --> 02:37:37.860
[Guest]: So you're not thinking about your resume.

02:37:38.500 --> 02:37:39.860
[Guest]: You're not thinking about grades.

02:37:41.220 --> 02:37:42.100
[Guest]: Maze karna hai, right?

02:37:42.100 --> 02:37:44.180
[Guest]: Ki do what you want to do.

02:37:44.180 --> 02:37:47.380
[Guest]: The other thing that happened around that time, I think it was second semester mein hua tha.

02:37:48.340 --> 02:37:49.700
[Guest]: Coursera came to this world.

02:37:49.700 --> 02:37:51.140
[Guest]: Coursera and Udacity, right?

02:37:51.140 --> 02:37:52.260
[Guest]: Massive online open course.

02:37:52.260 --> 02:37:52.980
[Guest]: Yeah.

02:37:52.980 --> 02:37:56.500
[Guest]: So I started and I was like, class mein toh mereko mazaa nahi raha, what I'm studying.

02:37:56.500 --> 02:37:59.940
[Guest]: But it's also not, main toh engineering mein interested hu.

02:38:00.580 --> 02:38:03.460
[Guest]: Lekin jo class mein padha rahe hain, wo nahi padhna hai, right?

02:38:03.460 --> 02:38:07.060
[Guest]: So I started spending most of my time in online courses.

02:38:07.060 --> 02:38:07.860
[Guest]: So I was studying.

02:38:08.420 --> 02:38:12.580
[Guest]: I was just not studying what my profs were teaching me, you know?

02:38:13.140 --> 02:38:14.580
[Guest]: So my grades stuck.

02:38:14.580 --> 02:38:17.860
[Guest]: It's just, you know, like my first semester performance was great.

02:38:17.860 --> 02:38:18.660
[Guest]: In fact, I used to joke,

02:38:19.220 --> 02:38:22.580
[Guest]: IIT mein B grade ki neeche lana toh matlab kitna tough kaam hai.

02:38:23.620 --> 02:38:24.020
[Guest]: Right?

02:38:24.020 --> 02:38:26.500
[Guest]: Kitti mehnat karni padhegi na padhne ke liye, you know?

02:38:26.500 --> 02:38:27.380
[Guest]: That was my attitude.

02:38:28.020 --> 02:38:30.660
[Guest]: And then, you know, C's started coming, D's started coming.

02:38:30.660 --> 02:38:32.340
[Guest]: And I was disoriented.

02:38:32.340 --> 02:38:35.700
[Guest]: Because on one hand, I said, you know, I came here with this passion of

02:38:36.340 --> 02:38:38.020
[Guest]: being like the best engineer.

02:38:38.020 --> 02:38:39.780
[Guest]: And this, I was told this is the institute.

02:38:39.780 --> 02:38:40.980
[Guest]: But yahan hoi nahi raha hai.

02:38:40.980 --> 02:38:43.460
[Guest]: So I started finding communities where people felt like me.

02:38:43.460 --> 02:38:45.940
[Guest]: And I did a lot of work in campus, in community building.

02:38:46.740 --> 02:38:49.780
[Guest]: And third semester ke baad, again, my grades fell.

02:38:49.780 --> 02:38:51.540
[Guest]: Like even, it was the worst.

02:38:51.540 --> 02:38:55.540
[Guest]: And I was in such a demotivated state that I wanted to leave the campus.

02:38:55.540 --> 02:38:56.580
[Guest]: Ki boss, mera ho gaya hai.

02:38:58.020 --> 02:38:59.300
[Guest]: This is not the right place for me.

02:38:59.300 --> 02:39:01.940
[Guest]: So I was in Bombay for an internship after my third semester.

02:39:01.940 --> 02:39:06.820
[Guest]: I, mere grades jis din aaye, I just could not believe that,

02:39:07.940 --> 02:39:08.820
[Guest]: that is not me.

02:39:08.820 --> 02:39:12.820
[Guest]: Like, these grades do not reflect who I felt I was.

02:39:13.700 --> 02:39:14.900
[Guest]: And wahan cafe mein baith ke,

02:39:14.900 --> 02:39:19.700
[Guest]: maine, I wrote a long rant email to my dean of academic affairs,

02:39:19.700 --> 02:39:20.740
[Guest]: who had taught,

02:39:20.740 --> 02:39:23.380
[Guest]: who had taught and I really respected him for his ethics.

02:39:23.380 --> 02:39:25.540
[Guest]: You know, ethics has something been very close to me.

02:39:25.540 --> 02:39:28.740
[Guest]: And this professor, still, I just met him a few months ago,

02:39:28.740 --> 02:39:31.620
[Guest]: was so central to even an IIT to shape my thinking around ethics.

02:39:32.420 --> 02:39:35.220
[Guest]: So I had something that, you know, this guy may understand.

02:39:35.220 --> 02:39:35.780
[Guest]: I don't know.

02:39:35.780 --> 02:39:37.540
[Guest]: But who writes email to dean?

02:39:37.540 --> 02:39:40.500
[Guest]: Main ho email unko itna bada rant lik diya.

02:39:41.620 --> 02:39:44.420
[Guest]: That, you know, boss, kya jaga hai ye?

02:39:44.420 --> 02:39:45.220
[Guest]: You know, what is happening?

02:39:45.220 --> 02:39:46.020
[Guest]: I can't understand.

02:39:46.020 --> 02:39:47.060
[Guest]: These grades don't reflect me.

02:39:47.060 --> 02:39:48.020
[Guest]: Tak tak tak tak.

02:39:48.020 --> 02:39:50.740
[Guest]: I read, main jab bhi usse padhta na, I'm like,

02:39:50.740 --> 02:39:52.340
[Guest]: how did I get the courage to write this email?

02:39:53.060 --> 02:39:53.620
[Guest]: Right?

02:39:53.620 --> 02:39:55.220
[Guest]: So, you know what the best thing happened?

02:39:55.220 --> 02:39:58.420
[Guest]: In 30 minutes, the dean of academic affairs responded.

02:39:59.460 --> 02:39:59.860
[Guest]: Okay.

02:39:59.860 --> 02:40:02.180
[Guest]: He wrote me a long email where he mentioned one thing.

02:40:02.180 --> 02:40:03.860
[Guest]: He said, look, don't worry.

02:40:04.580 --> 02:40:08.740
[Guest]: He said, you sit down and define what success means to you.

02:40:09.300 --> 02:40:10.980
[Guest]: It's not getting a nine point GPA.

02:40:10.980 --> 02:40:12.260
[Guest]: It's not eight point.

02:40:12.260 --> 02:40:14.420
[Guest]: He said, you say, I want a seven pointer

02:40:14.980 --> 02:40:17.620
[Guest]: and I want to do something else at campus.

02:40:17.620 --> 02:40:18.340
[Guest]: That is your metric.

02:40:18.340 --> 02:40:19.380
[Guest]: Forget everything else.

02:40:19.380 --> 02:40:20.500
[Guest]: And then he told me other things.

02:40:20.500 --> 02:40:22.500
[Guest]: And his email ended by saying,

02:40:22.500 --> 02:40:24.020
[Guest]: when you come to campus, come and meet me.

02:40:24.020 --> 02:40:24.580
[Guest]: We'll chat.

02:40:25.140 --> 02:40:28.020
[Guest]: And Amit, that mail just changed me because I was like,

02:40:29.540 --> 02:40:30.820
[Guest]: this person gets me.

02:40:30.820 --> 02:40:31.060
[Guest]: Right?

02:40:31.060 --> 02:40:31.700
[Guest]: He understood.

02:40:31.700 --> 02:40:32.740
[Guest]: And he's a dean.

02:40:32.740 --> 02:40:33.620
[Guest]: And when I met him,

02:40:34.260 --> 02:40:37.380
[Guest]: so I think that just made me, ki chalo ab ho gaya hai.

02:40:39.060 --> 02:40:40.500
[Guest]: Placement mein bhi nahi baithna hai.

02:40:40.500 --> 02:40:42.820
[Guest]: Dean ne bhi bol diya hai yaar ki tu apna kar le.

02:40:43.380 --> 02:40:45.540
[Guest]: So I think that zone came in.

02:40:45.540 --> 02:40:47.700
[Guest]: But in fourth semester, I had to drop.

02:40:47.700 --> 02:40:49.860
[Guest]: I had to go back home because of some family thing.

02:40:49.860 --> 02:40:53.540
[Guest]: So that gave me this whole space where I'm not at college.

02:40:53.540 --> 02:40:56.100
[Guest]: I was anyway frustrated ki what is happening, what is not happening.

02:40:56.660 --> 02:40:59.460
[Guest]: But uswaqt, I was working with a startup.

02:41:00.100 --> 02:41:02.020
[Guest]: You know, in my December internship was with a company.

02:41:02.020 --> 02:41:04.340
[Guest]: I was the first software developer at that company.

02:41:04.340 --> 02:41:06.500
[Guest]: I was like, what, 19 year old working with like,

02:41:07.220 --> 02:41:08.500
[Guest]: I was the first employee in that company.

02:41:08.500 --> 02:41:09.700
[Guest]: It was a small company.

02:41:09.700 --> 02:41:12.900
[Guest]: I was having a ball, you know, to write code, real,

02:41:12.900 --> 02:41:13.780
[Guest]: you know, things are happening.

02:41:13.780 --> 02:41:19.220
[Guest]: So, but that semester drop, right, like I was, I was telling you, right,

02:41:19.220 --> 02:41:20.660
[Guest]: I was going through my Facebook messages.

02:41:20.660 --> 02:41:23.780
[Guest]: I think that gave me a lot of time to introspect, ki kya hai, kya nahi.

02:41:23.780 --> 02:41:26.260
[Guest]: And then when I went back, I had a different frame.

02:41:26.820 --> 02:41:27.620
[Guest]: Toh fir maine yeh sab hataya.

02:41:27.620 --> 02:41:30.020
[Guest]: Maine ka dekho, dissatisfaction ka koi point nahi hai.

02:41:30.740 --> 02:41:34.740
[Guest]: I realized that main yaha baith ki I can compare IIT to MIT

02:41:34.740 --> 02:41:36.500
[Guest]: and I always feel ki boss kya hai.

02:41:36.500 --> 02:41:39.220
[Guest]: But when I used to talk to my friends from other engineering colleges,

02:41:39.940 --> 02:41:42.020
[Guest]: I was like, boss, do you even realize that

02:41:42.020 --> 02:41:44.420
[Guest]: do you even realize that where you are sitting?

02:41:45.780 --> 02:41:49.380
[Guest]: It's a privilege that you are getting to study at this institute

02:41:49.380 --> 02:41:51.540
[Guest]: with such great infrastructure, with such great people.

02:41:51.540 --> 02:41:54.820
[Guest]: So, if you utilize it properly and think, you can do wonders.

02:41:54.820 --> 02:41:56.340
[Guest]: So, I think wo sab ho raha tha maape.

02:41:56.340 --> 02:41:58.180
[Guest]: So, yeah, then I did whatever I want to do.

02:41:58.740 --> 02:42:01.620
[Guest]: I was extremely active in campus affairs, okay.

02:42:01.620 --> 02:42:05.060
[Guest]: I was building this company and I was doing my online courses.

02:42:05.060 --> 02:42:06.580
[Guest]: Toh iske round my learning was happening.

02:42:06.580 --> 02:42:09.220
[Guest]: I was still not reading, which is the only thing I regret.

02:42:09.220 --> 02:42:10.980
[Guest]: Possibly in retrospection, I could have done.

02:42:10.980 --> 02:42:12.420
[Guest]: But I was doing a lot of online courses

02:42:12.420 --> 02:42:15.540
[Guest]: from humanities to computer science to math.

02:42:15.540 --> 02:42:16.740
[Guest]: Everything was happening.

02:42:16.740 --> 02:42:18.900
[Guest]: My grades were kept going on, you know.

02:42:18.900 --> 02:42:20.340
[Guest]: They were not anywhere.

02:42:20.980 --> 02:42:24.740
[Guest]: So, that's my journey.

02:42:24.740 --> 02:42:26.580
[Guest]: That was, you know, intellectually what was happening

02:42:26.580 --> 02:42:28.500
[Guest]: on the academic side and my participation.

02:42:28.500 --> 02:42:30.100
[Guest]: Now, and that went on.

02:42:30.100 --> 02:42:32.100
[Guest]: Uske baad, ek point ke baad, you know,

02:42:32.100 --> 02:42:36.260
[Guest]: I got my first F grade in fifth semester, okay.

02:42:36.260 --> 02:42:38.260
[Guest]: It was such a funny thing because I never,

02:42:38.260 --> 02:42:41.220
[Guest]: the person who said ki B ke neeche lana toh kitna difficult hai,

02:42:41.220 --> 02:42:42.580
[Guest]: aapka F lag gaya.

02:42:42.580 --> 02:42:44.740
[Guest]: And then, you know, aapka disorient ho jata that

02:42:44.740 --> 02:42:46.820
[Guest]: how can someone like me get an F grade?

02:42:46.820 --> 02:42:50.180
[Guest]: Like mai, F, failure on my grade sheet, right.

02:42:50.180 --> 02:42:51.940
[Guest]: So, I went to the prof and I said,

02:42:51.940 --> 02:42:55.700
[Guest]: Sir, matlab, you know, matlab, can we talk?

02:42:55.700 --> 02:42:56.420
[Guest]: Right, you know.

02:42:56.420 --> 02:42:58.020
[Guest]: So, pehle woh meko lecture dete hain.

02:42:58.020 --> 02:42:59.860
[Guest]: You know, students like you,

02:42:59.860 --> 02:43:03.140
[Guest]: there was a time when people used to get D.

02:43:03.140 --> 02:43:04.980
[Guest]: They used to come and tell me,

02:43:04.980 --> 02:43:06.500
[Guest]: Sir, please give me an F.

02:43:06.500 --> 02:43:10.260
[Guest]: Because how can I learn a subject if I have a D grade?

02:43:10.260 --> 02:43:11.540
[Guest]: And now I have students like you,

02:43:12.260 --> 02:43:13.780
[Guest]: who have an F and they want a D.

02:43:13.780 --> 02:43:15.380
[Guest]: So, I said, theek hai, tum exam lo.

02:43:15.380 --> 02:43:16.740
[Guest]: You look at your paper.

02:43:16.740 --> 02:43:18.820
[Guest]: I turned the pages and I turned the pages

02:43:18.820 --> 02:43:19.860
[Guest]: and I could not say anything

02:43:19.860 --> 02:43:22.260
[Guest]: because there was nothing in my paper

02:43:22.260 --> 02:43:24.100
[Guest]: where I even had the courage to ask him,

02:43:24.100 --> 02:43:25.060
[Guest]: ki boss, do something.

02:43:25.700 --> 02:43:26.980
[Guest]: So, uske baad mujhe laga ki,

02:43:26.980 --> 02:43:28.740
[Guest]: I actually fucked up, right.

02:43:28.740 --> 02:43:31.220
[Guest]: And I realized that there is some indiscipline going on here.

02:43:31.220 --> 02:43:32.740
[Guest]: Kyuki itna bhi kharab nahi hona chahiye.

02:43:32.740 --> 02:43:34.660
[Guest]: So, disorientation end tak raha.

02:43:34.660 --> 02:43:36.580
[Guest]: Ki mujhe samajh nahi aara tha what's happening.

02:43:36.580 --> 02:43:38.500
[Guest]: But my other part was going really well,

02:43:38.500 --> 02:43:42.180
[Guest]: where I was campus community, yeh karenge, woh karenge.

02:43:42.180 --> 02:43:44.260
[Guest]: So, things were going great.

02:43:44.260 --> 02:43:50.420
[Guest]: Few things that really impacted me in this whole process was my...

02:43:52.340 --> 02:43:53.300
[Guest]: I was telling you about,

02:43:54.980 --> 02:43:59.540
[Guest]: in this IIT campus, it's not just about people getting jobs and,

02:44:00.420 --> 02:44:02.980
[Guest]: you know, there are actually some really smart people doing great things.

02:44:02.980 --> 02:44:04.820
[Guest]: You know, that's like the 10% of the campus.

02:44:04.820 --> 02:44:06.980
[Guest]: So, you take inspiration from them, other people are doing.

02:44:06.980 --> 02:44:09.380
[Guest]: So, it's not completely disillusion, but largely it is,

02:44:09.380 --> 02:44:13.700
[Guest]: you see ki yeh India ka aspiration ke liek vehicle hai.

02:44:13.700 --> 02:44:15.940
[Guest]: That, you know, people come, they want to get great lives.

02:44:15.940 --> 02:44:17.700
[Guest]: That is what this institute is, nothing else.

02:44:17.700 --> 02:44:19.220
[Guest]: But there is something else that was happening,

02:44:19.220 --> 02:44:22.420
[Guest]: which was that campus had a lot of issues,

02:44:23.060 --> 02:44:24.180
[Guest]: socio-political issues,

02:44:25.140 --> 02:44:28.500
[Guest]: which is what something that really caught my attention.

02:44:29.220 --> 02:44:31.460
[Guest]: Ki cheeze sahi nahi hai yaha pe, you know.

02:44:31.460 --> 02:44:33.380
[Guest]: And that is what started troubling me.

02:44:33.380 --> 02:44:34.660
[Guest]: Ki iske liye hum kuch karenge.

02:44:34.660 --> 02:44:37.940
[Guest]: And the thing about IIT Kanpur is that you are in Kanpur, but

02:44:39.140 --> 02:44:43.220
[Guest]: your world, you do not know what is happening outside the four walls of our campus.

02:44:43.220 --> 02:44:44.660
[Guest]: So, I'll give you an example.

02:44:44.660 --> 02:44:46.980
[Guest]: In 2013, Muzaffarnagar riots happened.

02:44:46.980 --> 02:44:48.740
[Guest]: I had no clue those riots happened.

02:44:48.740 --> 02:44:50.020
[Guest]: Aur hum Kanpur mein the.

02:44:50.580 --> 02:44:51.940
[Guest]: Like, I'm just giving an example.

02:44:51.940 --> 02:44:53.620
[Guest]: I was so disconnected.

02:44:53.620 --> 02:44:55.140
[Guest]: At the startup, I was working.

02:44:55.140 --> 02:44:57.780
[Guest]: There was a time when I had a fight, not fight,

02:44:57.780 --> 02:45:00.900
[Guest]: like a disagreement with my employer.

02:45:00.900 --> 02:45:03.460
[Guest]: And colleagues that there was a module I had to write,

02:45:04.100 --> 02:45:05.940
[Guest]: which would be, you know, it would be like,

02:45:05.940 --> 02:45:08.340
[Guest]: I felt that it's invading people's privacy.

02:45:08.340 --> 02:45:10.180
[Guest]: You know, ki yeh data points hum profile banayenge.

02:45:10.180 --> 02:45:12.020
[Guest]: I was like, yeh mera code hai.

02:45:12.900 --> 02:45:14.100
[Guest]: My code can't do this.

02:45:14.100 --> 02:45:15.140
[Guest]: You know, you feel an ownership.

02:45:15.700 --> 02:45:16.820
[Guest]: Ki mera software hai yaar.

02:45:16.820 --> 02:45:18.340
[Guest]: Main yeh nahi kar sakta, all of those things.

02:45:18.340 --> 02:45:19.380
[Guest]: But I had no idea.

02:45:20.020 --> 02:45:22.500
[Guest]: And at the same time, Snowden revelations were happening in the US.

02:45:22.500 --> 02:45:23.700
[Guest]: And I had no clue.

02:45:23.700 --> 02:45:27.540
[Guest]: So, I'm saying that my world was limited to the four walls of the campus.

02:45:27.540 --> 02:45:32.180
[Guest]: But the things that were troubling me were, you know,

02:45:32.180 --> 02:45:33.060
[Guest]: you know what I'm trying to say.

02:45:33.060 --> 02:45:34.660
[Guest]: It was just rooted in the campus.

02:45:35.220 --> 02:45:37.140
[Guest]: There was no sense of news, nothing.

02:45:37.140 --> 02:45:38.580
[Guest]: Aur humein lagta tha humein bahut pata hai.

02:45:38.580 --> 02:45:40.420
[Guest]: So, you know, elections ki baat kar lenge.

02:45:40.420 --> 02:45:41.300
[Guest]: Very ignorant.

02:45:41.300 --> 02:45:43.460
[Guest]: Kuchh pata hi nahi hai, na aap padh rahe ho.

02:45:43.460 --> 02:45:47.540
[Guest]: Even humanities courses, we have to compulsorily take humanities courses,

02:45:47.540 --> 02:45:48.900
[Guest]: which I don't think a lot of people know,

02:45:48.900 --> 02:45:51.300
[Guest]: that from the inception of IIT Kanpur,

02:45:51.300 --> 02:45:55.620
[Guest]: humanities is a core part of your engineering curriculum.

02:45:55.620 --> 02:45:58.340
[Guest]: Because our founder, P.K. Kelkar, he said that,

02:45:58.340 --> 02:46:01.060
[Guest]: engineers work in a society, so they need to know humanities.

02:46:01.060 --> 02:46:01.780
[Guest]: So, that way, right?

02:46:03.060 --> 02:46:05.220
[Guest]: Toh wo bhi like, you know, aap sociology padh rahe ho,

02:46:05.220 --> 02:46:07.380
[Guest]: you know, aap economics padh rahe ho, all of those things.

02:46:07.940 --> 02:46:10.100
[Guest]: Social psychology, but bahar nahi pata hai.

02:46:10.100 --> 02:46:13.780
[Guest]: But uska advantage yeh tha that I was so, I knew my campus in and out.

02:46:14.500 --> 02:46:16.180
[Guest]: Toh waha pe mein ko ek sense start hone laga,

02:46:16.180 --> 02:46:18.660
[Guest]: that boss, yaha pe toh kuchh discussions hi nahi ho rahe hain.

02:46:19.220 --> 02:46:22.020
[Guest]: Everyone is so involved in day-to-day.

02:46:22.660 --> 02:46:24.660
[Guest]: Toh student ka voice kahan se aayega?

02:46:24.660 --> 02:46:27.460
[Guest]: Jo hamare campus mein problems hain, uska forum kahan hain?

02:46:27.460 --> 02:46:31.220
[Guest]: And waha pe the student newspaper, the magazine,

02:46:31.220 --> 02:46:34.420
[Guest]: which was called Vox Populi, which started sometime in mid-2000s,

02:46:34.420 --> 02:46:38.020
[Guest]: that, during my, I think, second year, third year, it kind of died out.

02:46:38.020 --> 02:46:39.300
[Guest]: It used to be a print magazine.

02:46:40.500 --> 02:46:42.260
[Guest]: Someone tried to revamp it, kuchh nahi hua.

02:46:42.260 --> 02:46:44.420
[Guest]: So, all of these things, while they were happening,

02:46:45.060 --> 02:46:47.700
[Guest]: in my fourth year, when I was catering,

02:46:48.340 --> 02:46:50.740
[Guest]: I was like, main isko restart karunga.

02:46:51.380 --> 02:46:53.620
[Guest]: You know, this campus needs journalism.

02:46:53.620 --> 02:46:55.940
[Guest]: And I was anyway a blogger, I told you, right?

02:46:55.940 --> 02:46:58.100
[Guest]: Toh mereko wo tha ki, likhna hai mujhe,

02:46:58.100 --> 02:46:59.860
[Guest]: but I want to write about campus affairs.

02:46:59.860 --> 02:47:04.180
[Guest]: Because there was this thing I believed at the time, that words matter.

02:47:04.180 --> 02:47:07.380
[Guest]: Aur agar hum issues ko raise karenge, toh, you know, kuchh hoga.

02:47:07.380 --> 02:47:10.340
[Guest]: And I wanted to bridge the gap between students and faculty.

02:47:10.340 --> 02:47:12.580
[Guest]: Toh bahut ideas the, change leke aayenge campus mein.

02:47:12.580 --> 02:47:13.700
[Guest]: Koi toh kar nahi raha hai.

02:47:13.700 --> 02:47:16.100
[Guest]: Or English, I was telling you, language was weak.

02:47:16.100 --> 02:47:19.620
[Guest]: But thankfully, our friends at the Lit Society, they were not,

02:47:19.620 --> 02:47:20.500
[Guest]: I don't know what happened,

02:47:20.500 --> 02:47:22.580
[Guest]: they dominated kind of the Vox Populi of earlier.

02:47:22.580 --> 02:47:23.780
[Guest]: Humare time pe nahi tha.

02:47:23.780 --> 02:47:25.540
[Guest]: Toh hume toh kuchh aata hi nahi tha, nah likhna aata hai.

02:47:25.540 --> 02:47:27.940
[Guest]: Bas ek wo tha ki, the campus needs a voice.

02:47:27.940 --> 02:47:29.700
[Guest]: So me and a friend of mine, one batch junior,

02:47:29.700 --> 02:47:30.980
[Guest]: said, chalo hum banayenge.

02:47:30.980 --> 02:47:35.700
[Guest]: And that, Amit, was something that really, was brilliant.

02:47:35.700 --> 02:47:38.900
[Guest]: Like, you know, that year, when I built like,

02:47:38.900 --> 02:47:41.140
[Guest]: hum jaa jaa ke log ko bolte the, that, you know, write for us.

02:47:41.140 --> 02:47:44.820
[Guest]: I was giving these talks, that, you know, why campus needs journalism.

02:47:44.820 --> 02:47:46.580
[Guest]: Aur kuch journalism ka pata nahi hai, right?

02:47:46.580 --> 02:47:50.100
[Guest]: It's just that instinctive desire that, issues need to be discussed.

02:47:50.100 --> 02:47:52.020
[Guest]: And then I started seeing, toh humne third August,

02:47:52.020 --> 02:47:54.020
[Guest]: 2014 ko website launch kari.

02:47:54.020 --> 02:47:56.020
[Guest]: You know, our website was launched.

02:47:56.020 --> 02:47:58.500
[Guest]: And phir mene dekha, you know, humare, you know,

02:47:58.500 --> 02:48:01.300
[Guest]: starting sab, it's like, you feel like an entrepreneur.

02:48:01.300 --> 02:48:02.820
[Guest]: Solving a problem at the campus.

02:48:02.820 --> 02:48:04.260
[Guest]: Toh mera woh jo keeda tha, right?

02:48:04.260 --> 02:48:05.380
[Guest]: Ki entrepreneur banna hai.

02:48:05.380 --> 02:48:06.900
[Guest]: Toh ek time pe aaye hai ki, entrepreneur yaar,

02:48:06.900 --> 02:48:08.340
[Guest]: duniya ko baad mein dekh lenge,

02:48:08.340 --> 02:48:10.580
[Guest]: apne campus ko toh, kuchh kar lo, right?

02:48:10.580 --> 02:48:11.860
[Guest]: Oh, things started happening.

02:48:11.860 --> 02:48:12.980
[Guest]: And then I started seeing impact.

02:48:12.980 --> 02:48:14.740
[Guest]: I would go to a professor to interview for,

02:48:14.740 --> 02:48:17.140
[Guest]: like, humne tumhara woh article padha hai, right?

02:48:17.140 --> 02:48:19.780
[Guest]: So these things are happening and that gave me,

02:48:19.780 --> 02:48:21.460
[Guest]: you know, it just, I felt so good.

02:48:21.460 --> 02:48:23.380
[Guest]: You know, that something is happening,

02:48:23.380 --> 02:48:25.140
[Guest]: a conversation is being triggered.

02:48:25.140 --> 02:48:28.660
[Guest]: And in all this process, there's one specific incident

02:48:29.620 --> 02:48:33.780
[Guest]: that, like, really stood with me,

02:48:33.780 --> 02:48:34.820
[Guest]: which was in my final year.

02:48:34.820 --> 02:48:36.340
[Guest]: I was going to the campus gate

02:48:36.340 --> 02:48:37.700
[Guest]: to book a train ticket to Delhi.

02:48:38.500 --> 02:48:40.020
[Guest]: And wahan pe mein gaya and I saw,

02:48:40.660 --> 02:48:42.740
[Guest]: there was this bunch of 60 mess workers

02:48:43.700 --> 02:48:46.100
[Guest]: were sitting on a hunger strike, okay?

02:48:47.220 --> 02:48:49.860
[Guest]: And my first reaction was that,

02:48:49.860 --> 02:48:51.540
[Guest]: why is no one around me?

02:48:51.540 --> 02:48:53.700
[Guest]: Itne bhi log nahi the, it was at the end of the gate.

02:48:53.700 --> 02:48:54.820
[Guest]: No one was stopping, Amit.

02:48:56.260 --> 02:48:57.860
[Guest]: These 60 guys are sitting,

02:48:57.860 --> 02:49:00.260
[Guest]: and log, they're just passing.

02:49:00.260 --> 02:49:02.420
[Guest]: Like, main paanch minute toh khade hoke dekha ki,

02:49:02.420 --> 02:49:04.500
[Guest]: does no one want to know ki,

02:49:05.940 --> 02:49:08.100
[Guest]: kyu baitha hain yaha pe, right?

02:49:08.100 --> 02:49:10.660
[Guest]: So I felt that apathy that I saw in some students.

02:49:10.660 --> 02:49:11.700
[Guest]: Pehle toh mujhe bada gussa aaya.

02:49:11.700 --> 02:49:13.620
[Guest]: I was very self-righteous, I think, in a way,

02:49:13.620 --> 02:49:14.340
[Guest]: back then.

02:49:14.340 --> 02:49:15.540
[Guest]: I'm not now.

02:49:15.540 --> 02:49:16.580
[Guest]: At least that is what I think.

02:49:16.580 --> 02:49:18.180
[Guest]: So, us waqt tha, so mein gaya

02:49:18.180 --> 02:49:20.100
[Guest]: and I had my platform.

02:49:20.820 --> 02:49:22.180
[Guest]: I called two of my friends.

02:49:22.180 --> 02:49:23.300
[Guest]: Humne unka video bana ke,

02:49:24.100 --> 02:49:25.140
[Guest]: apne platform pe chalaya.

02:49:25.700 --> 02:49:26.820
[Guest]: That triggered a conversation.

02:49:26.820 --> 02:49:27.380
[Guest]: Ki, boss,

02:49:28.660 --> 02:49:30.340
[Guest]: there is something else going on in this campus,

02:49:30.340 --> 02:49:31.060
[Guest]: which we don't know.

02:49:31.060 --> 02:49:33.540
[Guest]: And that opened my eyes to the fact that,

02:49:33.540 --> 02:49:37.540
[Guest]: IIT community is not about students and faculty and alumni

02:49:37.540 --> 02:49:38.580
[Guest]: who do great things in the world,

02:49:38.580 --> 02:49:39.860
[Guest]: quote-unquote great things in the world.

02:49:40.420 --> 02:49:41.860
[Guest]: The community is also about

02:49:43.540 --> 02:49:44.500
[Guest]: our workers.

02:49:44.500 --> 02:49:46.820
[Guest]: You know, when you say campus community,

02:49:46.820 --> 02:49:48.340
[Guest]: you have to talk about everyone.

02:49:48.340 --> 02:49:49.620
[Guest]: And when I heard their story,

02:49:51.460 --> 02:49:52.740
[Guest]: and then uske baad maine

02:49:52.740 --> 02:49:54.020
[Guest]: bahut history padha aaya IIT Kanpur ko,

02:49:54.020 --> 02:49:55.140
[Guest]: I realized that, boss,

02:49:55.140 --> 02:49:57.300
[Guest]: right from the genesis of this institute,

02:49:58.180 --> 02:49:58.500
[Guest]: you know,

02:49:59.620 --> 02:50:01.380
[Guest]: we have fucked this up.

02:50:01.380 --> 02:50:03.540
[Guest]: We have not thought about this community at all.

02:50:03.540 --> 02:50:04.980
[Guest]: We have ignored them.

02:50:04.980 --> 02:50:06.980
[Guest]: Similar things have happened in the past,

02:50:06.980 --> 02:50:09.460
[Guest]: but students were relatively more active at the time.

02:50:09.460 --> 02:50:10.100
[Guest]: Now they are not.

02:50:10.900 --> 02:50:12.100
[Guest]: So jab woh hua na,

02:50:12.100 --> 02:50:13.460
[Guest]: maine pehli story toh kari,

02:50:13.460 --> 02:50:14.340
[Guest]: where I did the video.

02:50:15.060 --> 02:50:15.780
[Guest]: Uske baad,

02:50:15.780 --> 02:50:18.420
[Guest]: because I felt so connected to the issue

02:50:18.420 --> 02:50:20.740
[Guest]: that I tried ki maine isko solve karunga.

02:50:20.740 --> 02:50:21.060
[Guest]: Right?

02:50:21.780 --> 02:50:23.540
[Guest]: And I became the,

02:50:23.540 --> 02:50:24.980
[Guest]: I spoke so much to these guys,

02:50:24.980 --> 02:50:25.940
[Guest]: unka problem samjha,

02:50:25.940 --> 02:50:27.700
[Guest]: I went to talk to the faculty,

02:50:27.700 --> 02:50:29.380
[Guest]: unka perspective samjha.

02:50:29.380 --> 02:50:30.100
[Guest]: And I thought,

02:50:30.100 --> 02:50:32.180
[Guest]: this political debate can be solved

02:50:32.180 --> 02:50:34.020
[Guest]: if two parties sit next to each other.

02:50:34.660 --> 02:50:36.420
[Guest]: Baat karenge na toh solution nikal jaayega.

02:50:36.420 --> 02:50:39.140
[Guest]: So I tried with three or four friends,

02:50:39.140 --> 02:50:40.820
[Guest]: I think they were postgraduate students,

02:50:40.820 --> 02:50:41.540
[Guest]: ki hum yeh karenge.

02:50:43.380 --> 02:50:45.460
[Guest]: We were sitting and I remember being,

02:50:45.460 --> 02:50:46.420
[Guest]: I became the moderator,

02:50:46.420 --> 02:50:48.580
[Guest]: I had my faculty here on the right,

02:50:49.220 --> 02:50:50.740
[Guest]: my mess workers on the left.

02:50:50.740 --> 02:50:52.020
[Guest]: It was a one hour discussion Amit,

02:50:52.020 --> 02:50:53.220
[Guest]: and it went nowhere.

02:50:53.780 --> 02:50:54.980
[Guest]: Nothing happened.

02:50:54.980 --> 02:50:57.860
[Guest]: Because no one was budging from their position.

02:50:57.860 --> 02:50:58.980
[Guest]: At one point I felt,

02:51:00.020 --> 02:51:00.740
[Guest]: ki you know,

02:51:00.740 --> 02:51:02.260
[Guest]: thoda sa bhi agar dono upar neeche kar le,

02:51:02.260 --> 02:51:03.300
[Guest]: maybe something can happen.

02:51:03.300 --> 02:51:04.740
[Guest]: So that was my first hit of reality,

02:51:04.740 --> 02:51:05.220
[Guest]: that was,

02:51:06.100 --> 02:51:07.700
[Guest]: you know these political things,

02:51:07.700 --> 02:51:08.740
[Guest]: jo aapko lagta hai na ki,

02:51:10.260 --> 02:51:12.180
[Guest]: baat karo aise nahi hota hai.

02:51:12.180 --> 02:51:12.980
[Guest]: Second I realized,

02:51:12.980 --> 02:51:14.820
[Guest]: ki I was so ignorant about campus.

02:51:14.820 --> 02:51:16.100
[Guest]: Mereko uswaq toh mai,

02:51:16.100 --> 02:51:17.300
[Guest]: hota hai na dil pigal gaya aapka,

02:51:18.180 --> 02:51:20.660
[Guest]: ki people are sitting toh kuch kar lete hain.

02:51:20.660 --> 02:51:22.500
[Guest]: But you don't know the complete story,

02:51:22.500 --> 02:51:23.780
[Guest]: you don't know their history.

02:51:23.780 --> 02:51:25.220
[Guest]: So how complex the issue was,

02:51:25.780 --> 02:51:27.540
[Guest]: I had to go to professors to understand

02:51:27.540 --> 02:51:28.900
[Guest]: and still I could not.

02:51:28.900 --> 02:51:30.100
[Guest]: The thing I regret is,

02:51:30.100 --> 02:51:31.060
[Guest]: ki yeh sab maine kar liya,

02:51:31.060 --> 02:51:31.860
[Guest]: I didn't write about it.

02:51:33.460 --> 02:51:35.700
[Guest]: Because I was so involved in solving the problem,

02:51:35.700 --> 02:51:38.100
[Guest]: that I lost the fact that as the,

02:51:39.300 --> 02:51:40.740
[Guest]: like I was also a reporter right,

02:51:40.740 --> 02:51:41.460
[Guest]: ki likhna hai,

02:51:41.460 --> 02:51:42.980
[Guest]: maine story nahi likhi uspe kabhi.

02:51:42.980 --> 02:51:46.420
[Guest]: Because, and that left a deep regret in me till date,

02:51:46.980 --> 02:51:48.100
[Guest]: ki uswaq kya hua tha.

02:51:48.100 --> 02:51:50.260
[Guest]: And I went to campus in 2019,

02:51:50.260 --> 02:51:51.060
[Guest]: you know the thing I,

02:51:51.780 --> 02:51:52.660
[Guest]: still happens is that,

02:51:52.660 --> 02:51:53.780
[Guest]: those people still remember me.

02:51:54.820 --> 02:51:55.620
[Guest]: Unko jaisi,

02:51:55.620 --> 02:51:58.020
[Guest]: I asked my friend to book a room for me in a hostel,

02:51:58.020 --> 02:51:59.540
[Guest]: jaisi unhone naam dekha,

02:51:59.540 --> 02:52:00.100
[Guest]: and they were like,

02:52:00.100 --> 02:52:00.420
[Guest]: you know,

02:52:02.020 --> 02:52:03.300
[Guest]: this guy will help us.

02:52:03.300 --> 02:52:05.140
[Guest]: So they had the expectations and,

02:52:05.140 --> 02:52:05.860
[Guest]: unhone again bulaya hai,

02:52:05.860 --> 02:52:06.020
[Guest]: they said,

02:52:06.020 --> 02:52:07.460
[Guest]: ab humare sar yeh problem ho rahi hai,

02:52:07.460 --> 02:52:08.500
[Guest]: aap humari help karo.

02:52:08.500 --> 02:52:09.380
[Guest]: They got all the documents,

02:52:09.380 --> 02:52:10.340
[Guest]: photocopy kar aapke leya hai.

02:52:10.980 --> 02:52:12.580
[Guest]: And so I'm saying that,

02:52:12.580 --> 02:52:13.700
[Guest]: that lens when I got,

02:52:13.700 --> 02:52:15.700
[Guest]: which continues till date,

02:52:15.700 --> 02:52:16.420
[Guest]: it showed me that,

02:52:16.420 --> 02:52:16.660
[Guest]: you know,

02:52:16.660 --> 02:52:18.100
[Guest]: maybe I'm not looking at the world,

02:52:19.460 --> 02:52:21.780
[Guest]: like there's so many other things that are happening,

02:52:21.780 --> 02:52:23.540
[Guest]: and we are not looking at it.

02:52:23.540 --> 02:52:24.180
[Guest]: Like I'm,

02:52:24.180 --> 02:52:25.940
[Guest]: maine hain chaar saal nikal diye,

02:52:25.940 --> 02:52:28.020
[Guest]: and I never thought about those things.

02:52:28.980 --> 02:52:30.420
[Guest]: Right, then I also saw ek baar,

02:52:30.420 --> 02:52:31.540
[Guest]: Jadavpur University mein,

02:52:32.420 --> 02:52:34.180
[Guest]: I think 14 mein hua tha yeh,

02:52:34.180 --> 02:52:34.980
[Guest]: there was a protest,

02:52:34.980 --> 02:52:36.020
[Guest]: there was this girl,

02:52:36.020 --> 02:52:38.020
[Guest]: who had filed a complaint of molestation,

02:52:38.580 --> 02:52:40.740
[Guest]: and the administration did not respond properly.

02:52:40.740 --> 02:52:43.460
[Guest]: And students staged a protest,

02:52:43.460 --> 02:52:46.020
[Guest]: and police was called,

02:52:46.020 --> 02:52:47.140
[Guest]: and the students were beaten.

02:52:47.700 --> 02:52:48.740
[Guest]: So to support,

02:52:48.740 --> 02:52:51.060
[Guest]: to show solidarity in campus across India,

02:52:51.060 --> 02:52:53.940
[Guest]: there were candle march protests were happening,

02:52:53.940 --> 02:52:54.500
[Guest]: like, you know.

02:52:55.380 --> 02:52:56.180
[Guest]: Toh maine padha,

02:52:56.180 --> 02:52:56.980
[Guest]: maine ka hum bhi karenge,

02:52:57.700 --> 02:52:59.060
[Guest]: I went to my friend,

02:52:59.060 --> 02:53:00.100
[Guest]: who was in the student government,

02:53:00.100 --> 02:53:00.580
[Guest]: I said, you know,

02:53:00.580 --> 02:53:01.460
[Guest]: boss, karana hai,

02:53:01.460 --> 02:53:02.180
[Guest]: usne mana kar diya.

02:53:03.220 --> 02:53:04.260
[Guest]: He said no.

02:53:04.260 --> 02:53:05.220
[Guest]: And he's one of the,

02:53:06.340 --> 02:53:07.380
[Guest]: politically conscious,

02:53:08.100 --> 02:53:09.220
[Guest]: very smart guy.

02:53:09.220 --> 02:53:09.940
[Guest]: Sai nahi,

02:53:09.940 --> 02:53:12.580
[Guest]: as a student gymkhana of IIT Kanpur,

02:53:12.580 --> 02:53:14.580
[Guest]: we don't engage in outside politics.

02:53:14.580 --> 02:53:15.460
[Guest]: I was so angry.

02:53:16.260 --> 02:53:16.500
[Guest]: Ki,

02:53:17.460 --> 02:53:19.060
[Guest]: kal koi humare saath bhi hoga na.

02:53:19.060 --> 02:53:21.380
[Guest]: Like, I have this thing about administration,

02:53:21.380 --> 02:53:22.100
[Guest]: I've written about it.

02:53:23.060 --> 02:53:23.620
[Guest]: Toh maine ka,

02:53:23.620 --> 02:53:24.180
[Guest]: theek hai.

02:53:24.180 --> 02:53:24.980
[Guest]: So that, you know,

02:53:24.980 --> 02:53:25.860
[Guest]: maha se,

02:53:25.860 --> 02:53:26.980
[Guest]: ko na the sense of rebellion,

02:53:28.100 --> 02:53:28.660
[Guest]: mala,

02:53:28.660 --> 02:53:30.260
[Guest]: who are these to tell me ki,

02:53:30.260 --> 02:53:32.740
[Guest]: hum Jadavpur University ke students ko support nahi karenge.

02:53:32.740 --> 02:53:33.460
[Guest]: Toh maine ka,

02:53:33.460 --> 02:53:34.500
[Guest]: jo karna hai karo.

02:53:34.500 --> 02:53:35.060
[Guest]: I met,

02:53:35.620 --> 02:53:36.660
[Guest]: bunch of PG students,

02:53:36.660 --> 02:53:37.220
[Guest]: because they are more,

02:53:37.220 --> 02:53:37.540
[Guest]: you know,

02:53:38.100 --> 02:53:39.460
[Guest]: unlike undergraduates,

02:53:39.460 --> 02:53:40.660
[Guest]: post-graduate students are more,

02:53:41.700 --> 02:53:42.500
[Guest]: they think beyond.

02:53:43.140 --> 02:53:44.500
[Guest]: They're more politically conscious.

02:53:44.500 --> 02:53:45.540
[Guest]: Toh humne kara.

02:53:45.540 --> 02:53:46.100
[Guest]: And,

02:53:46.100 --> 02:53:46.820
[Guest]: humne posters,

02:53:46.820 --> 02:53:47.140
[Guest]: hostar,

02:53:47.140 --> 02:53:48.820
[Guest]: sabhaaye karwaya.

02:53:48.820 --> 02:53:49.380
[Guest]: And,

02:53:49.380 --> 02:53:50.340
[Guest]: on the day it was planned,

02:53:50.340 --> 02:53:52.340
[Guest]: 100 students scattered at the open-air theatre.

02:53:52.980 --> 02:53:53.540
[Guest]: And humne ka,

02:53:53.540 --> 02:53:53.780
[Unknown]: you know,

02:53:55.140 --> 02:53:56.100
[Guest]: agar ek baar ikathe ho gaye,

02:53:56.100 --> 02:53:57.300
[Guest]: toh yeh log kya karenge.

02:53:57.300 --> 02:53:57.860
[Guest]: Right?

02:53:57.860 --> 02:53:59.460
[Guest]: I didn't take any permissions.

02:53:59.460 --> 02:54:00.180
[Guest]: We were there.

02:54:00.180 --> 02:54:00.500
[Guest]: Humne ka,

02:54:00.500 --> 02:54:01.300
[Guest]: chalo now,

02:54:01.300 --> 02:54:02.580
[Guest]: because the only thing was those,

02:54:03.140 --> 02:54:03.460
[Guest]: like,

02:54:04.020 --> 02:54:05.700
[Guest]: why are you not allowing me,

02:54:05.700 --> 02:54:06.580
[Guest]: in my campus,

02:54:06.580 --> 02:54:08.980
[Guest]: to express support for students in another campus?

02:54:08.980 --> 02:54:09.940
[Guest]: Who are you?

02:54:09.940 --> 02:54:11.060
[Guest]: Why can the dean stop me?

02:54:11.620 --> 02:54:12.660
[Guest]: Toh humne wo march kiya.

02:54:12.660 --> 02:54:13.380
[Guest]: And in fact,

02:54:13.380 --> 02:54:14.260
[Guest]: jab bachche aagaye toh,

02:54:14.260 --> 02:54:15.940
[Guest]: the security could not do anything.

02:54:15.940 --> 02:54:16.340
[Guest]: So, you know,

02:54:16.340 --> 02:54:17.300
[Guest]: then you start feeling that,

02:54:17.300 --> 02:54:18.020
[Guest]: you know,

02:54:18.020 --> 02:54:18.900
[Guest]: challenge authority,

02:54:18.900 --> 02:54:19.400
[Guest]: yaar.

02:54:20.180 --> 02:54:20.980
[Guest]: Because hum,

02:54:20.980 --> 02:54:22.820
[Guest]: we're not even slogans bhi nahi kar rahe the.

02:54:22.820 --> 02:54:24.020
[Guest]: We just wanted to,

02:54:24.020 --> 02:54:25.380
[Guest]: peacefully march,

02:54:25.380 --> 02:54:26.420
[Guest]: to support,

02:54:26.420 --> 02:54:27.860
[Guest]: fellow students at another campus.

02:54:28.660 --> 02:54:29.060
[Guest]: Right?

02:54:29.060 --> 02:54:30.420
[Guest]: How can you say that,

02:54:30.420 --> 02:54:32.100
[Guest]: we don't engage in outside politics?

02:54:32.900 --> 02:54:33.460
[Guest]: Right?

02:54:33.460 --> 02:54:34.980
[Guest]: So, I think wo build up hota gaya yaha se,

02:54:34.980 --> 02:54:35.380
[Guest]: that you know,

02:54:35.940 --> 02:54:36.980
[Guest]: it's not just about,

02:54:36.980 --> 02:54:37.860
[Guest]: main wahan se start hua,

02:54:37.860 --> 02:54:38.100
[Guest]: right?

02:54:38.100 --> 02:54:40.180
[Guest]: Campus hai, but campus mein aur log hain.

02:54:40.180 --> 02:54:41.300
[Guest]: Sir hamara hi campus nahi hai,

02:54:41.300 --> 02:54:42.020
[Guest]: there are other students,

02:54:42.020 --> 02:54:43.060
[Guest]: there are also us.

02:54:43.060 --> 02:54:44.580
[Guest]: So, that consciousness started building up.

02:54:45.220 --> 02:54:46.180
[Guest]: And parallelly,

02:54:46.180 --> 02:54:46.740
[Guest]: you know,

02:54:46.740 --> 02:54:46.980
[Guest]: I mean,

02:54:46.980 --> 02:54:48.340
[Guest]: I'm saying this is the political part of it,

02:54:48.340 --> 02:54:48.740
[Guest]: right?

02:54:48.740 --> 02:54:49.700
[Guest]: And other things are happening.

02:54:49.700 --> 02:54:51.220
[Guest]: So, in all this journey,

02:54:51.220 --> 02:54:52.020
[Guest]: I think my,

02:54:52.020 --> 02:54:52.740
[Guest]: I developed,

02:54:53.300 --> 02:54:54.180
[Guest]: more empathy,

02:54:54.180 --> 02:54:54.660
[Guest]: when,

02:54:54.660 --> 02:54:55.060
[Guest]: like,

02:54:55.060 --> 02:54:56.180
[Guest]: politically conscious toh main hua hai,

02:54:56.180 --> 02:54:56.740
[Guest]: but empathy.

02:54:56.740 --> 02:54:57.220
[Guest]: Because,

02:54:57.220 --> 02:54:59.140
[Guest]: I reported a story about,

02:54:59.140 --> 02:55:01.140
[Guest]: the struggles of Hindi medium students,

02:55:01.140 --> 02:55:01.860
[Guest]: in campus.

02:55:01.860 --> 02:55:03.140
[Guest]: It blew me away.

02:55:03.140 --> 02:55:03.780
[Guest]: Because,

02:55:03.780 --> 02:55:05.140
[Guest]: when I spoke to this guy,

02:55:05.140 --> 02:55:05.640
[Guest]: the junior,

02:55:06.260 --> 02:55:06.980
[Guest]: he told me ki,

02:55:06.980 --> 02:55:07.780
[Guest]: boss,

02:55:07.780 --> 02:55:08.900
[Guest]: main apne wing mein,

02:55:08.900 --> 02:55:10.180
[Guest]: compared to everyone else,

02:55:10.180 --> 02:55:11.060
[Guest]: main saari class jaata hu,

02:55:11.060 --> 02:55:12.260
[Guest]: I attend all classes.

02:55:12.260 --> 02:55:13.220
[Guest]: I work triple hard,

02:55:13.940 --> 02:55:15.140
[Guest]: to take notes,

02:55:15.140 --> 02:55:15.780
[Guest]: right?

02:55:15.780 --> 02:55:17.140
[Guest]: When everyone is playing,

02:55:18.180 --> 02:55:19.060
[Guest]: you know,

02:55:19.060 --> 02:55:19.620
[Guest]: cricket,

02:55:19.620 --> 02:55:20.340
[Guest]: and watching movies,

02:55:20.340 --> 02:55:21.220
[Guest]: I study.

02:55:21.220 --> 02:55:22.500
[Guest]: And still I get less grades.

02:55:23.140 --> 02:55:24.180
[Guest]: And still I know when,

02:55:24.180 --> 02:55:25.380
[Guest]: I'll be at the job market.

02:55:26.740 --> 02:55:27.060
[Guest]: You know,

02:55:27.060 --> 02:55:27.940
[Guest]: no one is going to hire me,

02:55:27.940 --> 02:55:28.980
[Guest]: because I can't speak English.

02:55:30.340 --> 02:55:30.900
[Guest]: And again,

02:55:30.900 --> 02:55:31.540
[Guest]: I thought that,

02:55:32.340 --> 02:55:34.180
[Guest]: I am talking to him now as a reporter,

02:55:34.180 --> 02:55:34.340
[Guest]: like,

02:55:34.340 --> 02:55:34.500
[Guest]: you know,

02:55:34.500 --> 02:55:36.020
[Guest]: as a journalist who wants to write a story,

02:55:36.020 --> 02:55:36.660
[Guest]: in the campus.

02:55:36.660 --> 02:55:37.460
[Guest]: But,

02:55:37.460 --> 02:55:39.220
[Guest]: there would be people like him in my batch.

02:55:39.860 --> 02:55:41.620
[Guest]: And I was blind to it.

02:55:41.620 --> 02:55:41.860
[Guest]: You know,

02:55:41.860 --> 02:55:42.420
[Guest]: so,

02:55:42.420 --> 02:55:43.300
[Guest]: I'm saying,

02:55:43.300 --> 02:55:44.340
[Guest]: you know what I'm trying to say that,

02:55:45.700 --> 02:55:46.260
[Guest]: these,

02:55:46.820 --> 02:55:48.020
[Guest]: ideas started coming in.

02:55:48.020 --> 02:55:48.740
[Guest]: And I think,

02:55:48.740 --> 02:55:49.060
[Guest]: that,

02:55:49.060 --> 02:55:50.260
[Guest]: that's what I meant when I said,

02:55:50.260 --> 02:55:50.500
[Guest]: you know,

02:55:50.500 --> 02:55:51.460
[Guest]: it shaped me.

02:55:51.460 --> 02:55:51.860
[Guest]: That,

02:55:51.860 --> 02:55:53.300
[Guest]: the shaping was happening in two parts.

02:55:53.300 --> 02:55:54.100
[Guest]: One was,

02:55:54.100 --> 02:55:55.220
[Guest]: thik hai bahar ka kuch nahi pata hai,

02:55:55.220 --> 02:55:57.060
[Guest]: but campus toh mujhe samajh aa raha tha.

02:55:57.060 --> 02:55:58.500
[Guest]: That there are things that I was not seeing.

02:55:58.500 --> 02:55:59.220
[Guest]: And parallelly,

02:55:59.220 --> 02:55:59.460
[Guest]: you know,

02:55:59.460 --> 02:56:00.420
[Guest]: I was meeting,

02:56:00.420 --> 02:56:01.300
[Guest]: and reading about,

02:56:01.300 --> 02:56:02.740
[Guest]: all our illustrious alumni.

02:56:03.380 --> 02:56:03.860
[Guest]: Right?

02:56:03.860 --> 02:56:05.140
[Guest]: Someone is making films,

02:56:05.620 --> 02:56:06.580
[Guest]: someone is making movies,

02:56:06.580 --> 02:56:08.180
[Guest]: someone has built a unicorn company,

02:56:08.180 --> 02:56:08.740
[Guest]: you know,

02:56:08.740 --> 02:56:09.620
[Guest]: someone has done this,

02:56:09.620 --> 02:56:10.820
[Guest]: brilliant research in the US.

02:56:11.380 --> 02:56:12.100
[Guest]: You know,

02:56:12.100 --> 02:56:13.780
[Guest]: the fortune 500 CEOs,

02:56:13.780 --> 02:56:14.260
[Guest]: you know,

02:56:14.260 --> 02:56:15.700
[Guest]: these people would come to campus.

02:56:16.340 --> 02:56:18.180
[Guest]: And you just feel boss ki,

02:56:18.180 --> 02:56:18.740
[Guest]: if you think,

02:56:19.460 --> 02:56:20.180
[Guest]: and you,

02:56:20.180 --> 02:56:21.220
[Guest]: you are inspired by them,

02:56:21.220 --> 02:56:21.620
[Guest]: right?

02:56:21.620 --> 02:56:22.820
[Guest]: Ki agar inhone kar hai,

02:56:22.820 --> 02:56:23.540
[Guest]: and they would come,

02:56:23.540 --> 02:56:24.980
[Guest]: they would have chai with you.

02:56:24.980 --> 02:56:25.220
[Guest]: Right?

02:56:25.220 --> 02:56:25.860
[Guest]: These big people.

02:56:26.660 --> 02:56:27.220
[Guest]: And,

02:56:27.220 --> 02:56:28.820
[Guest]: they tell you stories from the campus,

02:56:28.820 --> 02:56:29.620
[Guest]: which you feel ki yaar,

02:56:29.620 --> 02:56:30.900
[Guest]: hamara bhi toh yeh story hai.

02:56:30.900 --> 02:56:32.420
[Guest]: So, I think you get that confidence ki,

02:56:32.420 --> 02:56:34.900
[Guest]: like they were also idiots like we are.

02:56:34.900 --> 02:56:35.460
[Guest]: Right?

02:56:35.460 --> 02:56:36.180
[Guest]: Unka bhi aise tha,

02:56:36.180 --> 02:56:36.820
[Guest]: toh you know,

02:56:36.820 --> 02:56:37.860
[Guest]: kuch bhi kar sakte hain.

02:56:37.860 --> 02:56:38.900
[Guest]: So, these things were happening

02:56:38.900 --> 02:56:40.180
[Guest]: that gave me a lot of confidence.

02:56:40.740 --> 02:56:41.380
[Guest]: And,

02:56:41.380 --> 02:56:42.820
[Guest]: that's how IIT shaped me.

02:56:42.820 --> 02:56:43.460
[Guest]: I mean,

02:56:43.460 --> 02:56:44.260
[Guest]: koi mein keh rahe hoon,

02:56:44.260 --> 02:56:44.580
[Guest]: I mean,

02:56:44.580 --> 02:56:45.860
[Guest]: I have spoken a lot,

02:56:45.860 --> 02:56:47.300
[Guest]: but I'll stop here.

02:56:47.300 --> 02:56:48.420
[Guest]: But I'm saying,

02:56:48.420 --> 02:56:49.620
[Guest]: at multiple levels,

02:56:49.620 --> 02:56:51.220
[Guest]: both from political consciousness to,

02:56:51.780 --> 02:56:52.820
[Guest]: inspiration,

02:56:52.820 --> 02:56:54.580
[Guest]: to seeing the traps that I told you about,

02:56:54.580 --> 02:56:54.820
[Guest]: right?

02:56:54.820 --> 02:56:55.540
[Guest]: In the beginning,

02:56:55.540 --> 02:56:57.620
[Guest]: ki I started seeing traps where,

02:56:57.620 --> 02:56:58.340
[Guest]: we were stuck.

02:56:59.060 --> 02:57:00.180
[Guest]: So, all of those together,

02:57:00.180 --> 02:57:00.740
[Guest]: I think,

02:57:00.740 --> 02:57:02.420
[Guest]: at least got me thinking that,

02:57:02.980 --> 02:57:04.420
[Guest]: the world is not what it is.

02:57:04.420 --> 02:57:05.220
[Guest]: There are layers.

02:57:05.780 --> 02:57:07.140
[Guest]: And if you look at them deeply,

02:57:07.140 --> 02:57:08.420
[Guest]: you will really understand

02:57:08.420 --> 02:57:08.980
[Guest]: what is happening.

02:57:09.700 --> 02:57:10.260
[Guest]: And,

02:57:10.260 --> 02:57:13.060
[Amit Varma]: what strikes me in all this is that,

02:57:13.780 --> 02:57:14.900
[Amit Varma]: we live in a world,

02:57:14.900 --> 02:57:16.660
[Amit Varma]: which is full of bubbles,

02:57:16.660 --> 02:57:18.180
[Amit Varma]: which is full of preset tracks,

02:57:18.180 --> 02:57:19.380
[Amit Varma]: which go a particular way

02:57:19.380 --> 02:57:20.900
[Amit Varma]: and don't go anywhere else.

02:57:20.900 --> 02:57:21.700
[Amit Varma]: And traps,

02:57:21.700 --> 02:57:22.500
[Amit Varma]: as you said.

02:57:22.500 --> 02:57:24.900
[Amit Varma]: So, a lot of these people who are in IIT,

02:57:24.900 --> 02:57:26.980
[Amit Varma]: IIT karke shayad koi IIM jayega,

02:57:26.980 --> 02:57:28.180
[Amit Varma]: consultant banega,

02:57:28.180 --> 02:57:29.620
[Amit Varma]: shayad koi abroad jayega,

02:57:29.620 --> 02:57:30.820
[Amit Varma]: shayad koi abroad jayega,

02:57:30.820 --> 02:57:31.940
[Amit Varma]: research karega,

02:57:31.940 --> 02:57:33.220
[Amit Varma]: brilliant kaam karega,

02:57:33.220 --> 02:57:34.820
[Amit Varma]: shayad koi software engineer karega,

02:57:34.820 --> 02:57:35.940
[Amit Varma]: Facebook mein jayega.

02:57:35.940 --> 02:57:37.380
[Amit Varma]: And these are different tracks.

02:57:37.380 --> 02:57:38.340
[Amit Varma]: And you're all in your bubble

02:57:38.340 --> 02:57:39.860
[Amit Varma]: and you're not looking out.

02:57:39.860 --> 02:57:40.900
[Amit Varma]: And you said that,

02:57:40.900 --> 02:57:42.100
[Amit Varma]: and they're not looking out.

02:57:42.100 --> 02:57:43.620
[Amit Varma]: And you said that,

02:57:43.620 --> 02:57:44.260
[Amit Varma]: one of course,

02:57:44.260 --> 02:57:45.540
[Amit Varma]: you avoided these tracks

02:57:45.540 --> 02:57:46.420
[Amit Varma]: by saying things like,

02:57:46.420 --> 02:57:48.340
[Amit Varma]: ki theek hai main placement mein nahi jaunga,

02:57:48.340 --> 02:57:50.020
[Amit Varma]: main wo game nahi khelunga,

02:57:50.020 --> 02:57:51.380
[Amit Varma]: main apna kaam karunga.

02:57:51.380 --> 02:57:53.380
[Amit Varma]: And you're also looking outside the bubble

02:57:53.380 --> 02:57:56.020
[Amit Varma]: and looking kind of beyond these layers.

02:57:56.020 --> 02:57:57.620
[Amit Varma]: And I realized while growing up also,

02:57:57.620 --> 02:57:58.500
[Amit Varma]: when I kind of,

02:57:58.500 --> 02:58:01.860
[Amit Varma]: kind of map my own sort of journey,

02:58:01.860 --> 02:58:02.580
[Amit Varma]: it's very clear

02:58:02.580 --> 02:58:04.020
[Amit Varma]: that there are all these layers

02:58:04.020 --> 02:58:04.900
[Amit Varma]: which make you blind

02:58:04.900 --> 02:58:06.820
[Amit Varma]: to different aspects of the world.

02:58:06.820 --> 02:58:08.100
[Amit Varma]: And then at different point,

02:58:08.100 --> 02:58:10.340
[Amit Varma]: these layers kind of start falling away.

02:58:10.340 --> 02:58:13.140
[Amit Varma]: So my first question arising from this is that,

02:58:14.100 --> 02:58:15.140
[Amit Varma]: do you think that

02:58:15.780 --> 02:58:19.700
[Amit Varma]: it's not just a question of IIT changing you?

02:58:19.700 --> 02:58:21.780
[Amit Varma]: It is also a question of you

02:58:21.780 --> 02:58:23.780
[Amit Varma]: being the kind of person inherently

02:58:23.780 --> 02:58:25.380
[Amit Varma]: who would be changed by IIT.

02:58:26.100 --> 02:58:28.180
[Amit Varma]: Kyuki the experiences you went through

02:58:28.180 --> 02:58:29.700
[Amit Varma]: would be common to everyone.

02:58:29.700 --> 02:58:31.060
[Amit Varma]: Campus toh same hai.

02:58:31.060 --> 02:58:32.660
[Amit Varma]: You know, jo ho raha hai, same hai.

02:58:32.660 --> 02:58:34.660
[Amit Varma]: But your nazariya is different.

02:58:34.660 --> 02:58:35.700
[Amit Varma]: You are, you know,

02:58:35.700 --> 02:58:37.380
[Amit Varma]: you're pursuing different things.

02:58:37.380 --> 02:58:38.740
[Amit Varma]: And from that,

02:58:38.740 --> 02:58:40.260
[Amit Varma]: different chains of events happen,

02:58:40.260 --> 02:58:41.300
[Amit Varma]: which, you know,

02:58:41.300 --> 02:58:43.940
[Amit Varma]: lead you to change in the ways that you say.

02:58:43.940 --> 02:58:45.780
[Amit Varma]: So what I'm trying to say is that

02:58:45.780 --> 02:58:47.540
[Amit Varma]: it's a two-way process, you know.

02:58:48.340 --> 02:58:50.340
[Amit Varma]: It's not just that the right things happened,

02:58:50.340 --> 02:58:51.780
[Amit Varma]: but you were also the right person

02:58:51.780 --> 02:58:52.820
[Amit Varma]: for them to happen too.

02:58:53.380 --> 02:58:54.580
[Amit Varma]: While for somebody else,

02:58:55.220 --> 02:58:55.720
[Amit Varma]: you know,

02:58:56.260 --> 02:58:56.900
[Amit Varma]: for them,

02:58:56.900 --> 02:58:58.740
[Amit Varma]: whatever track they took was the right track

02:58:58.740 --> 02:59:00.180
[Amit Varma]: that they went down on.

02:59:00.180 --> 02:59:01.460
[Amit Varma]: So when you look at yourself,

02:59:01.460 --> 02:59:02.820
[Amit Varma]: do you, like earlier,

02:59:02.820 --> 02:59:04.340
[Amit Varma]: before we started recording,

02:59:04.340 --> 02:59:05.700
[Amit Varma]: you were speaking about

02:59:05.700 --> 02:59:07.700
[Amit Varma]: how you developed this ethical sense

02:59:07.700 --> 02:59:09.300
[Amit Varma]: right from the time that you were in school.

02:59:09.860 --> 02:59:11.780
[Amit Varma]: So do you think there was something there,

02:59:11.780 --> 02:59:13.700
[Amit Varma]: something fundamental about you

02:59:13.700 --> 02:59:15.860
[Amit Varma]: that made you open to this change?

02:59:15.860 --> 02:59:16.980
[Amit Varma]: And if so,

02:59:17.620 --> 02:59:18.740
[Amit Varma]: where did it come from,

02:59:18.740 --> 02:59:19.940
[Amit Varma]: this sense of injustice

02:59:19.940 --> 02:59:22.020
[Amit Varma]: or the sense of trying to be a change agent?

02:59:22.020 --> 02:59:23.700
[Amit Varma]: You know, did it also,

02:59:23.700 --> 02:59:26.420
[Amit Varma]: and can you elaborate on what you had meant earlier

02:59:26.420 --> 02:59:29.140
[Amit Varma]: while talking about the ethical aspect of it?

02:59:29.140 --> 02:59:30.500
[Unknown]: And you've kind of spoken about that

02:59:30.500 --> 02:59:32.100
[Amit Varma]: a little bit here also,

02:59:32.100 --> 02:59:33.300
[Amit Varma]: you know, just sort of,

02:59:33.860 --> 02:59:36.660
[Amit Varma]: I want to understand the sense of

02:59:36.660 --> 02:59:37.620
[Amit Varma]: how you were shaped

02:59:37.620 --> 02:59:38.900
[Amit Varma]: and where you were coming from.

02:59:39.540 --> 02:59:40.100
[Guest]: Yeah, I'll tell you,

02:59:40.100 --> 02:59:41.940
[Guest]: but, you know, I just want to add something,

02:59:41.940 --> 02:59:45.460
[Guest]: you know, I just get so passionate about my institute

02:59:45.460 --> 02:59:46.260
[Guest]: because, you know,

02:59:46.260 --> 02:59:47.940
[Guest]: I'm like one of the worst critics of IIT,

02:59:47.940 --> 02:59:49.380
[Guest]: but also one of the champions

02:59:49.380 --> 02:59:52.260
[Guest]: because I really think that institute has potential.

02:59:52.260 --> 02:59:54.020
[Guest]: And one of the things that I'm hating

02:59:54.580 --> 02:59:55.460
[Guest]: at the moment as I talk,

02:59:55.460 --> 02:59:56.420
[Guest]: I'm just speaking out loud,

02:59:56.980 --> 02:59:58.980
[Guest]: is that I just feel if I am painting some,

02:59:58.980 --> 03:00:01.300
[Guest]: you know, my institute in some broad brushstrokes

03:00:01.300 --> 03:00:02.420
[Guest]: as if, you know,

03:00:02.980 --> 03:00:04.740
[Guest]: you know, I am different

03:00:04.740 --> 03:00:06.340
[Guest]: and, you know, everyone is this,

03:00:07.380 --> 03:00:08.980
[Amit Varma]: but, you know, everyone has multitudes.

03:00:08.980 --> 03:00:11.060
[Amit Varma]: I think sometimes deep criticism

03:00:11.060 --> 03:00:12.340
[Amit Varma]: can come out of deep love.

03:00:12.340 --> 03:00:13.620
[Guest]: That's where the frustration comes from.

03:00:13.620 --> 03:00:16.980
[Guest]: It is, you know, I think I heard this quote from,

03:00:18.340 --> 03:00:19.620
[Guest]: what's the last lecture?

03:00:19.620 --> 03:00:20.420
[Guest]: Who's the professor?

03:00:20.420 --> 03:00:20.900
[Guest]: Have you seen?

03:00:21.780 --> 03:00:23.140
[Amit Varma]: Rosh? Randy Rosh?

03:00:23.140 --> 03:00:24.100
[Unknown]: Something like that.

03:00:24.100 --> 03:00:24.980
[Guest]: He said something like that,

03:00:24.980 --> 03:00:27.300
[Guest]: you know, if the exact words are not right,

03:00:27.300 --> 03:00:28.580
[Guest]: but something like that,

03:00:28.580 --> 03:00:29.540
[Guest]: if you're doing something wrong

03:00:29.540 --> 03:00:30.340
[Guest]: and no one is telling you,

03:00:30.340 --> 03:00:31.460
[Guest]: that means they have given up on you,

03:00:32.580 --> 03:00:33.940
[Guest]: you know, something like that.

03:00:33.940 --> 03:00:36.020
[Guest]: So I would never give up on my institute.

03:00:36.020 --> 03:00:36.900
[Guest]: And I still like,

03:00:36.900 --> 03:00:39.460
[Guest]: I think we are going on a very downward trajectory

03:00:39.460 --> 03:00:41.140
[Guest]: given the political environment of the country

03:00:41.140 --> 03:00:42.820
[Guest]: is affecting us, right?

03:00:42.820 --> 03:00:44.500
[Guest]: I was in the center

03:00:44.500 --> 03:00:46.340
[Guest]: when the CA and RC protests were happening.

03:00:46.340 --> 03:00:48.020
[Guest]: Something had happened at IIT Kanpur

03:00:48.020 --> 03:00:49.300
[Guest]: and I made it just blew my mind

03:00:49.300 --> 03:00:50.660
[Guest]: about how propaganda works.

03:00:50.660 --> 03:00:52.900
[Guest]: So I could see what is happening at my campus,

03:00:52.900 --> 03:00:53.540
[Guest]: but I still,

03:00:53.540 --> 03:00:54.980
[Guest]: you know, my friends,

03:00:54.980 --> 03:00:57.300
[Guest]: like some of my deepest friendships are from IIT,

03:00:57.300 --> 03:00:59.220
[Guest]: you know, and I'll always be grateful,

03:00:59.220 --> 03:01:01.540
[Guest]: but I'm just saying that I just feel a bit,

03:01:01.540 --> 03:01:02.500
[Guest]: because I'm, you know, speaking,

03:01:02.500 --> 03:01:04.260
[Guest]: I'm not writing a piece where I could,

03:01:04.820 --> 03:01:06.660
[Guest]: you know, I could have all sorts of caveats.

03:01:06.660 --> 03:01:08.580
[Guest]: It's just one-on-one conversation.

03:01:08.580 --> 03:01:10.980
[Guest]: So I just wanted to put that out that,

03:01:12.180 --> 03:01:14.180
[Guest]: yeah, I don't want to make,

03:01:14.180 --> 03:01:16.260
[Guest]: and I also feel honestly uncomfortable

03:01:16.260 --> 03:01:18.900
[Guest]: when I talk about my experience

03:01:18.900 --> 03:01:20.260
[Guest]: and if it sounds like,

03:01:20.820 --> 03:01:22.100
[Guest]: oh, I am different

03:01:22.100 --> 03:01:25.300
[Guest]: because that, it just makes me uncomfortable

03:01:25.300 --> 03:01:26.660
[Guest]: for reasons I don't know.

03:01:26.660 --> 03:01:27.700
[Amit Varma]: No, and I'll tell you something,

03:01:27.700 --> 03:01:28.820
[Amit Varma]: just thinking aloud,

03:01:28.820 --> 03:01:30.420
[Amit Varma]: that what you're saying about IIT,

03:01:30.420 --> 03:01:31.780
[Amit Varma]: I feel the same way about India.

03:01:32.340 --> 03:01:34.180
[Amit Varma]: You know, I will criticize,

03:01:34.180 --> 03:01:35.220
[Amit Varma]: I will keep doing it,

03:01:35.220 --> 03:01:37.300
[Amit Varma]: I will dissent, I will protest,

03:01:37.300 --> 03:01:39.060
[Amit Varma]: but I'm doing it because bloody hell,

03:01:39.060 --> 03:01:40.900
[Amit Varma]: I love this country and I want it to change, right?

03:01:40.900 --> 03:01:42.260
[Amit Varma]: That's where we're coming from, right?

03:01:42.260 --> 03:01:44.260
[Guest]: And what the funny thing Amit is that,

03:01:44.260 --> 03:01:45.300
[Guest]: I used to be in IIT,

03:01:45.300 --> 03:01:46.820
[Guest]: I used to sit on campus,

03:01:46.820 --> 03:01:49.860
[Guest]: I mean, I'm saying,

03:01:49.860 --> 03:01:52.340
[Guest]: I'm saying, I'm saying,

03:01:52.340 --> 03:01:55.460
[Guest]: but when someone outside,

03:01:56.100 --> 03:01:57.140
[Guest]: you know, the campus,

03:01:57.940 --> 03:01:58.660
[Guest]: criticizes,

03:01:58.660 --> 03:02:00.740
[Unknown]: right?

03:02:00.740 --> 03:02:04.900
[Guest]: So I've never,

03:02:04.900 --> 03:02:06.980
[Guest]: I think I don't think it that way,

03:02:06.980 --> 03:02:07.620
[Guest]: but you know,

03:02:07.620 --> 03:02:08.660
[Guest]: when you're inside the system,

03:02:08.660 --> 03:02:09.300
[Guest]: because like,

03:02:09.300 --> 03:02:14.180
[Guest]: I'll talk about how I got there,

03:02:14.180 --> 03:02:16.340
[Guest]: when I was still at a semester left,

03:02:16.340 --> 03:02:17.220
[Guest]: someone at the Hindu,

03:02:17.220 --> 03:02:19.860
[Guest]: I went to this person,

03:02:19.860 --> 03:02:21.060
[Guest]: to ask for some advice,

03:02:21.060 --> 03:02:24.580
[Guest]: and he said it was something about Kashmir,

03:02:24.580 --> 03:02:25.060
[Guest]: that I wanted,

03:02:25.060 --> 03:02:26.180
[Guest]: I said I don't know anything,

03:02:26.180 --> 03:02:28.980
[Guest]: I'm this ignorant person who has no idea,

03:02:28.980 --> 03:02:29.700
[Guest]: can you tell me,

03:02:29.700 --> 03:02:30.660
[Guest]: I want to read,

03:02:30.660 --> 03:02:31.460
[Guest]: I want to understand,

03:02:31.460 --> 03:02:32.820
[Guest]: because I don't know,

03:02:32.820 --> 03:02:33.540
[Guest]: so he told me something,

03:02:33.540 --> 03:02:35.700
[Guest]: and he made a snarky comment saying,

03:02:35.700 --> 03:02:37.380
[Guest]: they don't teach this in your IIT,

03:02:38.500 --> 03:02:39.780
[Guest]: so I was like,

03:02:39.780 --> 03:02:42.180
[Guest]: they teach you so much in IIT,

03:02:42.180 --> 03:02:44.740
[Guest]: that you should at least ask questions,

03:02:44.740 --> 03:02:46.180
[Guest]: I mean, my professors have taught me so much,

03:02:46.180 --> 03:02:47.860
[Guest]: that I'm asking you,

03:02:48.420 --> 03:02:49.300
[Guest]: now okay,

03:02:49.300 --> 03:02:51.460
[Guest]: I don't know enough about politics,

03:02:51.460 --> 03:02:52.260
[Guest]: I don't know,

03:02:52.260 --> 03:02:53.540
[Guest]: I didn't have consciousness at that time,

03:02:54.180 --> 03:02:54.980
[Guest]: so that I,

03:02:54.980 --> 03:02:55.860
[Guest]: you know,

03:02:55.860 --> 03:02:56.340
[Guest]: it happens,

03:02:56.340 --> 03:02:56.580
[Guest]: you know,

03:02:56.580 --> 03:02:56.980
[Guest]: when,

03:02:56.980 --> 03:02:58.020
[Guest]: which is why I was telling you,

03:02:58.020 --> 03:02:58.500
[Guest]: you know,

03:02:58.500 --> 03:03:00.100
[Guest]: you talk a lot about gentleman amnesia,

03:03:00.100 --> 03:03:00.580
[Guest]: right,

03:03:00.580 --> 03:03:02.420
[Guest]: in the effect that,

03:03:02.420 --> 03:03:03.620
[Guest]: you read something in the papers,

03:03:04.500 --> 03:03:05.300
[Unknown]: and it doesn't hit,

03:03:05.300 --> 03:03:06.580
[Guest]: so it happens a lot with me in IIT,

03:03:06.580 --> 03:03:07.780
[Guest]: you have reduced,

03:03:07.780 --> 03:03:08.820
[Guest]: most IIT people,

03:03:09.460 --> 03:03:09.700
[Guest]: you know,

03:03:09.700 --> 03:03:10.820
[Guest]: one story comes every year,

03:03:10.820 --> 03:03:12.340
[Guest]: one crore package is applied,

03:03:12.340 --> 03:03:12.660
[Guest]: right,

03:03:12.660 --> 03:03:13.220
[Guest]: and then you say,

03:03:13.220 --> 03:03:14.180
[Guest]: kids are like this,

03:03:14.180 --> 03:03:14.420
[Guest]: you know,

03:03:14.420 --> 03:03:15.860
[Guest]: people take jobs in banks,

03:03:15.860 --> 03:03:16.260
[Guest]: and you say,

03:03:17.060 --> 03:03:18.020
[Guest]: these are greedy people,

03:03:18.580 --> 03:03:18.820
[Guest]: you know,

03:03:18.820 --> 03:03:20.340
[Guest]: why are they going to the bank after doing engineering,

03:03:20.340 --> 03:03:20.900
[Guest]: I'm like,

03:03:20.900 --> 03:03:21.620
[Guest]: boss,

03:03:21.620 --> 03:03:22.580
[Guest]: do you know,

03:03:22.580 --> 03:03:24.020
[Guest]: how placement happens,

03:03:24.020 --> 03:03:24.340
[Guest]: what,

