[Guest]: I asked him why he was going,

03:08:40.900 --> 03:08:41.780
[Guest]: so he told me the reasons,

03:08:41.780 --> 03:08:42.980
[Guest]: and he said,

03:08:42.980 --> 03:08:45.220
[Guest]: one factor to pick a job was,

03:08:45.220 --> 03:08:48.020
[Guest]: I will head the ethics committee of any institute I go,

03:08:48.820 --> 03:08:49.860
[Guest]: if you don't give me that,

03:08:49.860 --> 03:08:51.300
[Guest]: I don't want to come to your institute,

03:08:51.300 --> 03:08:52.900
[Guest]: so I was so inspired that,

03:08:52.900 --> 03:08:53.700
[Guest]: you know,

03:08:53.700 --> 03:08:54.180
[Guest]: people,

03:08:54.180 --> 03:08:55.300
[Guest]: because at that age,

03:08:55.300 --> 03:08:56.740
[Guest]: you are told that you are an idealist,

03:08:57.460 --> 03:08:57.780
[Guest]: you know,

03:08:57.780 --> 03:08:58.820
[Guest]: this is not how the world works,

03:08:58.820 --> 03:08:59.460
[Guest]: you are naive,

03:09:00.020 --> 03:09:00.580
[Guest]: and I'm like,

03:09:00.580 --> 03:09:00.900
[Guest]: you know,

03:09:00.900 --> 03:09:01.620
[Guest]: look at this guy,

03:09:01.620 --> 03:09:04.980
[Guest]: he has all the accomplishments,

03:09:04.980 --> 03:09:06.580
[Guest]: he studied at this college,

03:09:06.580 --> 03:09:07.780
[Guest]: went for a US PhD,

03:09:07.780 --> 03:09:08.500
[Guest]: he's teaching here,

03:09:09.220 --> 03:09:10.580
[Guest]: and if he can stand for ethics,

03:09:11.380 --> 03:09:12.100
[Guest]: to like who,

03:09:12.100 --> 03:09:12.260
[Guest]: like,

03:09:13.140 --> 03:09:14.180
[Guest]: you should stand for ethics,

03:09:14.180 --> 03:09:14.660
[Guest]: so I'm saying,

03:09:16.180 --> 03:09:19.460
[Guest]: so I was so glad that you had some compass,

03:09:19.460 --> 03:09:21.940
[Guest]: about kind of things that are happening,

03:09:21.940 --> 03:09:24.820
[Guest]: and that is what about I think ethics,

03:09:24.820 --> 03:09:26.340
[Guest]: and that stayed with me,

03:09:26.340 --> 03:09:28.420
[Guest]: the current thing is that,

03:09:28.420 --> 03:09:29.940
[Guest]: I'm now in a different phase,

03:09:29.940 --> 03:09:31.620
[Guest]: where I started questioning,

03:09:32.980 --> 03:09:33.940
[Guest]: which is why,

03:09:33.940 --> 03:09:35.620
[Guest]: one of my current personal projects,

03:09:35.620 --> 03:09:37.460
[Guest]: is to go deep into moral psychology,

03:09:37.460 --> 03:09:38.580
[Guest]: and moral philosophy,

03:09:38.580 --> 03:09:38.980
[Guest]: because you know,

03:09:38.980 --> 03:09:40.100
[Guest]: then you start understanding,

03:09:41.620 --> 03:09:42.100
[Guest]: like,

03:09:42.100 --> 03:09:43.140
[Guest]: why am I like this,

03:09:43.140 --> 03:09:43.380
[Guest]: like,

03:09:43.380 --> 03:09:44.740
[Guest]: why do I believe this is right,

03:09:44.740 --> 03:09:45.300
[Guest]: this is wrong,

03:09:46.180 --> 03:09:47.380
[Guest]: what do I believe,

03:09:47.380 --> 03:09:48.180
[Guest]: is that rational,

03:09:48.180 --> 03:09:48.980
[Guest]: is it not rational,

03:09:50.980 --> 03:09:51.940
[Guest]: but I'm saying that time,

03:09:51.940 --> 03:09:52.580
[Guest]: I was living it,

03:09:52.580 --> 03:09:53.700
[Guest]: now I'm just thinking about it.

03:09:54.340 --> 03:09:54.660
[Amit Varma]: Earlier,

03:09:54.660 --> 03:09:56.660
[Amit Varma]: you'd mentioned Dawkins and Pinker,

03:09:56.660 --> 03:09:58.980
[Amit Varma]: and I remember when I went into the rabbit hole,

03:09:58.980 --> 03:10:00.660
[Amit Varma]: of evolutionary psychology,

03:10:00.660 --> 03:10:01.540
[Amit Varma]: and so on,

03:10:01.540 --> 03:10:02.980
[Amit Varma]: one book that I enjoyed reading,

03:10:02.980 --> 03:10:05.220
[Amit Varma]: was a moral animal by Robert Wright,

03:10:05.220 --> 03:10:06.740
[Amit Varma]: and where he talks about,

03:10:06.740 --> 03:10:08.260
[Amit Varma]: the evolution of morality,

03:10:08.260 --> 03:10:10.820
[Amit Varma]: from an evolutionary psychology perspective,

03:10:10.820 --> 03:10:11.860
[Amit Varma]: which was super interesting,

03:10:11.860 --> 03:10:12.980
[Amit Varma]: in which I'll recommend,

03:10:12.980 --> 03:10:14.180
[Amit Varma]: but what you know,

03:10:14.180 --> 03:10:15.780
[Amit Varma]: but one of the things you kind of realize,

03:10:15.780 --> 03:10:17.780
[Amit Varma]: is that we are hardwired,

03:10:17.780 --> 03:10:19.780
[Amit Varma]: in different contradictory ways,

03:10:19.780 --> 03:10:20.980
[Amit Varma]: through different processes,

03:10:20.980 --> 03:10:22.340
[Amit Varma]: for different reasons,

03:10:22.340 --> 03:10:23.860
[Amit Varma]: so we are hardwired of course,

03:10:23.860 --> 03:10:24.580
[Amit Varma]: to be selfish,

03:10:24.580 --> 03:10:26.740
[Amit Varma]: but we are also hardwired for altruism,

03:10:26.740 --> 03:10:28.820
[Amit Varma]: and all these things exist together,

03:10:28.820 --> 03:10:31.620
[Amit Varma]: and I love this phrase of Pinker,

03:10:31.620 --> 03:10:32.980
[Amit Varma]: where he's talking about,

03:10:32.980 --> 03:10:33.860
[Amit Varma]: nature and nurture,

03:10:33.860 --> 03:10:34.980
[Amit Varma]: how the two work together,

03:10:34.980 --> 03:10:35.460
[Amit Varma]: and he says,

03:10:35.460 --> 03:10:36.420
[Amit Varma]: nature gives you knobs,

03:10:36.420 --> 03:10:37.300
[Amit Varma]: nurture turns them,

03:10:38.020 --> 03:10:39.780
[Unknown]: and I found that very resonant,

03:10:39.780 --> 03:10:40.340
[Amit Varma]: right,

03:10:40.340 --> 03:10:41.780
[Amit Varma]: that there might be some knobs,

03:10:41.780 --> 03:10:42.900
[Amit Varma]: which are huge in you,

03:10:42.900 --> 03:10:44.020
[Amit Varma]: but nurture doesn't turn,

03:10:44.020 --> 03:10:45.220
[Unknown]: and there might be some knobs,

03:10:45.220 --> 03:10:46.340
[Amit Varma]: which are like medium knobs,

03:10:46.340 --> 03:10:47.620
[Amit Varma]: and nurture turns them or not,

03:10:47.620 --> 03:10:50.020
[Unknown]: and that's kind of amplified,

03:10:50.020 --> 03:10:51.860
[Amit Varma]: so just on that question,

03:10:51.860 --> 03:10:52.660
[Amit Varma]: I kind of wonder,

03:10:52.660 --> 03:10:54.260
[Amit Varma]: because you know,

03:10:54.260 --> 03:10:55.140
[Amit Varma]: and that's a question,

03:10:55.140 --> 03:10:58.100
[Amit Varma]: I often ask myself as well,

03:10:58.100 --> 03:10:58.820
[Amit Varma]: that you know,

03:10:59.540 --> 03:11:00.900
[Unknown]: how do we live our lives,

03:11:00.900 --> 03:11:02.260
[Amit Varma]: it's a central question,

03:11:02.260 --> 03:11:03.540
[Amit Varma]: ki meri kya hai,

03:11:03.540 --> 03:11:04.020
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:11:04.020 --> 03:11:05.700
[Amit Varma]: initially you can,

03:11:05.700 --> 03:11:06.020
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:11:06.020 --> 03:11:07.300
[Amit Varma]: get your sense of morality,

03:11:07.300 --> 03:11:09.540
[Amit Varma]: from whatever the conventional way of thinking,

03:11:09.540 --> 03:11:10.660
[Amit Varma]: might be in your family,

03:11:10.660 --> 03:11:11.700
[Amit Varma]: or your small community,

03:11:11.700 --> 03:11:12.420
[Amit Varma]: or whatever,

03:11:12.420 --> 03:11:12.740
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:11:13.380 --> 03:11:14.500
[Amit Varma]: and later on,

03:11:14.500 --> 03:11:17.140
[Amit Varma]: you can modify it as you read more,

03:11:17.140 --> 03:11:18.980
[Amit Varma]: sometimes you can rely on your instincts,

03:11:18.980 --> 03:11:20.820
[Amit Varma]: as you did when you saw that wrong spelling,

03:11:20.820 --> 03:11:22.260
[Unknown]: and you didn't change your spelling,

03:11:22.260 --> 03:11:22.500
[Unknown]: right,

03:11:22.500 --> 03:11:22.740
[Unknown]: you know,

03:11:22.740 --> 03:11:24.180
[Amit Varma]: where you're relying on an instinct,

03:11:24.180 --> 03:11:25.380
[Amit Varma]: and Wright's argument would be,

03:11:25.380 --> 03:11:26.420
[Amit Varma]: you're hardwired for that,

03:11:26.420 --> 03:11:29.780
[Amit Varma]: hmm, you are also hardwired to want to be first,

03:11:29.780 --> 03:11:30.420
[Amit Varma]: right,

03:11:30.420 --> 03:11:31.140
[Amit Varma]: but you know,

03:11:31.140 --> 03:11:32.020
[Unknown]: one overlap,

03:11:32.020 --> 03:11:32.260
[Unknown]: yeah,

03:11:33.060 --> 03:11:33.380
[Unknown]: this one,

03:11:33.380 --> 03:11:34.100
[Unknown]: one over,

03:11:34.100 --> 03:11:35.060
[Unknown]: and somebody else,

03:11:35.060 --> 03:11:36.020
[Amit Varma]: something else,

03:11:36.020 --> 03:11:37.060
[Amit Varma]: may kind of win over,

03:11:38.020 --> 03:11:39.700
[Amit Varma]: so that's something I think about,

03:11:39.700 --> 03:11:40.820
[Amit Varma]: because it is very clear,

03:11:40.820 --> 03:11:44.420
[Amit Varma]: that some people have a greater urge,

03:11:45.220 --> 03:11:46.260
[Amit Varma]: to be changemakers,

03:11:46.260 --> 03:11:47.940
[Amit Varma]: and some people have a greater urge,

03:11:47.940 --> 03:11:49.460
[Amit Varma]: to fight for fairness,

03:11:49.460 --> 03:11:51.700
[Amit Varma]: and I think there are two sides of that coin also,

03:11:51.700 --> 03:11:52.100
[Amit Varma]: yeah,

03:11:52.100 --> 03:11:53.060
[Amit Varma]: because you're,

03:11:53.060 --> 03:11:53.540
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:11:53.540 --> 03:11:55.300
[Amit Varma]: a lot of the moralizing that people do,

03:11:55.300 --> 03:11:57.620
[Amit Varma]: can sometimes be driven by self-aggrandizement,

03:11:58.260 --> 03:11:59.860
[Amit Varma]: they are posturing to themselves,

03:11:59.860 --> 03:12:00.900
[Amit Varma]: they're performing,

03:12:00.900 --> 03:12:02.260
[Amit Varma]: as you would say,

03:12:02.260 --> 03:12:03.300
[Amit Varma]: but at the same time,

03:12:03.300 --> 03:12:04.420
[Amit Varma]: in many cases,

03:12:04.420 --> 03:12:06.180
[Amit Varma]: it's genuine,

03:12:06.180 --> 03:12:07.540
[Amit Varma]: like I'm thinking of that incident,

03:12:07.540 --> 03:12:09.220
[Amit Varma]: when you didn't change the spelling,

03:12:09.220 --> 03:12:11.140
[Amit Varma]: you were not performing for anybody,

03:12:11.140 --> 03:12:11.460
[Amit Varma]: right,

03:12:11.460 --> 03:12:12.100
[Amit Varma]: there's nobody,

03:12:12.100 --> 03:12:12.900
[Amit Varma]: there's nothing,

03:12:12.900 --> 03:12:13.540
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:12:13.540 --> 03:12:14.660
[Amit Varma]: you could just have changed it,

03:12:14.660 --> 03:12:15.300
[Amit Varma]: and you didn't,

03:12:15.300 --> 03:12:18.420
[Amit Varma]: and that's also sort of there,

03:12:18.420 --> 03:12:20.580
[Amit Varma]: and I would imagine at some level,

03:12:20.580 --> 03:12:20.740
[Amit Varma]: like,

03:12:20.740 --> 03:12:22.100
[Amit Varma]: do you feel that at some level,

03:12:22.100 --> 03:12:23.540
[Amit Varma]: that ethical sense alone,

03:12:23.540 --> 03:12:26.420
[Amit Varma]: forget the intellectual understanding,

03:12:26.420 --> 03:12:27.860
[Amit Varma]: of the different games,

03:12:27.860 --> 03:12:29.620
[Unknown]: that are being played at IIT,

03:12:29.620 --> 03:12:30.500
[Unknown]: or journalism,

03:12:30.500 --> 03:12:32.660
[Unknown]: or all those different professions,

03:12:32.660 --> 03:12:34.660
[Amit Varma]: but did that ethical compass,

03:12:34.660 --> 03:12:36.340
[Amit Varma]: also have something to do,

03:12:36.340 --> 03:12:38.020
[Amit Varma]: with your being willing,

03:12:38.020 --> 03:12:39.380
[Amit Varma]: to turn your back on,

03:12:39.380 --> 03:12:40.820
[Amit Varma]: the conventional way of doing things,

03:12:40.820 --> 03:12:41.380
[Amit Varma]: and say,

03:12:41.380 --> 03:12:42.340
[Amit Varma]: I'll go to the hills.

03:12:44.260 --> 03:12:45.780
[Guest]: So I've thought about it Amit,

03:12:45.780 --> 03:12:47.060
[Guest]: and I don't know the answer,

03:12:47.060 --> 03:12:48.260
[Guest]: because again,

03:12:48.260 --> 03:12:49.940
[Guest]: I was telling you when I was saying,

03:12:50.820 --> 03:12:51.140
[Guest]: this,

03:12:51.140 --> 03:12:51.540
[Guest]: because see,

03:12:51.540 --> 03:12:52.420
[Guest]: ultimately when you say,

03:12:52.420 --> 03:12:53.140
[Guest]: convention,

03:12:53.140 --> 03:12:53.700
[Guest]: non-convention,

03:12:55.700 --> 03:12:56.740
[Guest]: I want to say two things,

03:12:56.740 --> 03:12:57.220
[Guest]: first of all,

03:12:57.220 --> 03:12:59.540
[Guest]: this whole idea of convention,

03:13:01.300 --> 03:13:04.100
[Guest]: that just feels a bit weird.

03:13:05.940 --> 03:13:07.540
[Guest]: So I was listening to Noam Chomsky,

03:13:07.540 --> 03:13:08.180
[Guest]: in a podcast,

03:13:08.180 --> 03:13:11.220
[Guest]: and he gave this frame that,

03:13:11.220 --> 03:13:11.540
[Guest]: you know,

03:13:11.540 --> 03:13:13.140
[Guest]: when you go to a school,

03:13:13.140 --> 03:13:13.620
[Guest]: college,

03:13:13.620 --> 03:13:14.180
[Guest]: right,

03:13:14.180 --> 03:13:14.660
[Guest]: he says,

03:13:14.660 --> 03:13:14.820
[Guest]: like,

03:13:14.820 --> 03:13:15.700
[Guest]: this is Chomsky's theory,

03:13:15.700 --> 03:13:16.180
[Guest]: I don't know,

03:13:17.140 --> 03:13:17.780
[Guest]: I've not read,

03:13:17.780 --> 03:13:18.580
[Guest]: apart from what he says,

03:13:18.580 --> 03:13:19.300
[Guest]: he says that,

03:13:19.300 --> 03:13:21.620
[Guest]: the fundamental human desire,

03:13:21.620 --> 03:13:22.020
[Guest]: you know,

03:13:22.020 --> 03:13:22.260
[Guest]: like,

03:13:22.260 --> 03:13:23.220
[Guest]: our instinct is freedom.

03:13:24.180 --> 03:13:24.980
[Guest]: Okay,

03:13:24.980 --> 03:13:26.180
[Guest]: humans want freedom,

03:13:26.180 --> 03:13:27.380
[Guest]: that's our ultimate quest.

03:13:27.940 --> 03:13:29.780
[Guest]: But the society is structured in a way,

03:13:30.500 --> 03:13:31.700
[Guest]: to suck that,

03:13:32.420 --> 03:13:33.620
[Guest]: willingness of freedom out of you.

03:13:34.500 --> 03:13:35.780
[Guest]: And your education,

03:13:35.780 --> 03:13:36.580
[Guest]: universities,

03:13:36.580 --> 03:13:37.780
[Guest]: your workplaces,

03:13:38.260 --> 03:13:40.020
[Guest]: they school you into believing that,

03:13:40.980 --> 03:13:41.620
[Guest]: you can't,

03:13:43.060 --> 03:13:43.460
[Guest]: like,

03:13:43.460 --> 03:13:44.180
[Guest]: like they,

03:13:44.180 --> 03:13:44.500
[Guest]: you know,

03:13:44.500 --> 03:13:46.180
[Guest]: take out the idea of freedom from you.

03:13:46.180 --> 03:13:46.500
[Guest]: Now,

03:13:46.500 --> 03:13:46.980
[Guest]: then you can ask,

03:13:46.980 --> 03:13:47.860
[Guest]: what is freedom?

03:13:47.860 --> 03:13:48.660
[Guest]: I think there is no,

03:13:48.660 --> 03:13:49.860
[Guest]: freedom in my head,

03:13:49.860 --> 03:13:50.420
[Guest]: like,

03:13:51.460 --> 03:13:52.580
[Guest]: you can't define it,

03:13:52.580 --> 03:13:52.900
[Guest]: it's,

03:13:52.900 --> 03:13:53.220
[Guest]: you know,

03:13:53.220 --> 03:13:53.780
[Guest]: it's,

03:13:53.780 --> 03:13:54.660
[Guest]: freedom is freedom,

03:13:54.660 --> 03:13:55.300
[Guest]: it's human freedom.

03:13:55.300 --> 03:13:55.620
[Guest]: Now,

03:13:55.620 --> 03:13:56.100
[Guest]: you,

03:13:56.100 --> 03:13:57.700
[Guest]: you think you are free,

03:13:57.700 --> 03:13:58.260
[Guest]: but you know,

03:13:58.260 --> 03:13:58.820
[Guest]: as I say,

03:13:58.820 --> 03:13:59.060
[Guest]: you know,

03:13:59.060 --> 03:13:59.860
[Guest]: there's some,

03:13:59.860 --> 03:14:01.060
[Guest]: some trap in which you are,

03:14:01.060 --> 03:14:02.180
[Guest]: so you can't see it.

03:14:02.180 --> 03:14:03.140
[Guest]: So it's a very complicated,

03:14:03.140 --> 03:14:03.780
[Guest]: philosophical,

03:14:04.420 --> 03:14:05.540
[Guest]: rabbit hole in itself.

03:14:05.540 --> 03:14:06.660
[Guest]: But I'm saying that Chomsky,

03:14:06.660 --> 03:14:07.940
[Guest]: when he gave this framework that,

03:14:08.740 --> 03:14:09.540
[Guest]: we are,

03:14:10.260 --> 03:14:10.740
[Guest]: you know,

03:14:11.780 --> 03:14:12.740
[Guest]: we want to be free,

03:14:13.300 --> 03:14:14.100
[Guest]: but society,

03:14:14.100 --> 03:14:14.500
[Guest]: structures,

03:14:14.500 --> 03:14:15.860
[Guest]: school us not to be free.

03:14:15.860 --> 03:14:17.220
[Guest]: And then he says that,

03:14:17.220 --> 03:14:18.180
[Guest]: you look at it from this frame,

03:14:18.180 --> 03:14:18.900
[Guest]: and then you think,

03:14:18.900 --> 03:14:20.900
[Guest]: about the notion of a career.

03:14:20.900 --> 03:14:21.540
[Guest]: He says that,

03:14:21.540 --> 03:14:22.820
[Guest]: I think something a hundred year old,

03:14:22.820 --> 03:14:24.820
[Guest]: or two hundred year old idea.

03:14:24.820 --> 03:14:26.020
[Guest]: It didn't exist,

03:14:26.020 --> 03:14:27.220
[Guest]: 500 years ago,

03:14:27.220 --> 03:14:27.860
[Guest]: right?

03:14:27.860 --> 03:14:28.420
[Guest]: So,

03:14:29.300 --> 03:14:30.420
[Guest]: all I'm trying to say is that,

03:14:30.420 --> 03:14:31.380
[Guest]: if you,

03:14:31.380 --> 03:14:32.340
[Guest]: when I think about,

03:14:33.060 --> 03:14:33.780
[Guest]: human society,

03:14:33.780 --> 03:14:34.740
[Guest]: not at a,

03:14:34.740 --> 03:14:35.940
[Guest]: five year scale,

03:14:35.940 --> 03:14:36.980
[Guest]: or a 10 year scale,

03:14:36.980 --> 03:14:37.940
[Guest]: but you expand,

03:14:38.580 --> 03:14:39.140
[Guest]: your,

03:14:39.140 --> 03:14:39.620
[Guest]: you know,

03:14:39.620 --> 03:14:39.620
[Guest]: you,

03:14:40.500 --> 03:14:41.940
[Guest]: talk in centuries or stuff.

03:14:42.580 --> 03:14:43.620
[Guest]: In that frame,

03:14:43.620 --> 03:14:44.820
[Guest]: you think what is normal?

03:14:46.820 --> 03:14:47.620
[Guest]: Then I just feel like,

03:14:47.620 --> 03:14:49.380
[Guest]: what, like,

03:14:49.380 --> 03:14:50.740
[Guest]: what is the meaning of convention?

03:14:51.460 --> 03:14:52.340
[Guest]: You know what I'm trying to say?

03:14:52.340 --> 03:14:53.060
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, yeah.

03:14:53.060 --> 03:14:53.780
[Amit Varma]: Sample size,

03:14:53.780 --> 03:14:55.220
[Amit Varma]: if you change it,

03:14:55.220 --> 03:14:56.260
[Guest]: everything looks different.

03:14:56.260 --> 03:14:56.580
[Guest]: Right?

03:14:56.580 --> 03:14:57.220
[Guest]: Everything,

03:14:57.220 --> 03:14:58.020
[Guest]: everything feels different.

