03:20:15.140 --> 03:20:16.260
[Amit Varma]: and in pretty much life,

03:20:16.260 --> 03:20:18.180
[Amit Varma]: most people get into these grooves

03:20:18.180 --> 03:20:19.700
[Amit Varma]: and they go along these grooves.

03:20:19.700 --> 03:20:21.220
[Amit Varma]: And that's a game that is being played.

03:20:21.780 --> 03:20:24.340
[Amit Varma]: And in journalism also,

03:20:24.340 --> 03:20:25.060
[Amit Varma]: I see that,

03:20:25.620 --> 03:20:28.260
[Amit Varma]: there are different kinds of frames

03:20:28.260 --> 03:20:29.460
[Amit Varma]: that you can bring to it.

03:20:29.460 --> 03:20:30.740
[Amit Varma]: You can become a journalist

03:20:30.740 --> 03:20:31.940
[Amit Varma]: and say that,

03:20:31.940 --> 03:20:32.660
[Unknown]: this is a career.

03:20:32.660 --> 03:20:33.300
[Unknown]: Hmm.

03:20:33.300 --> 03:20:33.620
[Unknown]: Okay,

03:20:33.620 --> 03:20:34.580
[Amit Varma]: I will do a career.

03:20:34.580 --> 03:20:36.340
[Amit Varma]: I need these skills in my career.

03:20:36.340 --> 03:20:37.540
[Amit Varma]: Either I'm good at it

03:20:37.540 --> 03:20:38.500
[Amit Varma]: or I like it

03:20:38.500 --> 03:20:40.260
[Amit Varma]: or both and all of that.

03:20:40.260 --> 03:20:40.660
[Amit Varma]: Right.

03:20:40.660 --> 03:20:41.380
[Amit Varma]: And you say,

03:20:41.380 --> 03:20:43.460
[Amit Varma]: okay, I will perform in my career.

03:20:43.460 --> 03:20:44.500
[Amit Varma]: I will excel.

03:20:44.500 --> 03:20:46.180
[Amit Varma]: And you enter that groove.

03:20:46.180 --> 03:20:49.060
[Amit Varma]: And that is what animates you.

03:20:49.060 --> 03:20:51.140
[Amit Varma]: And those are the incentives at play.

03:20:51.140 --> 03:20:53.140
[Amit Varma]: And they're conventional incentives.

03:20:53.140 --> 03:20:53.380
[Amit Varma]: Right.

03:20:54.580 --> 03:20:55.620
[Amit Varma]: That's one,

03:20:55.620 --> 03:20:56.500
[Amit Varma]: as an individual,

03:20:56.500 --> 03:20:59.060
[Amit Varma]: that is one sort of path you can take.

03:20:59.060 --> 03:21:02.820
[Amit Varma]: And the other path is to say that,

03:21:02.820 --> 03:21:03.460
[Amit Varma]: is to go in there

03:21:03.460 --> 03:21:05.780
[Amit Varma]: with a different kind of set of values

03:21:05.780 --> 03:21:06.900
[Amit Varma]: and a different kind of fire

03:21:06.900 --> 03:21:07.780
[Amit Varma]: and say that I want to change.

03:21:07.780 --> 03:21:10.100
[Amit Varma]: That journalism is about,

03:21:10.100 --> 03:21:10.740
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:21:10.740 --> 03:21:11.780
[Amit Varma]: all the cliches,

03:21:11.780 --> 03:21:12.580
[Amit Varma]: truth to power,

03:21:13.140 --> 03:21:14.100
[Amit Varma]: comfort the afflicted,

03:21:14.100 --> 03:21:14.980
[Amit Varma]: afflict the comforted,

03:21:14.980 --> 03:21:15.860
[Amit Varma]: so on and so forth.

03:21:15.860 --> 03:21:17.300
[Amit Varma]: That I want to do this kind of work.

03:21:17.300 --> 03:21:18.580
[Amit Varma]: I want to write great stories.

03:21:18.580 --> 03:21:20.260
[Amit Varma]: I want to do great investigative journalism.

03:21:20.260 --> 03:21:21.460
[Amit Varma]: You're burning with that.

03:21:21.460 --> 03:21:22.660
[Amit Varma]: You go in with that.

03:21:22.660 --> 03:21:23.620
[Amit Varma]: And that's,

03:21:23.620 --> 03:21:24.100
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:21:24.100 --> 03:21:26.180
[Amit Varma]: one set of motivations.

03:21:26.180 --> 03:21:28.980
[Amit Varma]: And the incentives are slightly different.

03:21:28.980 --> 03:21:30.180
[Unknown]: And the way it plays out is,

03:21:30.180 --> 03:21:32.420
[Amit Varma]: if I look at it at the institutional level,

03:21:32.420 --> 03:21:33.780
[Amit Varma]: at the institutional level,

03:21:34.420 --> 03:21:37.220
[Amit Varma]: for pretty much every big media house,

03:21:37.220 --> 03:21:39.380
[Amit Varma]: you have to stay within a particular groove

03:21:39.380 --> 03:21:41.140
[Amit Varma]: and not challenge those in power too much.

03:21:42.260 --> 03:21:43.460
[Amit Varma]: You're a media house,

03:21:43.460 --> 03:21:44.900
[Amit Varma]: you are running a big newspaper,

03:21:44.900 --> 03:21:46.900
[Amit Varma]: but you also have a chemical factory.

03:21:46.900 --> 03:21:48.020
[Amit Varma]: And that is an incentive.

03:21:50.500 --> 03:21:52.820
[Amit Varma]: And if the government raids one person,

03:21:52.820 --> 03:21:53.940
[Amit Varma]: then it's like,

03:21:53.940 --> 03:21:54.260
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:21:54.260 --> 03:21:55.620
[Amit Varma]: a warning to everyone else.

03:21:55.620 --> 03:21:56.980
[Amit Varma]: It has a chilling effect.

03:21:56.980 --> 03:21:59.060
[Amit Varma]: So the incentive,

03:21:59.060 --> 03:22:00.420
[Amit Varma]: the institutional incentive

03:22:00.420 --> 03:22:02.100
[Amit Varma]: for these big institutions

03:22:02.100 --> 03:22:03.380
[Amit Varma]: is toe the line,

03:22:03.380 --> 03:22:04.980
[Amit Varma]: don't mess around, right?

03:22:04.980 --> 03:22:08.420
[Amit Varma]: But there is another kind of set of values in play,

03:22:08.980 --> 03:22:11.540
[Amit Varma]: where people are animated by something higher.

03:22:11.540 --> 03:22:13.220
[Amit Varma]: They're saying journalism,

03:22:13.220 --> 03:22:13.540
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:22:13.540 --> 03:22:16.340
[Amit Varma]: I might be running a company or an enterprise.

03:22:16.340 --> 03:22:19.460
[Amit Varma]: Journalism is not about a profit and loss statement.

03:22:19.460 --> 03:22:20.660
[Amit Varma]: Ki kuch aur hai.

03:22:20.660 --> 03:22:21.540
[Amit Varma]: There is a calling.

03:22:21.540 --> 03:22:22.500
[Amit Varma]: There is a higher purpose.

03:22:22.500 --> 03:22:23.140
[Amit Varma]: Wo karna hai.

03:22:23.140 --> 03:22:24.580
[Amit Varma]: Kuch bhi ho jaye karna hai.

03:22:24.580 --> 03:22:25.220
[Amit Varma]: You know,

03:22:25.220 --> 03:22:27.700
[Amit Varma]: and what I increasingly see is that

03:22:27.700 --> 03:22:28.260
[Amit Varma]: in India,

03:22:28.260 --> 03:22:29.700
[Amit Varma]: for very rational reasons,

03:22:30.420 --> 03:22:32.820
[Amit Varma]: anybody who has more than a certain amount to lose

03:22:32.820 --> 03:22:34.420
[Amit Varma]: is, you know, toeing the line.

03:22:34.980 --> 03:22:36.820
[Amit Varma]: But there are, of course,

03:22:36.820 --> 03:22:40.020
[Amit Varma]: exceptions who are sort of fighting,

03:22:40.020 --> 03:22:40.420
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:22:40.420 --> 03:22:42.580
[Amit Varma]: your Alt News and News Minute

03:22:42.580 --> 03:22:43.620
[Unknown]: and all those guys,

03:22:43.620 --> 03:22:43.860
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:22:43.860 --> 03:22:45.700
[Amit Varma]: they're standing up there and they're fighting

03:22:45.700 --> 03:22:47.860
[Amit Varma]: and they're clearly animated by principle.

03:22:47.860 --> 03:22:50.020
[Amit Varma]: Aisa nahi hai ki isme market bara hai

03:22:50.020 --> 03:22:51.780
[Amit Varma]: or they're occupying some niche or whatever.

03:22:51.780 --> 03:22:52.420
[Amit Varma]: No,

03:22:52.420 --> 03:22:54.100
[Amit Varma]: they're animated by principle

03:22:54.100 --> 03:22:55.380
[Amit Varma]: and they're doing what they're doing.

03:22:55.380 --> 03:22:58.900
[Amit Varma]: So the individuals are animated by principle there,

03:22:58.900 --> 03:22:59.460
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:22:59.460 --> 03:23:01.380
[Amit Varma]: and Dhanya Rajendran has a higher purpose

03:23:01.380 --> 03:23:03.620
[Amit Varma]: and Rahul Kanwal does not,

03:23:03.620 --> 03:23:04.020
[Amit Varma]: right?

03:23:04.020 --> 03:23:05.140
[Amit Varma]: Simple as that.

03:23:05.140 --> 03:23:06.500
[Amit Varma]: And equally,

03:23:06.500 --> 03:23:08.180
[Amit Varma]: an institution like a News Minute

03:23:08.180 --> 03:23:09.300
[Amit Varma]: will take those risks

03:23:09.300 --> 03:23:10.420
[Amit Varma]: and will take those stories

03:23:10.420 --> 03:23:12.180
[Amit Varma]: because they feel that what they are doing

03:23:12.180 --> 03:23:14.260
[Amit Varma]: is not just about supply and demand.

03:23:14.260 --> 03:23:14.580
[Amit Varma]: You know,

03:23:14.580 --> 03:23:16.340
[Amit Varma]: there's a sort of story you want to do

03:23:16.340 --> 03:23:17.940
[Amit Varma]: and you're hoping it shapes the demand,

03:23:17.940 --> 03:23:19.540
[Amit Varma]: but you're going to do it anyway.

03:23:19.540 --> 03:23:20.500
[Amit Varma]: And, you know,

03:23:20.500 --> 03:23:22.260
[Amit Varma]: a bigger media house may not be like that.

03:23:23.220 --> 03:23:24.660
[Amit Varma]: So what do you feel about this game?

03:23:24.660 --> 03:23:25.460
[Amit Varma]: Because I feel,

03:23:26.100 --> 03:23:26.740
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:23:26.740 --> 03:23:28.980
[Amit Varma]: uncomfortable standing in judgment

03:23:29.540 --> 03:23:31.220
[Amit Varma]: over the bigger media houses

03:23:31.220 --> 03:23:33.300
[Amit Varma]: or the journalists doing conventional things,

03:23:34.900 --> 03:23:35.780
[Amit Varma]: they have families,

03:23:35.780 --> 03:23:37.700
[Amit Varma]: they have children to send to school.

03:23:37.700 --> 03:23:39.380
[Amit Varma]: I don't want to stand in judgment over them.

03:23:39.380 --> 03:23:40.260
[Amit Varma]: Absolutely.

03:23:40.260 --> 03:23:42.180
[Amit Varma]: Even though as an individual,

03:23:42.180 --> 03:23:43.780
[Amit Varma]: what I would be drawn to is

03:23:43.780 --> 03:23:45.620
[Amit Varma]: being the independent guy who is doing

03:23:45.620 --> 03:23:48.420
[Amit Varma]: what he is doing in spite of everything.

03:23:48.420 --> 03:23:48.900
[Amit Varma]: So,

03:23:48.900 --> 03:23:51.380
[Amit Varma]: and you are in the same sort of thinking as me,

03:23:51.380 --> 03:23:52.500
[Amit Varma]: as far as I can make out.

03:23:52.500 --> 03:23:55.860
[Amit Varma]: So what is your thinking when you sort of

03:23:55.860 --> 03:23:57.140
[Amit Varma]: look at this landscape

03:23:57.700 --> 03:23:59.940
[Amit Varma]: and does it make you feel lonely?

03:23:59.940 --> 03:24:01.940
[Amit Varma]: Did you ever feel lonely in IIT, for example,

03:24:01.940 --> 03:24:03.860
[Amit Varma]: when you were fighting the fights that you were fighting?

03:24:04.500 --> 03:24:05.000
[Amit Varma]: You know,

03:24:05.860 --> 03:24:08.180
[Amit Varma]: that sense of frustration that

03:24:08.180 --> 03:24:09.380
[Amit Varma]: why aren't enough people,

03:24:09.380 --> 03:24:12.180
[Amit Varma]: why don't enough people see things the same way as I do?

03:24:12.180 --> 03:24:13.460
[Amit Varma]: Even though it's rational for them

03:24:13.460 --> 03:24:14.660
[Guest]: and it's understandable.

03:24:14.660 --> 03:24:15.700
[Guest]: Yeah. Again, I think,

03:24:15.700 --> 03:24:17.140
[Guest]: thank you for bringing it up that

03:24:17.140 --> 03:24:17.620
[Guest]: there's no,

03:24:17.620 --> 03:24:18.260
[Guest]: I mean,

03:24:18.260 --> 03:24:19.060
[Guest]: I'm describing it,

03:24:19.060 --> 03:24:21.140
[Guest]: but not from a place of judgment.

03:24:21.140 --> 03:24:23.860
[Guest]: It's more descriptive in what you're feeling.

03:24:23.860 --> 03:24:24.980
[Guest]: I think there is a difference if

03:24:25.700 --> 03:24:26.900
[Guest]: people can appreciate that.

03:24:26.900 --> 03:24:28.420
[Guest]: But I don't,

03:24:28.420 --> 03:24:29.780
[Guest]: I just remember one incident

03:24:29.780 --> 03:24:31.060
[Guest]: where I deeply felt lonely

03:24:31.700 --> 03:24:32.900
[Guest]: at IIT and that was toward,

03:24:32.900 --> 03:24:33.400
[Guest]: like,

03:24:35.700 --> 03:24:38.740
[Guest]: I say that IIT placement office

03:24:38.740 --> 03:24:40.420
[Guest]: is the place where engineers are killed.

03:24:41.860 --> 03:24:43.780
[Guest]: Okay. The way things happen.

03:24:43.780 --> 03:24:44.280
[Guest]: So,

03:24:45.380 --> 03:24:46.340
[Guest]: this was one incident,

03:24:47.060 --> 03:24:47.700
[Guest]: and you know,

03:24:47.700 --> 03:24:48.900
[Guest]: I was helping my friends.

03:24:52.660 --> 03:24:53.160
[Guest]: So,

03:24:53.860 --> 03:24:54.580
[Guest]: so,

03:24:54.580 --> 03:24:56.100
[Guest]: that moment of placement is

03:24:57.220 --> 03:24:58.100
[Guest]: full of emotions.

03:24:58.100 --> 03:24:59.780
[Guest]: If you want to study human emotions,

03:24:59.780 --> 03:25:02.260
[Guest]: go to IIT for 10 days at the time of placement.

03:25:02.260 --> 03:25:03.620
[Guest]: You'll see everything there.

03:25:03.620 --> 03:25:06.020
[Guest]: From jealousy to ambition to fear,

03:25:06.020 --> 03:25:06.500
[Guest]: everything is there.

03:25:06.500 --> 03:25:07.000
[Guest]: Right?

03:25:07.780 --> 03:25:08.420
[Guest]: There was one,

03:25:08.420 --> 03:25:09.620
[Guest]: I won't get into details.

03:25:09.620 --> 03:25:10.340
[Guest]: I mean,

03:25:10.340 --> 03:25:12.820
[Guest]: then I can keep talking about IIT for the next five hours.

03:25:12.820 --> 03:25:14.420
[Guest]: But there was one incident,

03:25:14.420 --> 03:25:14.920
[Guest]: which,

03:25:15.860 --> 03:25:16.500
[Guest]: it happened and

03:25:17.220 --> 03:25:18.260
[Guest]: I just gave up.

03:25:18.260 --> 03:25:18.900
[Guest]: I mean, at that time,

03:25:18.900 --> 03:25:20.340
[Guest]: Tamasha movie was released.

03:25:20.340 --> 03:25:21.060
[Guest]: You know,

03:25:21.060 --> 03:25:21.780
[Guest]: Imtiaz Ali's.

03:25:23.060 --> 03:25:23.460
[Guest]: And,

03:25:23.460 --> 03:25:24.340
[Guest]: let's watch the movie.

03:25:24.340 --> 03:25:25.460
[Guest]: And that placement was going on

03:25:25.460 --> 03:25:26.340
[Guest]: and we went

03:25:26.340 --> 03:25:27.460
[Guest]: to our hall.

03:25:27.460 --> 03:25:28.660
[Guest]: Amit, I didn't watch the movie.

03:25:28.660 --> 03:25:29.620
[Guest]: I was like,

03:25:29.620 --> 03:25:30.340
[Guest]: Tamasha is going on here.

03:25:30.340 --> 03:25:31.860
[Guest]: Look, Tamasha is going on in my campus.

03:25:32.980 --> 03:25:33.540
[Guest]: That's it.

03:25:33.540 --> 03:25:34.020
[Guest]: And that day,

03:25:35.060 --> 03:25:35.560
[Guest]: it was

03:25:36.180 --> 03:25:37.220
[Guest]: late in the night,

03:25:37.220 --> 03:25:37.620
[Guest]: evening,

03:25:37.620 --> 03:25:38.180
[Guest]: late evening,

03:25:38.180 --> 03:25:39.940
[Guest]: and I went to the campus CCD.

03:25:40.820 --> 03:25:42.660
[Guest]: And I sat there alone.

03:25:42.660 --> 03:25:43.160
[Guest]: I said,

03:25:44.100 --> 03:25:44.580
[Guest]: like,

03:25:44.580 --> 03:25:47.220
[Guest]: I could not see what was happening in my hostel.

03:25:47.220 --> 03:25:49.380
[Guest]: You know, I saw the smartest kid I knew

03:25:50.180 --> 03:25:50.820
[Guest]: running around

03:25:52.100 --> 03:25:52.660
[Guest]: for a job.

03:25:52.660 --> 03:25:53.700
[Guest]: And I was like,

03:25:53.700 --> 03:25:55.220
[Guest]: how is this possible, man?

03:25:55.220 --> 03:25:57.700
[Guest]: He, this person is significantly smarter.

03:25:57.700 --> 03:25:58.900
[Guest]: For this company,

03:25:58.900 --> 03:26:00.260
[Guest]: why is he behaving like this?

03:26:00.260 --> 03:26:00.760
[Guest]: You know?

03:26:01.380 --> 03:26:01.880
[Guest]: So,

03:26:02.820 --> 03:26:03.540
[Guest]: like, I'm just saying,

03:26:03.540 --> 03:26:04.980
[Guest]: I'm just describing my

03:26:04.980 --> 03:26:05.940
[Guest]: state of mind.

03:26:05.940 --> 03:26:06.740
[Guest]: So I went,

03:26:06.740 --> 03:26:08.020
[Guest]: I sat there and I

03:26:08.020 --> 03:26:08.820
[Guest]: opened Facebook.

03:26:08.820 --> 03:26:10.340
[Guest]: There's a senior of mine

03:26:10.340 --> 03:26:11.460
[Guest]: whom I met.

03:26:11.460 --> 03:26:13.620
[Guest]: She's six, seven years older than me.

03:26:13.620 --> 03:26:14.500
[Guest]: But with her,

03:26:14.500 --> 03:26:14.900
[Guest]: you know,

03:26:14.900 --> 03:26:16.580
[Guest]: I had a heart-to-heart about,

03:26:16.580 --> 03:26:17.860
[Guest]: so I messaged her.

03:26:17.860 --> 03:26:18.820
[Guest]: And I was like,

03:26:18.820 --> 03:26:19.700
[Guest]: explain a little, man.

03:26:20.420 --> 03:26:21.620
[Guest]: What was like at your time?

03:26:21.620 --> 03:26:22.180
[Guest]: What was it?

03:26:22.180 --> 03:26:22.740
[Guest]: This and that.

03:26:22.740 --> 03:26:23.940
[Guest]: So all that discussions happened.

03:26:23.940 --> 03:26:25.460
[Guest]: So that just gave me comfort

03:26:25.460 --> 03:26:25.940
[Guest]: that, you know,

03:26:25.940 --> 03:26:26.900
[Guest]: I'm not an idiot.

03:26:26.900 --> 03:26:28.260
[Guest]: There are others who have thought about it.

03:26:28.820 --> 03:26:29.540
[Guest]: So at some point,

03:26:29.540 --> 03:26:30.420
[Guest]: there was this friend of mine.

03:26:30.420 --> 03:26:31.940
[Guest]: He's a very hardcore lefty,

03:26:31.940 --> 03:26:33.540
[Guest]: anarchist, right?

03:26:33.540 --> 03:26:34.580
[Guest]: Principles fellow, you know.

03:26:34.580 --> 03:26:36.580
[Guest]: So his point of view is different.

03:26:36.580 --> 03:26:37.780
[Guest]: But when I didn't understand,

03:26:37.780 --> 03:26:38.740
[Guest]: I would just hang out with him.

03:26:38.740 --> 03:26:39.780
[Guest]: Like, what is it?

03:26:39.780 --> 03:26:41.220
[Guest]: He used to tell me 10 more things

03:26:41.220 --> 03:26:42.020
[Guest]: that I didn't even see.

03:26:42.900 --> 03:26:43.700
[Guest]: You know?

03:26:43.700 --> 03:26:44.420
[Guest]: So I was like,

03:26:44.420 --> 03:26:45.460
[Guest]: no, there are people.

03:26:45.460 --> 03:26:46.260
[Guest]: It's just that,

03:26:46.260 --> 03:26:47.780
[Guest]: you'll roam around the campus,

03:26:47.780 --> 03:26:48.980
[Guest]: you'll see the community.

03:26:48.980 --> 03:26:50.020
[Guest]: I am not the only person.

03:26:50.020 --> 03:26:50.580
[Guest]: There are other people

03:26:50.580 --> 03:26:51.860
[Guest]: thinking about these questions.

03:26:51.860 --> 03:26:52.980
[Guest]: It's about finding them,

03:26:52.980 --> 03:26:54.020
[Guest]: talking to them.

03:26:54.020 --> 03:26:54.660
[Guest]: So at that time,

03:26:54.660 --> 03:26:55.700
[Guest]: I think in that way,

03:26:55.700 --> 03:26:56.740
[Guest]: at least at the campus level,

03:26:57.540 --> 03:26:58.580
[Guest]: I wouldn't say.

03:26:58.580 --> 03:26:59.220
[Guest]: I mean, again,

03:26:59.220 --> 03:26:59.940
[Guest]: I don't know if the picture

03:26:59.940 --> 03:27:00.900
[Guest]: is emerging that

03:27:00.900 --> 03:27:02.340
[Guest]: I was always in distress at IIT.

03:27:02.340 --> 03:27:03.140
[Guest]: I was very happy.

03:27:03.140 --> 03:27:03.940
[Guest]: It's just that

03:27:03.940 --> 03:27:04.980
[Guest]: things are happening in parallel

03:27:04.980 --> 03:27:06.100
[Guest]: and questions are coming.

03:27:06.100 --> 03:27:07.220
[Guest]: So not strictly lonely,

03:27:07.220 --> 03:27:08.180
[Guest]: apart from that one moment

03:27:08.180 --> 03:27:10.660
[Guest]: when my batch was being placed.

03:27:10.660 --> 03:27:12.180
[Guest]: That was a very low time for me.

03:27:12.900 --> 03:27:14.580
[Amit Varma]: And in journalism,

03:27:14.580 --> 03:27:15.860
[Amit Varma]: what's it, you know,

03:27:15.860 --> 03:27:17.380
[Amit Varma]: to kind of extend the question?

03:27:17.380 --> 03:27:17.880
[Unknown]: Yeah.

03:27:19.300 --> 03:27:20.020
[Guest]: So journalism,

03:27:20.020 --> 03:27:23.300
[Guest]: so journalism, I can tell you

03:27:24.020 --> 03:27:24.820
[Guest]: instances again.

03:27:24.820 --> 03:27:26.420
[Guest]: So let's say the context

03:27:26.420 --> 03:27:27.140
[Guest]: now we have spoken.

03:27:27.140 --> 03:27:28.500
[Guest]: So I think you have the frame

03:27:28.500 --> 03:27:29.540
[Amit Varma]: where I'm coming from.

03:27:29.540 --> 03:27:30.340
[Guest]: The frame is clear.

03:27:31.300 --> 03:27:33.460
[Guest]: Again, I had no idea

03:27:34.180 --> 03:27:36.500
[Guest]: that how mainstream journalism happens.

03:27:36.500 --> 03:27:37.780
[Guest]: I had, I didn't know

03:27:37.780 --> 03:27:39.140
[Guest]: any journalist before

03:27:39.140 --> 03:27:40.180
[Guest]: I became a journalist.

03:27:40.180 --> 03:27:41.780
[Guest]: I entered into journalism

03:27:41.780 --> 03:27:42.820
[Guest]: by pure chance.

03:27:42.820 --> 03:27:44.260
[Guest]: I was never asked

03:27:44.260 --> 03:27:45.700
[Guest]: that how a young kid

03:27:45.700 --> 03:27:46.900
[Guest]: becomes a journalist.

03:27:46.900 --> 03:27:47.940
[Guest]: I'm like, I don't know.

03:27:48.500 --> 03:27:49.140
[Guest]: You know,

03:27:49.140 --> 03:27:50.420
[Guest]: I was not supposed to be a journalist.

03:27:50.420 --> 03:27:51.460
[Guest]: I became a journalist

03:27:51.460 --> 03:27:52.420
[Guest]: by totally by accident.

03:27:52.420 --> 03:27:53.060
[Guest]: So I didn't know

03:27:54.420 --> 03:27:55.380
[Guest]: like what are the norms,

03:27:55.380 --> 03:27:57.140
[Guest]: but the first principles,

03:27:57.140 --> 03:27:57.780
[Guest]: you know,

03:27:57.780 --> 03:27:59.300
[Guest]: truth seeking, you know,

03:27:59.300 --> 03:27:59.940
[Guest]: something, something.

03:28:00.500 --> 03:28:02.980
[Guest]: So my time at the Hindu was great.

03:28:02.980 --> 03:28:04.340
[Guest]: You know, so I started my job

03:28:04.340 --> 03:28:06.100
[Guest]: at the Hindu as a reporter,

03:28:06.100 --> 03:28:06.740
[Guest]: data reporter.

03:28:06.740 --> 03:28:07.780
[Guest]: And then I went to HT

03:28:08.580 --> 03:28:10.660
[Guest]: and then I did a six month fellowship

03:28:10.660 --> 03:28:12.020
[Guest]: at the Wall Street Journal in New York

03:28:12.020 --> 03:28:13.300
[Guest]: in the investigative reporting team.

03:28:14.180 --> 03:28:15.780
[Guest]: And by the HT was two years

03:28:15.780 --> 03:28:16.980
[Guest]: and after that I left.

03:28:16.980 --> 03:28:18.180
[Guest]: I did two months at India today

03:28:18.180 --> 03:28:19.620
[Guest]: and then I've been freelance.

03:28:19.620 --> 03:28:21.540
[Guest]: So in this HT, Hindu was great.

03:28:21.540 --> 03:28:24.340
[Guest]: I was learning the basics of,

03:28:24.340 --> 03:28:25.780
[Guest]: you know, ABC of reporting,

03:28:25.780 --> 03:28:27.060
[Guest]: trying to understand.

03:28:27.060 --> 03:28:30.260
[Guest]: In HT, there was one incident

03:28:30.260 --> 03:28:31.780
[Guest]: that I was what?

03:28:31.780 --> 03:28:32.980
[Guest]: 24, I think.

03:28:32.980 --> 03:28:34.260
[Guest]: 24, yeah, I think 24.

03:28:34.260 --> 03:28:35.860
[Guest]: And Amit, it,

03:28:37.780 --> 03:28:38.260
[Guest]: first shock,

03:28:40.020 --> 03:28:41.220
[Guest]: so I don't know why still people

03:28:42.340 --> 03:28:42.820
[Guest]: acknowledge.

03:28:42.820 --> 03:28:44.260
[Guest]: Do you know the Bobby Ghosh incident?

03:28:44.900 --> 03:28:46.260
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, I know the Bobby Ghosh incident

03:28:46.260 --> 03:28:47.540
[Guest]: where he had to leave.

03:28:47.540 --> 03:28:48.660
[Guest]: So just to put in clearly,

03:28:48.660 --> 03:28:49.060
[Guest]: because, you know,

03:28:49.060 --> 03:28:50.340
[Guest]: people talk in abstract.

03:28:50.340 --> 03:28:51.460
[Guest]: So I know a lot about it.

03:28:51.460 --> 03:28:53.060
[Guest]: I can't say in

03:28:53.060 --> 03:28:54.420
[Guest]: because people have told me,

03:28:54.420 --> 03:28:55.620
[Guest]: but to one line description

03:28:55.620 --> 03:28:56.900
[Guest]: for who don't know,

03:28:56.900 --> 03:28:58.900
[Guest]: Bobby Ghosh was the editor-in-chief of HT

03:28:59.540 --> 03:29:03.940
[Guest]: and he, in theory, he resigned.

03:29:05.140 --> 03:29:06.980
[Guest]: In reality, he was asked to leave.

03:29:07.620 --> 03:29:09.940
[Guest]: Okay, because the PM of this country,

03:29:09.940 --> 03:29:11.460
[Guest]: Mr. Modi didn't want him to stay.

03:29:11.460 --> 03:29:12.260
[Guest]: It now I can, you know,

03:29:12.260 --> 03:29:13.300
[Guest]: say with authority

03:29:13.300 --> 03:29:14.900
[Guest]: without disrespecting

03:29:14.900 --> 03:29:16.660
[Guest]: what people have told me in private.

03:29:16.660 --> 03:29:17.700
[Amit Varma]: And a similar thing happened

03:29:17.700 --> 03:29:18.740
[Amit Varma]: a few years before this

03:29:18.740 --> 03:29:20.500
[Amit Varma]: with Chidambaram, who was then FM,

03:29:20.500 --> 03:29:22.180
[Amit Varma]: I think, and Raju Nari said to it.

03:29:22.180 --> 03:29:23.060
[Guest]: Right, so that's the,

03:29:23.060 --> 03:29:23.780
[Guest]: so I'm saying,

03:29:23.780 --> 03:29:25.300
[Guest]: let's just keep it as a fact,

03:29:25.300 --> 03:29:26.340
[Guest]: because somehow, you know,

03:29:26.340 --> 03:29:27.300
[Guest]: people still do he said,

03:29:27.300 --> 03:29:28.180
[Guest]: she said on this incident.

03:29:28.180 --> 03:29:29.620
[Guest]: So that's, now, you know,

03:29:30.100 --> 03:29:31.220
[Guest]: the day this happened

03:29:31.700 --> 03:29:32.980
[Guest]: in the newsroom, I,

03:29:32.980 --> 03:29:34.020
[Guest]: so I have this habit.

03:29:34.020 --> 03:29:35.700
[Guest]: I write long emails to people

03:29:35.700 --> 03:29:37.060
[Guest]: like I write to you, right?

03:29:37.060 --> 03:29:37.940
[Guest]: Before the show,

03:29:37.940 --> 03:29:39.380
[Guest]: I love writing emails.

03:29:39.380 --> 03:29:41.300
[Guest]: So I wrote an email to TN Nainan

03:29:41.300 --> 03:29:42.100
[Guest]: at Business Standard.

03:29:42.100 --> 03:29:43.140
[Guest]: I read his book

03:29:43.140 --> 03:29:44.100
[Guest]: and I loved it.

03:29:44.100 --> 03:29:45.780
[Guest]: And I said, sir, I want to meet you.

03:29:45.780 --> 03:29:46.500
[Guest]: I wrote him an email.

03:29:46.500 --> 03:29:47.620
[Guest]: He called me to his office.

03:29:47.620 --> 03:29:49.380
[Guest]: I went, had a great chat with him.

03:29:49.380 --> 03:29:50.500
[Guest]: I was coming back,

03:29:50.500 --> 03:29:52.260
[Guest]: exited the Barakhamba metro

03:29:52.260 --> 03:29:53.540
[Guest]: and my friend called me

03:29:53.540 --> 03:29:54.260
[Guest]: and she said,

03:29:54.740 --> 03:29:56.580
[Guest]: did Nainan offer you a job?

03:29:56.580 --> 03:29:57.460
[Guest]: I was like,

03:29:57.460 --> 03:29:58.820
[Guest]: why would Nainan offer me a job?

03:29:58.820 --> 03:29:59.780
[Guest]: I don't even want to work

03:29:59.780 --> 03:30:00.580
[Guest]: at Business Standard.

03:30:01.140 --> 03:30:02.900
[Guest]: He said, no, maybe you should look out

03:30:02.900 --> 03:30:04.820
[Guest]: because Bobby is going.

03:30:06.020 --> 03:30:07.060
[Guest]: And I was, what do you mean?

03:30:07.060 --> 03:30:07.780
[Guest]: He said, come to office.

03:30:07.780 --> 03:30:08.260
[Guest]: I will tell you.

03:30:08.260 --> 03:30:09.060
[Guest]: I go to office

03:30:09.620 --> 03:30:11.220
[Guest]: and that mail comes from

03:30:11.220 --> 03:30:12.660
[Guest]: Madam Shobhna Bhartia

03:30:12.660 --> 03:30:14.340
[Guest]: Shobhna Bhartia that he's resigned.

03:30:15.060 --> 03:30:15.940
[Guest]: And then I was in shock

03:30:15.940 --> 03:30:17.620
[Guest]: and then people know what has happened.

03:30:18.900 --> 03:30:20.100
[Guest]: I was still trying to process.

03:30:20.100 --> 03:30:21.140
[Guest]: There were a couple of colleagues

03:30:21.140 --> 03:30:22.180
[Guest]: who were looking at each other.

03:30:22.180 --> 03:30:23.860
[Guest]: And again, Amit, just to know,

03:30:23.860 --> 03:30:25.860
[Guest]: I am 18 years,

03:30:25.860 --> 03:30:27.460
[Guest]: 18 months old in journalism.

03:30:27.460 --> 03:30:28.260
[Guest]: Okay.

03:30:28.260 --> 03:30:28.980
[Guest]: Aur uss waqt to

03:30:29.620 --> 03:30:30.740
[Guest]: aapko kuch pata hi nahi hai na,

03:30:30.740 --> 03:30:31.460
[Guest]: bigger things.

03:30:31.460 --> 03:30:32.820
[Guest]: Now I've thought so much about the media.

03:30:32.820 --> 03:30:34.500
[Guest]: So, uss waqt to

03:30:34.500 --> 03:30:36.340
[Guest]: you are just in a different zone.

03:30:37.060 --> 03:30:38.500
[Guest]: You know what affected me

03:30:38.500 --> 03:30:39.380
[Guest]: the most that day

03:30:39.380 --> 03:30:40.020
[Guest]: in that newsroom?

03:30:40.020 --> 03:30:41.060
[Guest]: I have that vivid memory.

03:30:41.060 --> 03:30:42.660
[Guest]: Everything that day

03:30:42.660 --> 03:30:43.700
[Guest]: in the newsroom was normal.

03:30:45.620 --> 03:30:46.820
[Guest]: You know, I would expect

03:30:46.820 --> 03:30:47.540
[Guest]: ki agar itna bada

03:30:48.420 --> 03:30:49.860
[Guest]: like what was the signal?

03:30:49.860 --> 03:30:50.740
[Guest]: The signal was,

03:30:50.740 --> 03:30:51.460
[Guest]: at least for me,

03:30:52.180 --> 03:30:54.180
[Guest]: that the government is saying,

03:30:54.980 --> 03:30:57.300
[Guest]: we can take your editor-in-chief's job.

03:30:57.300 --> 03:30:58.740
[Guest]: Who are you as a reporter?

03:31:00.260 --> 03:31:02.740
[Guest]: You know, that was the sense I got.

03:31:03.300 --> 03:31:05.860
[Guest]: Ki bhai, tumhare boss ki naukri chale gayi,

03:31:05.860 --> 03:31:06.420
[Guest]: tum kaun ho?

03:31:07.860 --> 03:31:08.580
[Guest]: Stay in line.

03:31:08.580 --> 03:31:09.780
[Guest]: It's not an explicit message.

03:31:09.780 --> 03:31:10.660
[Guest]: But don't you think people

03:31:10.660 --> 03:31:11.620
[Guest]: would imagine that?

03:31:13.140 --> 03:31:13.700
[Amit Varma]: Mujhe laga.

03:31:13.700 --> 03:31:14.580
[Amit Varma]: I think, in fact,

03:31:14.580 --> 03:31:16.180
[Amit Varma]: that questions a very

03:31:17.220 --> 03:31:18.260
[Amit Varma]: basis of the job.

03:31:19.700 --> 03:31:20.180
[Guest]: Right?

03:31:21.540 --> 03:31:23.220
[Guest]: And I was like,

03:31:23.220 --> 03:31:24.260
[Guest]: there should be like

03:31:24.260 --> 03:31:25.300
[Guest]: a newsroom gathering

03:31:26.020 --> 03:31:26.820
[Guest]: where people discuss,

03:31:26.820 --> 03:31:27.700
[Guest]: okay, what has happened?

03:31:28.660 --> 03:31:29.460
[Guest]: This, like,

03:31:29.460 --> 03:31:31.220
[Guest]: what could be the most direct attack

03:31:31.220 --> 03:31:33.540
[Guest]: on free press in this country?

03:31:33.540 --> 03:31:34.100
[Guest]: Toh aap, you know,

03:31:34.100 --> 03:31:34.740
[Guest]: when I go out

03:31:34.740 --> 03:31:35.940
[Guest]: and talk to my friends

03:31:35.940 --> 03:31:37.860
[Guest]: and they press freedom ki baat karte hain,

03:31:37.860 --> 03:31:38.580
[Guest]: toh bhai,

03:31:38.580 --> 03:31:40.260
[Guest]: you know, I want to engage.

03:31:40.980 --> 03:31:41.300
[Guest]: Okay?

03:31:41.300 --> 03:31:42.260
[Guest]: And I do engage

03:31:42.260 --> 03:31:43.700
[Guest]: with everyone on these issues.

03:31:43.700 --> 03:31:45.540
[Guest]: But when someone crosses the line

03:31:45.540 --> 03:31:46.580
[Guest]: about press freedom,

03:31:46.580 --> 03:31:47.140
[Guest]: I was like,

03:31:47.140 --> 03:31:49.300
[Guest]: boss, I've been inside, okay?

03:31:49.300 --> 03:31:50.420
[Guest]: Don't lecture me.

03:31:50.420 --> 03:31:52.660
[Guest]: Ki is country mein free press hain,

03:31:52.660 --> 03:31:53.540
[Guest]: chhap toh raha hai,

03:31:53.540 --> 03:31:54.820
[Guest]: critical articles aa toh rahe hain.

03:31:54.820 --> 03:31:56.260
[Guest]: Tum kaise kah sakte ho sarkaar ne?

03:31:57.220 --> 03:31:58.260
[Guest]: Censorship thodi ho rahe hain.

03:31:58.260 --> 03:31:58.900
[Guest]: I was like, boss,

03:31:58.900 --> 03:31:59.860
[Guest]: that is not the story.

03:31:59.860 --> 03:32:01.700
[Guest]: You don't know how things work.

03:32:01.700 --> 03:32:02.740
[Guest]: Don't tell me.

03:32:02.740 --> 03:32:03.940
[Guest]: I have seen what happens.

03:32:03.940 --> 03:32:05.140
[Guest]: And the chilling effect for me

03:32:05.140 --> 03:32:06.260
[Guest]: was that that day,

03:32:06.260 --> 03:32:08.260
[Guest]: the newsroom was functioning

03:32:08.260 --> 03:32:09.380
[Guest]: as if nothing has happened.

03:32:10.820 --> 03:32:11.620
[Guest]: People are laughing.

03:32:12.580 --> 03:32:13.620
[Guest]: Story file kar rahe hain,

03:32:13.620 --> 03:32:15.220
[Guest]: edit, wahan desk pe kaam chal raha hai.

03:32:15.780 --> 03:32:16.500
[Guest]: People are roaming around,

03:32:16.500 --> 03:32:17.300
[Guest]: graphics ban rahe hain.

03:32:18.260 --> 03:32:18.980
[Guest]: And thankfully, like,

03:32:18.980 --> 03:32:19.700
[Guest]: I've been fortunate.

03:32:19.700 --> 03:32:21.300
[Guest]: I was not a daily news reporter.

03:32:21.300 --> 03:32:22.420
[Guest]: Toh mera aisa kaam nahi tha.

03:32:22.420 --> 03:32:23.380
[Guest]: But Amit,

03:32:23.380 --> 03:32:24.500
[Guest]: I'm just saying that,

03:32:24.500 --> 03:32:25.940
[Guest]: shouldn't there be something like,

03:32:25.940 --> 03:32:26.980
[Guest]: like, is it too idealistic

03:32:26.980 --> 03:32:28.420
[Guest]: to expect that for 15 minutes,

03:32:28.420 --> 03:32:29.300
[Guest]: the newsroom gathers

03:32:30.340 --> 03:32:31.460
[Guest]: and discusses, like,

03:32:31.460 --> 03:32:32.260
[Guest]: what has happened?

03:32:33.140 --> 03:32:34.180
[Guest]: Us din I thought ki,

03:32:34.180 --> 03:32:35.140
[Guest]: boss, I have seen

03:32:35.140 --> 03:32:36.260
[Guest]: Us din I thought ki, boss, I...

03:32:36.900 --> 03:32:38.420
[Guest]: Again, you can say it's coming

03:32:38.420 --> 03:32:39.780
[Guest]: from a sense of judgment.

03:32:39.780 --> 03:32:40.740
[Guest]: Right? And I know

03:32:40.740 --> 03:32:41.780
[Guest]: when I hear about

03:32:41.780 --> 03:32:42.660
[Guest]: the kind of salaries

03:32:43.380 --> 03:32:44.660
[Guest]: people make in journalism,

03:32:44.660 --> 03:32:46.420
[Guest]: the exploitation that happens.

03:32:46.420 --> 03:32:46.900
[Guest]: You know, ek,

03:32:46.900 --> 03:32:47.940
[Guest]: someone told me, this friend,

03:32:47.940 --> 03:32:48.420
[Guest]: that, you know,

03:32:48.420 --> 03:32:49.540
[Guest]: when you think about morals,

03:32:49.540 --> 03:32:50.100
[Guest]: even having,

03:32:50.820 --> 03:32:52.260
[Guest]: thinking morally is a privilege.

03:32:52.900 --> 03:32:53.700
[Guest]: You know?

03:32:53.700 --> 03:32:54.980
[Guest]: Toh wo, sab hai dimaag mein.

03:32:54.980 --> 03:32:55.540
[Guest]: But I am saying,

03:32:55.540 --> 03:32:56.500
[Guest]: I just felt ki, yaar,

03:32:57.300 --> 03:32:59.140
[Guest]: I didn't come to this profession

03:32:59.140 --> 03:33:00.660
[Guest]: to become immune to these things.

03:33:01.780 --> 03:33:02.900
[Guest]: Ki, you know, matlab...

03:33:02.900 --> 03:33:05.140
[Amit Varma]: No, that's why I am saying,

03:33:05.140 --> 03:33:06.180
[Amit Varma]: sab chal rahe hain groove pe.

03:33:07.060 --> 03:33:08.020
[Amit Varma]: And which is rational.

03:33:08.020 --> 03:33:09.220
[Unknown]: They got families to support.

03:33:09.220 --> 03:33:10.180
[Unknown]: They have jobs.

03:33:10.180 --> 03:33:11.220
[Unknown]: Sab chal rahe hain groove mein.

03:33:11.220 --> 03:33:11.780
[Unknown]: Sab theek hai.

03:33:12.580 --> 03:33:13.380
[Amit Varma]: And they're not thinking

03:33:13.380 --> 03:33:14.260
[Amit Varma]: of press freedom.

03:33:14.260 --> 03:33:15.060
[Amit Varma]: They're not thinking that,

03:33:15.060 --> 03:33:15.620
[Amit Varma]: oh, you know,

03:33:15.620 --> 03:33:16.660
[Amit Varma]: what is a great meaning

03:33:16.660 --> 03:33:18.180
[Unknown]: of journalism and blah blah blah.

03:33:18.180 --> 03:33:19.220
[Amit Varma]: But you are.

03:33:19.220 --> 03:33:20.020
[Amit Varma]: So, it's almost like

03:33:20.020 --> 03:33:20.660
[Amit Varma]: there are two games

03:33:20.660 --> 03:33:21.860
[Amit Varma]: being played at the same time.

03:33:22.740 --> 03:33:23.240
[Amit Varma]: And...

03:33:24.420 --> 03:33:25.620
[Guest]: But it shapes, you know,

03:33:25.620 --> 03:33:26.180
[Guest]: in a way.

03:33:26.180 --> 03:33:27.060
[Guest]: Like, and there were other people,

03:33:27.060 --> 03:33:28.340
[Guest]: at least, it's not like everyone.

03:33:28.340 --> 03:33:28.820
[Guest]: And I don't know,

03:33:28.820 --> 03:33:29.940
[Guest]: private mein log kya baat kar rahe the.

03:33:29.940 --> 03:33:31.140
[Guest]: Main toh bas dekh raha hoon,

03:33:31.140 --> 03:33:32.340
[Guest]: ki what is happening around me.

03:33:32.340 --> 03:33:33.300
[Guest]: There were two, three of us.

03:33:33.300 --> 03:33:33.940
[Guest]: We went down,

03:33:34.500 --> 03:33:35.540
[Guest]: you know, had chai.

03:33:35.540 --> 03:33:36.020
[Guest]: Soch rahe the ki,

03:33:36.020 --> 03:33:36.660
[Guest]: what does it mean?

03:33:36.660 --> 03:33:37.860
[Guest]: What does it mean for us?

03:33:37.860 --> 03:33:39.060
[Guest]: What does it mean for the country?

03:33:39.060 --> 03:33:40.580
[Guest]: All of those discussions were happening.

03:33:40.580 --> 03:33:41.620
[Guest]: Us waqt main toh agli de,

03:33:41.620 --> 03:33:42.340
[Guest]: main toh yahan se jaa rahe hoon.

03:33:42.340 --> 03:33:43.060
[Guest]: I am resigning.

03:33:43.060 --> 03:33:44.020
[Guest]: That's the thought.

03:33:44.020 --> 03:33:45.780
[Guest]: Like, how can I be in a place

03:33:45.780 --> 03:33:46.980
[Guest]: where so and so things are happening?

