04:29:57.500 --> 04:29:58.220
[Guest]: when you talk about,

04:29:58.220 --> 04:29:58.380
[Guest]: you know,

04:29:58.380 --> 04:29:59.980
[Guest]: when we say deep reportage,

04:29:59.980 --> 04:30:01.020
[Guest]: what is deep reportage?

04:30:01.020 --> 04:30:03.500
[Guest]: There, where you don't settle for easy answers,

04:30:04.060 --> 04:30:04.940
[Guest]: you keep,

04:30:04.940 --> 04:30:05.340
[Guest]: you know,

04:30:05.340 --> 04:30:05.820
[Guest]: as I think,

04:30:05.820 --> 04:30:06.060
[Guest]: who,

04:30:06.060 --> 04:30:06.780
[Guest]: who is that editor?

04:30:06.780 --> 04:30:07.340
[Guest]: I've said,

04:30:07.340 --> 04:30:08.220
[Guest]: keep peeling the onion,

04:30:08.220 --> 04:30:09.100
[Guest]: keep peeling the onion,

04:30:09.100 --> 04:30:09.420
[Guest]: you know.

04:30:10.380 --> 04:30:10.620
[Guest]: And,

04:30:12.140 --> 04:30:13.900
[Guest]: I'm not even saying investigative reporting.

04:30:13.900 --> 04:30:15.180
[Guest]: I'm not even saying that.

04:30:15.180 --> 04:30:16.220
[Guest]: I'm saying journalism,

04:30:17.020 --> 04:30:19.180
[Guest]: news is about what happened yesterday,

04:30:19.180 --> 04:30:20.140
[Guest]: and we want to report,

04:30:20.140 --> 04:30:21.980
[Guest]: so that you are informed about current events.

04:30:22.540 --> 04:30:24.300
[Guest]: Journalism is about truth-seeking.

04:30:24.300 --> 04:30:27.020
[Guest]: Journalism is about understanding,

04:30:27.020 --> 04:30:27.740
[Guest]: you know.

04:30:27.740 --> 04:30:28.060
[Guest]: And,

04:30:28.620 --> 04:30:30.300
[Guest]: there are so many ways to understand the world.

04:30:30.300 --> 04:30:30.860
[Guest]: You can be,

04:30:30.860 --> 04:30:32.300
[Guest]: you can become a scientist.

04:30:32.300 --> 04:30:33.580
[Guest]: But I think that,

04:30:33.580 --> 04:30:34.780
[Guest]: there's a power,

04:30:34.780 --> 04:30:36.620
[Guest]: in the profession of journalism,

04:30:36.620 --> 04:30:37.500
[Guest]: which others,

04:30:38.620 --> 04:30:38.940
[Guest]: other,

04:30:39.500 --> 04:30:40.060
[Guest]: like,

04:30:40.060 --> 04:30:41.100
[Guest]: you can be at a think tank,

04:30:41.100 --> 04:30:42.300
[Guest]: you could be a scientist.

04:30:42.300 --> 04:30:44.060
[Guest]: The things that a journalist can do that you can't.

04:30:45.020 --> 04:30:45.260
[Guest]: Right?

04:30:45.260 --> 04:30:45.820
[Guest]: For example,

04:30:47.340 --> 04:30:48.380
[Guest]: like I was at this conference,

04:30:48.380 --> 04:30:49.500
[Guest]: and people were telling me about,

04:30:49.500 --> 04:30:50.940
[Guest]: the problems with Indian think tanks.

04:30:50.940 --> 04:30:51.580
[Guest]: Like, you know how,

04:30:52.300 --> 04:30:52.780
[Guest]: you know,

04:30:52.780 --> 04:30:53.740
[Guest]: they've been co-op,

04:30:53.740 --> 04:30:54.220
[Guest]: like,

04:30:54.220 --> 04:30:55.660
[Guest]: they're not free anymore in a way,

04:30:55.660 --> 04:30:56.780
[Guest]: like there's some decline.

04:30:56.780 --> 04:30:57.820
[Guest]: So, when I asked this person,

04:30:58.620 --> 04:30:59.580
[Guest]: this is so important,

04:31:00.140 --> 04:31:01.820
[Guest]: can you talk about it in public?

04:31:01.820 --> 04:31:02.300
[Guest]: And they said,

04:31:02.300 --> 04:31:03.340
[Guest]: no, it's too risky.

04:31:03.340 --> 04:31:03.820
[Guest]: I can't.

04:31:04.540 --> 04:31:05.020
[Guest]: So, Amit,

04:31:05.020 --> 04:31:06.060
[Guest]: I am not doing anything right now,

04:31:06.060 --> 04:31:07.020
[Guest]: but it's in my notes.

04:31:07.020 --> 04:31:07.820
[Guest]: I'm like, okay,

04:31:07.820 --> 04:31:08.620
[Guest]: that's a story.

04:31:09.580 --> 04:31:11.340
[Guest]: But this is one person telling me this.

04:31:11.340 --> 04:31:12.220
[Guest]: In the back of my head,

04:31:12.220 --> 04:31:13.500
[Guest]: I don't know if I'll write it.

04:31:13.500 --> 04:31:15.180
[Guest]: But in my ideas,

04:31:15.180 --> 04:31:16.140
[Guest]: it's a story that,

04:31:16.140 --> 04:31:17.420
[Guest]: this person can't say this because,

04:31:17.420 --> 04:31:17.740
[Guest]: you know,

04:31:17.740 --> 04:31:19.900
[Guest]: the society may alienate this person,

04:31:20.460 --> 04:31:20.940
[Guest]: right, whatever.

04:31:20.940 --> 04:31:21.500
[Guest]: But it's a,

04:31:22.140 --> 04:31:24.060
[Guest]: it's a process about how,

04:31:24.060 --> 04:31:25.740
[Guest]: knowledge production in India has been affected.

04:31:26.620 --> 04:31:27.120
[Guest]: Okay.

04:31:27.660 --> 04:31:28.380
[Guest]: Am I convinced?

04:31:28.380 --> 04:31:29.980
[Guest]: No, because this one person told me,

04:31:29.980 --> 04:31:31.980
[Guest]: but someone I trust has told me this,

04:31:31.980 --> 04:31:32.540
[Guest]: in private.

04:31:33.260 --> 04:31:34.940
[Guest]: So, can I use a journalistic method,

04:31:35.980 --> 04:31:37.660
[Guest]: to find out and connect the dots

04:31:37.660 --> 04:31:39.180
[Guest]: and talk to 10 people?

04:31:39.180 --> 04:31:40.460
[Guest]: And I take the risk,

04:31:40.460 --> 04:31:41.260
[Guest]: in the sense of,

04:31:41.980 --> 04:31:42.940
[Guest]: to be the person,

04:31:43.500 --> 04:31:45.100
[Guest]: who brings this to the information sphere,

04:31:45.100 --> 04:31:45.580
[Guest]: right?

04:31:45.580 --> 04:31:46.460
[Guest]: The journalistic,

04:31:46.460 --> 04:31:47.020
[Guest]: the people,

04:31:47.020 --> 04:31:47.980
[Guest]: journalists take the risk.

04:31:47.980 --> 04:31:49.260
[Guest]: We name people,

04:31:49.260 --> 04:31:50.380
[Guest]: about this organization.

04:31:50.380 --> 04:31:51.020
[Guest]: We, you know,

04:31:51.020 --> 04:31:53.260
[Guest]: academics generally talk in broad brush strokes.

04:31:53.980 --> 04:31:54.620
[Guest]: You know,

04:31:54.620 --> 04:31:55.180
[Guest]: this happens,

04:31:55.180 --> 04:31:55.820
[Guest]: that happens.

04:31:55.820 --> 04:31:56.320
[Guest]: I think,

04:31:56.780 --> 04:31:57.260
[Guest]: journalism,

04:31:57.260 --> 04:31:58.780
[Guest]: we talk in specifics.

04:31:58.780 --> 04:31:59.500
[Guest]: We name people.

04:31:59.500 --> 04:32:00.140
[Guest]: We are not saying,

04:32:01.740 --> 04:32:02.220
[Guest]: you know,

04:32:02.220 --> 04:32:04.620
[Guest]: X person is doing something with their taxes.

04:32:04.620 --> 04:32:05.020
[Guest]: We say,

04:32:05.020 --> 04:32:06.460
[Guest]: this person did this,

04:32:06.460 --> 04:32:06.700
[Guest]: right?

04:32:06.700 --> 04:32:07.260
[Guest]: Now you can say,

04:32:07.260 --> 04:32:07.980
[Guest]: there's bias in this,

04:32:07.980 --> 04:32:08.460
[Guest]: etc.

04:32:08.460 --> 04:32:08.940
[Guest]: No,

04:32:08.940 --> 04:32:09.740
[Guest]: but I'm saying,

04:32:09.740 --> 04:32:11.660
[Guest]: the mechanism of accountability,

04:32:11.660 --> 04:32:12.780
[Guest]: the mechanism of that,

04:32:13.820 --> 04:32:14.320
[Guest]: you know,

04:32:14.320 --> 04:32:19.040
[Guest]: like we take risk and we have the right to offend,

04:32:19.040 --> 04:32:19.840
[Guest]: you know,

04:32:19.840 --> 04:32:21.440
[Guest]: and then we write and report.

04:32:21.440 --> 04:32:22.720
[Guest]: And then I think the society should,

04:32:24.720 --> 04:32:25.600
[Guest]: give us like,

04:32:25.600 --> 04:32:26.880
[Guest]: if we are taking that risk,

04:32:26.880 --> 04:32:28.080
[Guest]: they should insure us.

04:32:28.080 --> 04:32:30.080
[Guest]: So I think that's a social contract.

04:32:30.080 --> 04:32:31.520
[Guest]: That's one example where I say that,

04:32:31.520 --> 04:32:31.760
[Guest]: you know,

04:32:31.760 --> 04:32:33.280
[Guest]: this is not news because,

04:32:33.280 --> 04:32:34.240
[Guest]: it's not something that,

04:32:34.800 --> 04:32:35.600
[Guest]: today something happened,

04:32:35.600 --> 04:32:36.160
[Guest]: like,

04:32:36.160 --> 04:32:38.160
[Guest]: someone will be fired at a think tank.

04:32:38.160 --> 04:32:39.120
[Guest]: It will become an event.

04:32:39.680 --> 04:32:41.440
[Guest]: But news comes and goes,

04:32:41.440 --> 04:32:42.560
[Guest]: in one week it dies.

04:32:42.560 --> 04:32:43.360
[Guest]: But what did you learn?

04:32:43.360 --> 04:32:44.480
[Guest]: About the country.

04:32:44.480 --> 04:32:45.840
[Guest]: So that's why I think journalism,

04:32:45.840 --> 04:32:46.640
[Guest]: in that way I'm saying,

04:32:47.520 --> 04:32:48.240
[Guest]: that's the difference.

04:32:48.240 --> 04:32:49.040
[Guest]: That's one way,

04:32:49.760 --> 04:32:51.600
[Guest]: I think it's much bigger than news rather than.

04:32:53.440 --> 04:32:56.160
[Amit Varma]: And what I find resonant in what you're saying,

04:32:56.160 --> 04:32:58.560
[Amit Varma]: is the distinction that you're making,

04:32:58.560 --> 04:32:59.520
[Amit Varma]: though not in so many words,

04:32:59.520 --> 04:33:01.200
[Amit Varma]: but this is me thinking aloud,

04:33:01.200 --> 04:33:05.040
[Amit Varma]: between the essence of an act and the packaging of it.

04:33:05.040 --> 04:33:05.440
[Unknown]: Right?

04:33:05.440 --> 04:33:06.080
[Unknown]: For example,

04:33:06.080 --> 04:33:06.720
[Unknown]: I often tell,

04:33:06.720 --> 04:33:07.120
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:33:07.120 --> 04:33:09.120
[Amit Varma]: people will object to e-readers,

04:33:09.120 --> 04:33:09.760
[Amit Varma]: for example,

04:33:09.760 --> 04:33:10.160
[Unknown]: and say,

04:33:10.160 --> 04:33:10.400
[Unknown]: no,

04:33:10.400 --> 04:33:11.600
[Amit Varma]: the book should be physical,

04:33:11.600 --> 04:33:12.800
[Amit Varma]: the paper should smell like,

04:33:12.800 --> 04:33:14.000
[Amit Varma]: this will smell like this,

04:33:14.000 --> 04:33:14.720
[Amit Varma]: this will smell like that.

04:33:14.720 --> 04:33:15.840
[Amit Varma]: And my point is,

04:33:15.840 --> 04:33:18.240
[Amit Varma]: a book is a words an author writes,

04:33:18.240 --> 04:33:18.640
[Amit Varma]: that,

04:33:18.640 --> 04:33:19.040
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:33:19.040 --> 04:33:20.480
[Amit Varma]: your paperback and your hardcovers,

04:33:20.480 --> 04:33:21.520
[Amit Varma]: they are forms of packaging,

04:33:21.520 --> 04:33:23.440
[Amit Varma]: your Kindle is a form of packaging,

04:33:23.440 --> 04:33:24.320
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:33:24.320 --> 04:33:26.080
[Amit Varma]: those are all different forms of packaging.

04:33:26.080 --> 04:33:26.720
[Amit Varma]: Similarly,

04:33:26.720 --> 04:33:29.680
[Amit Varma]: if you strip down the essence of journalism,

04:33:29.680 --> 04:33:31.680
[Amit Varma]: to the pursuit of truth,

04:33:31.680 --> 04:33:33.440
[Amit Varma]: to making sense of the world,

04:33:33.440 --> 04:33:36.560
[Amit Varma]: then we have some antiquated forms of packaging,

04:33:36.560 --> 04:33:37.840
[Amit Varma]: which kind of linger on,

04:33:37.840 --> 04:33:40.400
[Amit Varma]: like newspapers and TV channels and whatever,

04:33:40.400 --> 04:33:42.160
[Amit Varma]: and some of them will become artifacts.

04:33:42.160 --> 04:33:44.880
[Amit Varma]: And some of them will morph into other things.

04:33:44.880 --> 04:33:46.480
[Amit Varma]: But those are not important.

04:33:46.480 --> 04:33:48.320
[Amit Varma]: What is important is the thing itself,

04:33:48.320 --> 04:33:49.440
[Amit Varma]: the pursuit of truth,

04:33:49.440 --> 04:33:51.200
[Amit Varma]: the desire to understand the world.

04:33:51.200 --> 04:33:54.240
[Amit Varma]: And a long form podcast can contribute to that as much as,

04:33:54.240 --> 04:33:54.720
[Unknown]: you know,

04:33:54.720 --> 04:33:55.680
[Amit Varma]: a pamphlet can,

04:33:55.680 --> 04:33:56.400
[Unknown]: for example,

04:33:56.400 --> 04:33:57.520
[Unknown]: from the past.

04:33:57.520 --> 04:34:00.800
[Amit Varma]: So I think that's an important sort of distinction.

04:34:00.800 --> 04:34:00.960
[Amit Varma]: I mean,

04:34:00.960 --> 04:34:01.520
[Amit Varma]: for example,

04:34:01.520 --> 04:34:03.120
[Amit Varma]: when people talk of tech monopolies,

04:34:03.120 --> 04:34:04.320
[Amit Varma]: Facebook has no competition,

04:34:04.320 --> 04:34:05.440
[Amit Varma]: Twitter has no competition.

04:34:06.000 --> 04:34:06.400
[Amit Varma]: Actually,

04:34:06.400 --> 04:34:07.200
[Amit Varma]: if you think about it,

04:34:07.200 --> 04:34:08.080
[Amit Varma]: they all do.

04:34:08.080 --> 04:34:08.320
[Amit Varma]: You know,

04:34:08.320 --> 04:34:09.120
[Amit Varma]: in a narrow sense,

04:34:09.120 --> 04:34:12.960
[Amit Varma]: they're monopolies of whatever specific domain they operate in.

04:34:12.960 --> 04:34:14.000
[Amit Varma]: But in a broader sense,

04:34:14.000 --> 04:34:15.280
[Amit Varma]: they're all competing for our time.

04:34:15.280 --> 04:34:17.520
[Unknown]: They're all competing for our attention,

04:34:17.520 --> 04:34:17.760
[Amit Varma]: right?

04:34:17.760 --> 04:34:18.400
[Amit Varma]: And if you,

04:34:18.400 --> 04:34:19.200
[Amit Varma]: so it's,

04:34:19.200 --> 04:34:20.480
[Amit Varma]: I think at some level,

04:34:20.480 --> 04:34:22.640
[Amit Varma]: sometimes when we think about all of these things,

04:34:23.360 --> 04:34:28.720
[Amit Varma]: just as it helps to embody the abstract and give it concrete shape,

04:34:28.720 --> 04:34:29.600
[Amit Varma]: it also helps,

04:34:29.600 --> 04:34:29.920
[Amit Varma]: I think,

04:34:29.920 --> 04:34:33.360
[Amit Varma]: to step back and look at the bigger picture.

04:34:33.360 --> 04:34:33.760
[Amit Varma]: You know,

04:34:33.760 --> 04:34:35.120
[Amit Varma]: you might do it in terms of time,

04:34:35.120 --> 04:34:38.320
[Amit Varma]: look at something over 500 years instead of the last 30 years,

04:34:38.320 --> 04:34:40.640
[Amit Varma]: or you might do it in terms of asking,

04:34:40.640 --> 04:34:43.440
[Amit Varma]: what is the need this thing is,

04:34:43.440 --> 04:34:43.840
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:34:43.840 --> 04:34:44.800
[Unknown]: fulfilling?

04:34:44.800 --> 04:34:46.240
[Unknown]: And a need that today,

04:34:46.240 --> 04:34:46.720
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:34:46.720 --> 04:34:49.840
[Amit Varma]: an HD or an India today was fulfilling say in 1990.

04:34:50.640 --> 04:34:53.040
[Amit Varma]: Those needs are not being fulfilled by those institutions today.

04:34:53.040 --> 04:34:53.520
[Amit Varma]: Those needs,

04:34:53.520 --> 04:34:54.400
[Amit Varma]: if you think about it,

04:34:54.400 --> 04:34:56.080
[Amit Varma]: have been completely taken over.

04:34:56.080 --> 04:34:58.080
[Amit Varma]: You could argue that they are,

04:34:58.080 --> 04:34:58.400
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:34:58.400 --> 04:34:59.040
[Amit Varma]: in some cases,

04:34:59.040 --> 04:35:00.880
[Amit Varma]: they have become event management firms,

04:35:00.880 --> 04:35:01.280
[Amit Varma]: like,

04:35:01.280 --> 04:35:01.520
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:35:01.520 --> 04:35:04.160
[Amit Varma]: political journalists asked to invite politicians to events.

04:35:04.720 --> 04:35:06.000
[Amit Varma]: In other cases,

04:35:06.000 --> 04:35:08.480
[Amit Varma]: they have become sources of entertainment,

04:35:08.480 --> 04:35:08.880
[Unknown]: where,

04:35:08.880 --> 04:35:09.200
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:35:09.200 --> 04:35:11.120
[Amit Varma]: all of these events are what they're entertaining.

04:35:11.120 --> 04:35:13.680
[Amit Varma]: They're not necessarily casting light on the world.

04:35:13.680 --> 04:35:19.200
[Amit Varma]: So I agree with you that I'm hopeful that in a future of unknown unknowns,

04:35:19.200 --> 04:35:21.120
[Amit Varma]: different kinds of solutions will emerge.

04:35:22.000 --> 04:35:22.480
[Amit Varma]: What I,

04:35:22.480 --> 04:35:27.120
[Amit Varma]: another thing I want to focus on is that so far in our conversation,

04:35:27.680 --> 04:35:28.800
[Amit Varma]: I've been,

04:35:29.760 --> 04:35:30.080
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:35:30.640 --> 04:35:31.600
[Amit Varma]: critical,

04:35:31.600 --> 04:35:35.520
[Amit Varma]: or maybe critical in an understanding way of a mainstream media,

04:35:35.520 --> 04:35:37.520
[Amit Varma]: which almost cows down before,

04:35:37.520 --> 04:35:37.840
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:35:37.840 --> 04:35:38.720
[Amit Varma]: the powers that be.

04:35:39.280 --> 04:35:39.920
[Amit Varma]: And,

04:35:39.920 --> 04:35:42.560
[Amit Varma]: and I almost seem to be valorizing independent media,

04:35:42.560 --> 04:35:43.760
[Unknown]: which is standing up and saying,

04:35:43.760 --> 04:35:44.480
[Unknown]: we shall fight.

04:35:45.280 --> 04:35:47.680
[Amit Varma]: But the interesting thing is in modern times,

04:35:47.680 --> 04:35:50.720
[Amit Varma]: a lot of what passes for journalism is really narrative battles.

04:35:50.720 --> 04:35:51.440
[Amit Varma]: Absolutely.

04:35:51.440 --> 04:35:53.440
[Amit Varma]: And even within,

04:35:53.440 --> 04:35:53.760
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:35:53.760 --> 04:35:55.520
[Amit Varma]: the so-called independent media,

04:35:55.520 --> 04:36:00.080
[Amit Varma]: what journalists and editors need to watch out for is they need to introspect

04:36:00.080 --> 04:36:03.120
[Amit Varma]: and think about whether they themselves have agendas,

04:36:03.120 --> 04:36:06.720
[Amit Varma]: whether there's a danger of politics kind of getting in the way of that,

04:36:06.720 --> 04:36:06.960
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:36:06.960 --> 04:36:12.640
[Amit Varma]: you wrote a long and lovely critical essay of a story broken by the wire a while back,

04:36:12.640 --> 04:36:14.240
[Amit Varma]: where they perhaps,

04:36:14.240 --> 04:36:14.800
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:36:14.800 --> 04:36:19.920
[Amit Varma]: allowed their desire to break a particular kind of story to cloud their better judgment about

04:36:19.920 --> 04:36:22.800
[Amit Varma]: whether the story warranted to be published.

04:36:22.800 --> 04:36:23.680
[Amit Varma]: You've also,

04:36:23.680 --> 04:36:24.000
[Amit Varma]: you know,

04:36:24.000 --> 04:36:25.920
[Amit Varma]: criticized the caravan in the past,

04:36:25.920 --> 04:36:27.280
[Amit Varma]: and I have deep critiques of them.

04:36:27.280 --> 04:36:29.040
[Amit Varma]: I appreciate their courage,

04:36:29.040 --> 04:36:31.200
[Amit Varma]: but I feel that a lot of what they do,

04:36:31.200 --> 04:36:32.560
[Amit Varma]: I wouldn't call it journalism,

04:36:32.560 --> 04:36:35.040
[Amit Varma]: you know, a lot of their profiles are really hit pieces,

04:36:35.040 --> 04:36:39.760
[Amit Varma]: where they have decided the conclusion in advance that we're going to take person X down.

04:36:39.760 --> 04:36:40.800
[Amit Varma]: And, you know,

04:36:40.800 --> 04:36:43.360
[Amit Varma]: and everything is sort of mediated towards that.

04:36:43.360 --> 04:36:44.800
[Amit Varma]: So what are your thoughts on this?

04:36:45.360 --> 04:36:46.400
[Guest]: Yeah, I have.

04:36:46.400 --> 04:36:47.280
[Guest]: Okay, I'll tell you.

04:36:47.280 --> 04:36:47.760
[Guest]: But just,

04:36:47.760 --> 04:36:52.000
[Guest]: I just want to add a note to everything I've said.

