[Guest]: I don't have answers.

04:36:59.040 --> 04:36:59.360
[Guest]: I mean,

04:36:59.360 --> 04:36:59.920
[Guest]: I hope I mean,

04:36:59.920 --> 04:37:03.600
[Guest]: I mean, this is a kind of a conversation where all sorts of meandering is happening,

04:37:03.600 --> 04:37:04.960
[Guest]: but I hope you can see that.

04:37:04.960 --> 04:37:06.320
[Amit Varma]: I think it's a freewheeling conversation,

04:37:06.320 --> 04:37:07.440
[Amit Varma]: which listeners on the show,

04:37:07.440 --> 04:37:08.000
[Amit Varma]: of the show,

04:37:08.000 --> 04:37:08.560
[Amit Varma]: at least,

04:37:08.560 --> 04:37:08.720
[Amit Varma]: yeah,

04:37:08.720 --> 04:37:09.920
[Amit Varma]: will take in the right spirit.

04:37:09.920 --> 04:37:10.800
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, because,

04:37:10.800 --> 04:37:12.000
[Guest]: yeah, I'm like,

04:37:12.000 --> 04:37:12.400
[Guest]: you know,

04:37:12.400 --> 04:37:13.200
[Guest]: I say,

04:37:13.200 --> 04:37:14.960
[Guest]: I'm the most qualified expert on nothing.

04:37:16.400 --> 04:37:17.200
[Guest]: I don't know, man,

04:37:17.200 --> 04:37:17.760
[Guest]: but it's just that,

04:37:18.960 --> 04:37:19.360
[Guest]: I think,

04:37:19.360 --> 04:37:20.960
[Guest]: but it's important to ask these questions.

04:37:20.960 --> 04:37:21.920
[Guest]: Yeah, that's it.

04:37:21.920 --> 04:37:25.040
[Guest]: And I think all my thought process is in that frame.

04:37:25.040 --> 04:37:25.760
[Guest]: Okay.

04:37:25.760 --> 04:37:26.160
[Guest]: So yeah,

04:37:26.160 --> 04:37:28.400
[Guest]: so on this independent media thing,

04:37:28.400 --> 04:37:30.800
[Guest]: that's why I think the wire piece that I wrote.

04:37:32.080 --> 04:37:33.360
[Guest]: So let me put it this way,

04:37:33.360 --> 04:37:33.600
[Guest]: you know,

04:37:33.600 --> 04:37:34.880
[Guest]: I donate to the wire.

04:37:34.880 --> 04:37:36.320
[Guest]: I don't know to the caravan.

04:37:36.320 --> 04:37:36.800
[Guest]: Okay.

04:37:36.800 --> 04:37:37.760
[Guest]: I have a subscription,

04:37:37.760 --> 04:37:39.600
[Guest]: but I don't read either,

04:37:40.320 --> 04:37:42.080
[Guest]: because I think they need to exist.

04:37:42.080 --> 04:37:48.640
[Guest]: And I support them because they are among the few who are fighting the good fight.

04:37:48.640 --> 04:37:49.040
[Guest]: So, you know,

04:37:49.040 --> 04:37:49.680
[Guest]: you,

04:37:49.680 --> 04:37:51.840
[Guest]: so I'm making this distinction that I'm critical,

04:37:53.440 --> 04:37:54.640
[Guest]: but I'm not saying that

04:37:56.160 --> 04:37:56.480
[Guest]: they

04:37:56.480 --> 04:37:58.080
[Guest]: don't need to exist.

04:37:58.080 --> 04:37:58.640
[Guest]: You know,

04:37:58.640 --> 04:38:02.960
[Guest]: some people make a comparison between OpIndia and wire.

04:38:03.520 --> 04:38:04.720
[Amit Varma]: I think that's a ludicrous comparison.

04:38:04.720 --> 04:38:05.280
[Guest]: That's ridiculous.

04:38:05.280 --> 04:38:05.840
[Guest]: That's ludicrous.

04:38:05.840 --> 04:38:06.400
[Guest]: That's ridiculous.

04:38:06.400 --> 04:38:07.440
[Guest]: Like you're saying,

04:38:07.440 --> 04:38:08.160
[Guest]: Oh no,

04:38:08.160 --> 04:38:09.520
[Guest]: but so they'll tell me,

04:38:09.520 --> 04:38:09.920
[Guest]: you know,

04:38:09.920 --> 04:38:12.240
[Guest]: you said that the wire hasn't done,

04:38:12.240 --> 04:38:12.560
[Guest]: you know,

04:38:12.560 --> 04:38:13.280
[Guest]: this was a wrong article.

04:38:13.280 --> 04:38:13.760
[Guest]: I said,

04:38:13.760 --> 04:38:14.320
[Guest]: yes,

04:38:14.320 --> 04:38:16.080
[Guest]: I'm saying I'm critical of the wire.

04:38:16.080 --> 04:38:17.920
[Guest]: I'm critical of the caravan,

04:38:17.920 --> 04:38:20.000
[Guest]: but that's such an unfair comparison.

04:38:20.000 --> 04:38:24.160
[Guest]: You should say that how unfortunate it is for the,

04:38:24.160 --> 04:38:24.560
[Guest]: I mean,

04:38:24.560 --> 04:38:27.680
[Guest]: from my vantage point,

04:38:27.680 --> 04:38:32.880
[Guest]: for the larger Indian right-wing to not have a publication that they can be proud of,

04:38:33.520 --> 04:38:33.680
[Guest]: that,

04:38:33.680 --> 04:38:34.000
[Guest]: you know,

04:38:34.880 --> 04:38:35.840
[Guest]: that does journalism,

04:38:36.800 --> 04:38:37.280
[Guest]: not,

04:38:37.280 --> 04:38:39.760
[Guest]: so I'm saying that's a distinction that these,

04:38:39.760 --> 04:38:40.560
[Guest]: you know,

04:38:40.560 --> 04:38:41.680
[Guest]: these are messy things where,

04:38:41.680 --> 04:38:41.920
[Guest]: again,

04:38:41.920 --> 04:38:43.120
[Guest]: when you start bucketing,

04:38:43.120 --> 04:38:43.360
[Guest]: yeah,

04:38:43.360 --> 04:38:44.000
[Guest]: propaganda,

04:38:44.000 --> 04:38:44.480
[Guest]: journalism,

04:38:45.600 --> 04:38:45.840
[Guest]: right.

04:38:45.840 --> 04:38:46.960
[Guest]: I remember again,

04:38:47.520 --> 04:38:48.000
[Guest]: despite,

04:38:48.720 --> 04:38:49.600
[Guest]: like I left HT,

04:38:50.480 --> 04:38:52.480
[Guest]: someone comes and tells me HT is a propaganda.

04:38:52.480 --> 04:38:52.800
[Guest]: I was like,

04:38:52.800 --> 04:38:53.440
[Guest]: you are an idiot.

04:38:53.440 --> 04:38:53.840
[Guest]: Okay.

04:38:53.840 --> 04:38:56.720
[Guest]: Because you are doing this because you're thinking is lazy.

04:38:57.360 --> 04:38:58.720
[Guest]: You don't want to think deep enough.

04:38:59.360 --> 04:39:01.360
[Guest]: So you say that the paper has problems.

04:39:01.360 --> 04:39:02.720
[Guest]: Don't say it's propaganda.

04:39:03.360 --> 04:39:05.120
[Guest]: So I'm saying that is the frame.

04:39:05.120 --> 04:39:05.440
[Guest]: Now,

04:39:05.440 --> 04:39:06.080
[Guest]: in that,

04:39:06.080 --> 04:39:06.960
[Guest]: what has started happening,

04:39:06.960 --> 04:39:07.840
[Guest]: I think,

04:39:07.840 --> 04:39:08.640
[Guest]: in the independent media,

04:39:08.640 --> 04:39:10.640
[Guest]: like this editor once gave me this brilliant statement.

04:39:10.640 --> 04:39:10.960
[Guest]: He said,

04:39:10.960 --> 04:39:11.600
[Guest]: you know,

04:39:11.600 --> 04:39:12.000
[Guest]: Samarth,

04:39:12.000 --> 04:39:13.440
[Guest]: we are living in a time when

04:39:14.560 --> 04:39:17.760
[Guest]: the BJP will give us certificate of nationalism.

04:39:19.040 --> 04:39:22.640
[Guest]: The communist party will give us the certificate of secularism.

04:39:22.640 --> 04:39:25.040
[Guest]: And the caravan will give us a certificate for journalism.

04:39:27.440 --> 04:39:29.040
[Guest]: And I think,

04:39:30.560 --> 04:39:30.880
[Unknown]: again,

04:39:30.880 --> 04:39:31.360
[Unknown]: I say,

04:39:32.080 --> 04:39:34.480
[Guest]: all of this conversation is from the vantage point of a reporter.

04:39:34.480 --> 04:39:36.880
[Guest]: I just want to write stories and I report.

04:39:38.880 --> 04:39:40.240
[Guest]: If you go down to the concrete,

04:39:40.240 --> 04:39:40.480
[Guest]: again,

04:39:40.480 --> 04:39:40.800
[Guest]: concrete,

04:39:40.800 --> 04:39:41.280
[Guest]: abstract,

04:39:41.280 --> 04:39:41.520
[Guest]: right,

04:39:41.520 --> 04:39:42.960
[Guest]: forget like in the abstract,

04:39:42.960 --> 04:39:44.000
[Guest]: it's very simple.

04:39:44.000 --> 04:39:45.920
[Guest]: I think what has started happening is that

04:39:45.920 --> 04:39:46.960
[Guest]: I believe that

04:39:48.080 --> 04:39:49.760
[Guest]: journalism should be about truth seeking.

04:39:49.760 --> 04:39:51.200
[Guest]: And truth seeking is hard because,

04:39:51.200 --> 04:39:51.760
[Guest]: you know,

04:39:51.760 --> 04:39:53.760
[Guest]: all sorts of human motivations come in

04:39:53.760 --> 04:39:54.960
[Guest]: that take you away from,

04:39:54.960 --> 04:39:56.000
[Guest]: not human motivations,

04:39:56.640 --> 04:39:57.840
[Guest]: human nature comes in

04:39:57.840 --> 04:39:59.600
[Guest]: that takes you away from the path.

04:39:59.600 --> 04:40:00.720
[Guest]: It happens with scientists,

04:40:00.720 --> 04:40:01.760
[Guest]: happens with journalists,

04:40:01.760 --> 04:40:02.720
[Guest]: anyone who says that,

04:40:02.720 --> 04:40:03.120
[Guest]: you know,

04:40:03.120 --> 04:40:04.480
[Guest]: my only commitment is to the truth.

04:40:04.480 --> 04:40:05.680
[Guest]: I don't care about anyone else.

04:40:05.680 --> 04:40:06.640
[Guest]: They're probably lying.

04:40:07.200 --> 04:40:08.480
[Guest]: I want to believe that.

04:40:08.480 --> 04:40:09.200
[Guest]: So, you know,

04:40:09.200 --> 04:40:09.680
[Guest]: I am there,

04:40:09.680 --> 04:40:10.960
[Guest]: but there could be,

04:40:10.960 --> 04:40:11.280
[Guest]: you know,

04:40:11.280 --> 04:40:12.880
[Guest]: forces that will take me away from that,

04:40:12.880 --> 04:40:13.120
[Guest]: right?

04:40:13.120 --> 04:40:13.600
[Guest]: So let's,

04:40:14.160 --> 04:40:15.280
[Guest]: but in principle,

04:40:15.280 --> 04:40:16.080
[Guest]: you agree.

04:40:16.080 --> 04:40:16.400
[Guest]: Now,

04:40:16.400 --> 04:40:18.800
[Guest]: the second thing is what I think has started happening is that

04:40:18.800 --> 04:40:20.240
[Guest]: you think that

04:40:20.240 --> 04:40:21.760
[Guest]: there is much more than truth seeking

04:40:21.760 --> 04:40:22.640
[Guest]: that journalism achieves,

04:40:22.640 --> 04:40:23.760
[Guest]: which is a social change.

04:40:24.480 --> 04:40:24.800
[Guest]: Okay.

04:40:24.800 --> 04:40:25.520
[Guest]: Impact,

04:40:25.520 --> 04:40:26.560
[Guest]: saving democracy.

04:40:27.440 --> 04:40:28.160
[Guest]: Now,

04:40:28.160 --> 04:40:30.480
[Guest]: there is no direct correlation between

04:40:30.480 --> 04:40:32.000
[Guest]: truth seeking and these ends.

04:40:33.520 --> 04:40:35.360
[Guest]: And I think that is the conflict that

04:40:35.360 --> 04:40:36.560
[Guest]: we need to address

04:40:36.560 --> 04:40:37.600
[Guest]: and understand.

04:40:37.600 --> 04:40:38.640
[Guest]: Do you know Jill Lepore?

04:40:38.640 --> 04:40:39.680
[Guest]: This American historian.

04:40:39.680 --> 04:40:41.600
[Guest]: She loves beautiful stuff in the New Yorker.

04:40:41.600 --> 04:40:42.640
[Unknown]: I love her writing.

04:40:42.640 --> 04:40:43.360
[Guest]: She,

04:40:43.360 --> 04:40:44.240
[Guest]: in one of

04:40:44.240 --> 04:40:45.040
[Guest]: our panel discussions,

04:40:45.040 --> 04:40:45.840
[Guest]: she made this point.

04:40:45.840 --> 04:40:46.240
[Guest]: She said,

04:40:46.240 --> 04:40:51.680
[Guest]: that who has said that in a battlefield between truth and lies,

04:40:51.680 --> 04:40:52.640
[Guest]: truth will win.

04:40:52.640 --> 04:40:53.600
[Guest]: If there's a boxing match,

04:40:54.880 --> 04:40:55.440
[Guest]: it's a myth,

04:40:55.440 --> 04:40:55.680
[Guest]: right?

04:40:55.680 --> 04:40:58.240
[Guest]: We see the truth will always,

04:40:58.240 --> 04:40:58.880
[Guest]: Satyamev Jayate,

04:40:58.880 --> 04:40:59.600
[Guest]: truth triumphs.

04:40:59.600 --> 04:41:01.200
[Guest]: This is a mythology.

04:41:03.200 --> 04:41:07.840
[Guest]: Ask someone who has been let down by the justice system.

04:41:09.600 --> 04:41:11.840
[Guest]: Go and tell them in the face that

04:41:11.840 --> 04:41:14.880
[Guest]: truth always wins.

04:41:14.880 --> 04:41:15.920
[Guest]: Ask Bilqis Bhanu.

04:41:15.920 --> 04:41:16.480
[Guest]: Bilqis,

04:41:16.480 --> 04:41:17.120
[Guest]: recent event,

04:41:17.120 --> 04:41:17.440
[Guest]: right?

04:41:17.440 --> 04:41:17.760
[Guest]: Yeah.

04:41:17.760 --> 04:41:18.080
[Guest]: Yeah.

04:41:18.080 --> 04:41:18.640
[Guest]: So like,

04:41:19.520 --> 04:41:20.800
[Guest]: this idea that

04:41:20.800 --> 04:41:21.600
[Guest]: truth seeking

04:41:22.960 --> 04:41:24.160
[Guest]: will lead to

04:41:24.160 --> 04:41:24.960
[Guest]: a better world.

04:41:26.080 --> 04:41:26.880
[Guest]: It's a

04:41:26.880 --> 04:41:27.680
[Guest]: lovely

04:41:28.320 --> 04:41:29.680
[Guest]: idea to have in your head

04:41:29.680 --> 04:41:30.800
[Guest]: to comfort yourself.

04:41:31.520 --> 04:41:32.000
[Guest]: But,

04:41:32.000 --> 04:41:34.240
[Guest]: I don't think that's a neat translation.

04:41:35.040 --> 04:41:37.440
[Guest]: So what I feel is happening in the independent media

04:41:38.080 --> 04:41:38.720
[Guest]: is that

04:41:38.720 --> 04:41:40.240
[Guest]: truth will always win.

04:41:40.240 --> 04:41:42.720
[Guest]: So what I feel is happening in the independent media

04:41:42.720 --> 04:41:45.200
[Guest]: is that we want to believe we are doing journalism.

04:41:45.200 --> 04:41:46.880
[Guest]: So if from my vantage point,

04:41:46.880 --> 04:41:49.040
[Guest]: my critique of The Wire came from that point,

04:41:49.040 --> 04:41:49.540
[Guest]: that

04:41:50.160 --> 04:41:52.160
[Guest]: if you say truth seeking is your job,

04:41:52.160 --> 04:41:53.120
[Guest]: you failed at it.

04:41:54.160 --> 04:41:54.880
[Guest]: Okay?

04:41:54.880 --> 04:41:57.120
[Guest]: You injected something in the public sphere,

04:41:57.120 --> 04:41:58.880
[Amit Varma]: and I've written in great detail about my

04:41:59.440 --> 04:42:00.080
[Amit Varma]: critique.

04:42:00.080 --> 04:42:01.520
[Guest]: I'll link it from the show notes.

04:42:02.880 --> 04:42:03.600
[Guest]: Which is like,

04:42:03.600 --> 04:42:03.840
[Guest]: you know,

04:42:03.840 --> 04:42:05.920
[Guest]: you spent whatever years in this investigation

04:42:05.920 --> 04:42:07.520
[Guest]: to put out something that

04:42:07.520 --> 04:42:10.160
[Guest]: does not stand any journalistic scrutiny.

04:42:10.160 --> 04:42:10.720
[Guest]: It's not journalism.

04:42:11.280 --> 04:42:12.480
[Guest]: You have good intentions,

04:42:12.480 --> 04:42:14.560
[Guest]: but good intentions don't make for good journalism.

04:42:15.120 --> 04:42:15.680
[Guest]: Right?

04:42:15.680 --> 04:42:17.840
[Guest]: You can be very courageous,

04:42:17.840 --> 04:42:19.840
[Guest]: but courage does not lead to good journalism.

04:42:19.840 --> 04:42:20.080
[Guest]: Right?

04:42:20.080 --> 04:42:21.520
[Guest]: Good journalism is about process.

04:42:22.080 --> 04:42:22.800
[Guest]: And I think that

04:42:23.600 --> 04:42:24.080
[Guest]: moral,

04:42:24.080 --> 04:42:24.640
[Guest]: not moral,

04:42:24.640 --> 04:42:26.000
[Guest]: I think that clarity about

04:42:26.000 --> 04:42:26.560
[Guest]: what is it,

04:42:28.320 --> 04:42:28.560
[Guest]: like,

04:42:28.560 --> 04:42:29.680
[Guest]: what is journalism for

04:42:31.440 --> 04:42:32.720
[Guest]: in a time when,

04:42:33.840 --> 04:42:34.400
[Guest]: and I,

04:42:34.400 --> 04:42:35.520
[Guest]: you can clearly see right there,

04:42:35.520 --> 04:42:38.720
[Guest]: in a time when press freedom is clearly under attack,

04:42:39.440 --> 04:42:40.000
[Guest]: where,

04:42:40.640 --> 04:42:41.040
[Guest]: you know,

04:42:41.040 --> 04:42:41.520
[Guest]: people

04:42:42.080 --> 04:42:43.280
[Guest]: who speak truth to power,

04:42:43.280 --> 04:42:43.680
[Guest]: outs,

04:42:43.680 --> 04:42:44.400
[Guest]: not just newsroom,

04:42:44.400 --> 04:42:44.960
[Guest]: anyone, right?

04:42:45.520 --> 04:42:46.240
[Guest]: There being

04:42:46.240 --> 04:42:47.680
[Guest]: all sorts of things are happening,

04:42:47.680 --> 04:42:48.960
[Guest]: democratic backsliding,

04:42:48.960 --> 04:42:49.440
[Guest]: you know,

04:42:49.440 --> 04:42:50.880
[Guest]: we are in that ecosystem.

04:42:50.880 --> 04:42:51.440
[Guest]: So,

04:42:51.440 --> 04:42:53.360
[Guest]: does that change the role of journalism?

04:42:53.360 --> 04:42:53.840
[Guest]: I think,

04:42:54.800 --> 04:42:55.840
[Guest]: individual journalists,

04:42:55.840 --> 04:42:56.400
[Guest]: perhaps,

04:42:56.400 --> 04:42:58.400
[Guest]: and news organizations are struggling with it.

04:42:59.520 --> 04:43:01.920
[Guest]: And maybe the answer that they have settled on

04:43:01.920 --> 04:43:02.640
[Guest]: is that

04:43:03.920 --> 04:43:04.640
[Guest]: there is no

04:43:04.640 --> 04:43:06.480
[Guest]: there is more to our work

04:43:06.480 --> 04:43:07.840
[Guest]: than just reporting.

04:43:07.840 --> 04:43:09.600
[Guest]: Maybe we are part of the change.

04:43:09.600 --> 04:43:11.120
[Guest]: And I think once you take that frame,

04:43:11.840 --> 04:43:13.520
[Guest]: the way you look at the world changes,

04:43:14.160 --> 04:43:14.480
[Guest]: okay?

04:43:15.200 --> 04:43:15.840
[Guest]: Maybe that

04:43:16.720 --> 04:43:17.360
[Guest]: dilutes

04:43:17.920 --> 04:43:18.560
[Guest]: your filter.

04:43:22.160 --> 04:43:24.800
[Guest]: Like what makes journalism different from everything else,

04:43:24.800 --> 04:43:25.760
[Guest]: fundamentally,

04:43:25.760 --> 04:43:27.280
[Guest]: is the editorial layer.

04:43:27.280 --> 04:43:28.560
[Guest]: It matters a lot.

04:43:28.560 --> 04:43:29.680
[Guest]: Because as a reporter,

04:43:29.680 --> 04:43:31.520
[Guest]: I'm always attached to my material.

04:43:31.520 --> 04:43:33.520
[Guest]: It's my editor who will come and tell me,

04:43:33.520 --> 04:43:35.840
[Guest]: that boss,

04:43:35.840 --> 04:43:36.720
[Guest]: you fucked up here.

04:43:37.360 --> 04:43:37.840
[Guest]: Right?

04:43:37.840 --> 04:43:38.720
[Guest]: Remove this from here.

04:43:39.360 --> 04:43:40.560
[Guest]: You brought two sources,

04:43:40.560 --> 04:43:41.200
[Guest]: I want four.

04:43:41.920 --> 04:43:42.400
[Guest]: Okay?

04:43:42.400 --> 04:43:43.680
[Guest]: This thing is not adding up.

04:43:43.680 --> 04:43:44.320
[Guest]: That's what

04:43:44.880 --> 04:43:45.520
[Guest]: good editors do.

04:43:45.520 --> 04:43:46.240
[Guest]: It's not that they are

04:43:46.800 --> 04:43:48.000
[Guest]: copy editing your story.

04:43:48.000 --> 04:43:49.040
[Guest]: They help you get to

04:43:51.280 --> 04:43:51.840
[Guest]: what do we call?

04:43:51.840 --> 04:43:52.800
[Guest]: Journalistic standards.

04:43:52.800 --> 04:43:54.080
[Guest]: You meet the journalistic standards,

04:43:54.080 --> 04:43:54.800
[Guest]: publishable, right?

04:43:55.520 --> 04:43:56.240
[Guest]: Maybe in this

04:43:56.960 --> 04:43:57.920
[Guest]: framing about

04:43:57.920 --> 04:43:58.480
[Guest]: our

04:43:58.480 --> 04:43:59.920
[Guest]: reconception of what our role is,

04:44:01.360 --> 04:44:02.320
[Guest]: at least the way I think

04:44:02.320 --> 04:44:03.440
[Guest]: journalistic standards should be,

04:44:03.440 --> 04:44:04.480
[Guest]: I just feel some of

04:44:05.200 --> 04:44:06.560
[Guest]: and I can name the wire and the caravan,

04:44:06.560 --> 04:44:07.760
[Guest]: they have diluted this.

04:44:07.760 --> 04:44:08.640
[Guest]: And Amit,

04:44:08.640 --> 04:44:09.360
[Guest]: this is such,

04:44:09.360 --> 04:44:10.480
[Guest]: I have observed,

04:44:10.480 --> 04:44:12.320
[Guest]: I have these private conversations with my friends.

04:44:13.280 --> 04:44:14.480
[Guest]: There is, I can tell you,

04:44:14.480 --> 04:44:15.440
[Guest]: a lot of discomfort

04:44:16.000 --> 04:44:16.640
[Guest]: among

04:44:16.640 --> 04:44:17.760
[Guest]: liberal-leaning journalists

04:44:18.320 --> 04:44:18.960
[Guest]: about

04:44:18.960 --> 04:44:19.920
[Guest]: what is happening.

04:44:19.920 --> 04:44:20.880
[Guest]: But you can't,

04:44:20.880 --> 04:44:21.520
[Guest]: you

04:44:21.520 --> 04:44:23.200
[Guest]: struggle to say it in public because

04:44:23.840 --> 04:44:25.200
[Guest]: you feel that will

04:44:25.200 --> 04:44:26.320
[Guest]: me saying this,

04:44:26.320 --> 04:44:27.520
[Guest]: will that de-legitimize

04:44:28.480 --> 04:44:29.280
[Guest]: the work

04:44:29.280 --> 04:44:30.640
[Guest]: that these guys are doing?

04:44:30.640 --> 04:44:31.040
[Guest]: Because,

04:44:31.040 --> 04:44:32.720
[Guest]: and that's a tricky bit because

04:44:32.720 --> 04:44:33.680
[Guest]: in today's time,

04:44:35.040 --> 04:44:36.640
[Guest]: anyone who wants to discredit the media,

04:44:37.520 --> 04:44:38.000
[Guest]: right?

04:44:38.000 --> 04:44:39.040
[Guest]: They just want one thing.

04:44:40.240 --> 04:44:41.840
[Guest]: And they will come after you to

04:44:41.840 --> 04:44:42.800
[Guest]: not to,

04:44:42.800 --> 04:44:44.400
[Guest]: they don't want to attack a story.

04:44:44.400 --> 04:44:47.120
[Guest]: They want to de-legitimize institutions so that

04:44:47.120 --> 04:44:48.320
[Guest]: you become irrelevant.

04:44:49.600 --> 04:44:50.560
[Guest]: So which is why there is,

04:44:50.560 --> 04:44:51.760
[Guest]: I feel at least

04:44:51.760 --> 04:44:53.360
[Guest]: in my private conversations,

04:44:53.360 --> 04:44:54.080
[Guest]: that

04:44:54.080 --> 04:44:56.160
[Guest]: there is a conflict where on one hand you see,

04:44:56.160 --> 04:44:58.160
[Guest]: ya kuch toh problem hain haan pe,

04:44:58.160 --> 04:44:59.120
[Guest]: you know?

04:44:59.120 --> 04:44:59.680
[Guest]: But,

04:44:59.680 --> 04:45:01.280
[Guest]: we don't know how to battle with it.

04:45:01.280 --> 04:45:03.040
[Guest]: And then you go and talk to your readers.

04:45:03.040 --> 04:45:03.920
[Guest]: There's this friend of mine,

04:45:03.920 --> 04:45:05.520
[Guest]: I think she's 32, 33,

04:45:05.520 --> 04:45:06.240
[Guest]: once I was having,

04:45:06.240 --> 04:45:07.200
[Guest]: and very, you know,

04:45:07.200 --> 04:45:08.080
[Guest]: passionate about the media,

04:45:08.080 --> 04:45:08.880
[Guest]: I want to think.

04:45:08.880 --> 04:45:09.600
[Guest]: So she once,

04:45:09.600 --> 04:45:11.360
[Guest]: we were on a video call and she tells me,

04:45:11.360 --> 04:45:12.480
[Guest]: someone has,

04:45:12.480 --> 04:45:14.240
[Guest]: I think, you know, as I'm aging,

04:45:14.240 --> 04:45:15.440
[Guest]: I'm moving towards the right.

04:45:16.160 --> 04:45:16.640
[Guest]: You know?

04:45:16.640 --> 04:45:17.360
[Guest]: I said, why?

04:45:17.360 --> 04:45:18.640
[Guest]: She said, because, you know, now I read

04:45:19.520 --> 04:45:20.560
[Guest]: The Wire

04:45:20.560 --> 04:45:21.680
[Guest]: and I'm not able to relate.

04:45:22.720 --> 04:45:23.600
[Guest]: You know, so I think, you know,

04:45:23.600 --> 04:45:25.360
[Guest]: but The Wire is a great institution,

04:45:25.360 --> 04:45:26.880
[Guest]: so maybe my values have changed.

04:45:27.840 --> 04:45:28.320
[Guest]: Right?

04:45:28.320 --> 04:45:29.920
[Guest]: And then I asked her that,

04:45:29.920 --> 04:45:31.440
[Guest]: please don't think like that.

04:45:31.440 --> 04:45:32.480
[Guest]: Because she was like, no.

04:45:33.120 --> 04:45:34.800
[Guest]: She took the responsibility on her

04:45:34.800 --> 04:45:35.280
[Guest]: because she said,

04:45:35.280 --> 04:45:36.880
[Guest]: I cannot relate anymore.

04:45:36.880 --> 04:45:38.160
[Guest]: This is becoming too much for me.

04:45:39.280 --> 04:45:40.000
[Guest]: So I stopped.

04:45:40.800 --> 04:45:41.440
[Guest]: So,

04:45:41.440 --> 04:45:42.960
[Guest]: I am saying that there is a shift happening,

04:45:43.600 --> 04:45:45.200
[Guest]: at least from my vantage point.

04:45:45.200 --> 04:45:45.680
[Guest]: I don't,

04:45:45.680 --> 04:45:46.480
[Guest]: there's no easy answer,

04:45:46.480 --> 04:45:47.360
[Guest]: but I'm saying,

04:45:47.360 --> 04:45:48.800
[Guest]: if we don't acknowledge

04:45:50.000 --> 04:45:50.720
[Guest]: that,

04:45:50.720 --> 04:45:52.880
[Guest]: from the perspective of truth seeking,

04:45:52.880 --> 04:45:54.320
[Guest]: our idea that

04:45:54.320 --> 04:45:56.000
[Guest]: democracy needs to be saved,

04:45:56.000 --> 04:45:56.960
[Guest]: and there's some, you know,

04:45:56.960 --> 04:45:58.640
[Guest]: bigger problems happening in this country,

04:45:58.640 --> 04:46:00.160
[Guest]: and journalists need to stand up for it,

04:46:00.960 --> 04:46:02.560
[Guest]: and how that skews incentives,

04:46:04.000 --> 04:46:05.680
[Guest]: then we are deluding ourselves

04:46:05.680 --> 04:46:06.640
[Guest]: if we don't acknowledge this.

04:46:07.680 --> 04:46:09.200
[Guest]: And, you know, we talk about pressures,

04:46:09.200 --> 04:46:09.680
[Guest]: you know,

04:46:10.240 --> 04:46:11.440
[Guest]: that there's a pressure from the government

04:46:11.440 --> 04:46:13.280
[Guest]: because it's a government ad or business.

04:46:13.280 --> 04:46:14.880
[Guest]: I mean, there's also a subscriber pressure, no?

04:46:16.160 --> 04:46:18.000
[Guest]: If you have built an audience

04:46:18.000 --> 04:46:19.680
[Guest]: which wants you to speak

04:46:20.640 --> 04:46:22.240
[Guest]: critical about the government,

04:46:22.240 --> 04:46:24.640
[Guest]: then that is a pressure that you also have

04:46:24.640 --> 04:46:25.680
[Guest]: because you will get,

04:46:25.680 --> 04:46:26.160
[Guest]: and this is,

04:46:26.160 --> 04:46:28.000
[Guest]: and this is, I'm not just saying it theoretically,

04:46:28.000 --> 04:46:29.280
[Guest]: I think it was Andrew Potter,

04:46:29.280 --> 04:46:32.160
[Guest]: he was the editor of a Canadian newspaper,

04:46:32.160 --> 04:46:33.760
[Guest]: he has written about in his blog

04:46:33.760 --> 04:46:34.240
[Guest]: that how,

04:46:34.800 --> 04:46:35.440
[Guest]: you know, sometimes,

04:46:35.440 --> 04:46:37.120
[Guest]: let's say there's a story that someone covers,

04:46:37.920 --> 04:46:39.520
[Guest]: and instead of the lead story,

04:46:39.520 --> 04:46:40.400
[Guest]: they put it down.

04:46:40.400 --> 04:46:41.600
[Guest]: You know, it's not the lead story,

04:46:41.600 --> 04:46:43.600
[Guest]: it's the third story.

04:46:43.600 --> 04:46:44.480
[Guest]: People become angry

04:46:45.360 --> 04:46:46.800
[Guest]: because you feel,

04:46:46.800 --> 04:46:49.680
[Guest]: no, this should be the lead story.

04:46:49.680 --> 04:46:50.480
[Guest]: Why is it inside?

04:46:50.480 --> 04:46:51.760
[Guest]: Why is it not amplified?

04:46:51.760 --> 04:46:53.600
[Guest]: Not that information is being censored.

04:46:53.600 --> 04:46:55.040
[Guest]: It's that you feel,

04:46:55.040 --> 04:46:56.480
[Guest]: this is Potter's words,

04:46:56.480 --> 04:46:56.980
[Guest]: that,

04:46:58.080 --> 04:46:59.360
[Guest]: the institution I love,

04:46:59.360 --> 04:47:00.240
[Guest]: they have let me down.

04:47:01.360 --> 04:47:01.860
[Guest]: Right?

04:47:02.560 --> 04:47:03.840
[Guest]: And when you're a subscriber,

04:47:04.560 --> 04:47:06.000
[Guest]: you have these expectations

04:47:06.000 --> 04:47:07.600
[Guest]: that you subscribe

04:47:07.600 --> 04:47:08.480
[Guest]: because in a way,

04:47:08.480 --> 04:47:09.920
[Guest]: it reinforces your identity

04:47:09.920 --> 04:47:11.280
[Guest]: as a political citizen,

04:47:11.280 --> 04:47:12.560
[Guest]: standing up for something.

04:47:12.560 --> 04:47:13.680
[Guest]: You don't buy a newspaper

04:47:13.680 --> 04:47:14.480
[Guest]: because you want to read.

04:47:15.040 --> 04:47:16.160
[Guest]: I don't know,

04:47:16.160 --> 04:47:17.440
[Guest]: oh, I want to know the truth,

04:47:17.440 --> 04:47:19.120
[Guest]: so I want to read the paper.

04:47:19.120 --> 04:47:21.120
[Guest]: There are other reasons why people subscribe.

04:47:22.160 --> 04:47:23.040
[Guest]: Or, you know,

04:47:23.040 --> 04:47:23.680
[Guest]: our loyalties,

04:47:23.680 --> 04:47:26.880
[Guest]: you know, so I'm saying this whole idea

04:47:26.880 --> 04:47:27.520
[Guest]: that, you know,

04:47:27.520 --> 04:47:28.480
[Guest]: if readers will pay,

04:47:29.760 --> 04:47:30.960
[Guest]: it's independent.

04:47:30.960 --> 04:47:31.920
[Guest]: So you need to question, right?

04:47:31.920 --> 04:47:33.120
[Guest]: Like, what is independence?

04:47:33.760 --> 04:47:35.040
[Guest]: You will always have the pressure

04:47:35.040 --> 04:47:36.480
[Guest]: of what your subscriber wants.

04:47:36.480 --> 04:47:38.000
[Guest]: So it works all the way.

04:47:38.000 --> 04:47:40.000
[Guest]: So again, there's no neat distinction,

04:47:40.000 --> 04:47:41.120
[Guest]: just because you're independent

04:47:41.120 --> 04:47:42.320
[Guest]: in the sense you're not mainstream,

04:47:42.960 --> 04:47:44.640
[Guest]: that your incentives are totally aligned.

04:47:44.640 --> 04:47:45.520
[Guest]: And that's where I think

04:47:45.520 --> 04:47:47.440
[Guest]: my primary critique comes in.

04:47:48.000 --> 04:47:49.360
[Guest]: And I don't actually see this

04:47:49.360 --> 04:47:51.280
[Guest]: going in the right direction

04:47:51.280 --> 04:47:52.080
[Guest]: from my vantage point,

04:47:52.080 --> 04:47:53.040
[Guest]: but still, yeah,

04:47:53.040 --> 04:47:54.080
[Guest]: I think they need to exist

04:47:54.880 --> 04:47:56.160
[Guest]: and I'll continue to support them.

04:47:56.800 --> 04:47:58.800
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, and I just want to give a message

04:47:58.800 --> 04:48:00.160
[Amit Varma]: to your 32-year-old friend

04:48:00.160 --> 04:48:02.160
[Amit Varma]: who told you that she was aging.

04:48:02.160 --> 04:48:03.840
[Unknown]: Listen, shut up, okay?

04:48:03.840 --> 04:48:04.800
[Unknown]: You're not aging.

04:48:04.800 --> 04:48:05.680
[Amit Varma]: It's okay.

04:48:05.680 --> 04:48:07.200
[Amit Varma]: You know, the best years of your life

04:48:07.200 --> 04:48:07.840
[Amit Varma]: are ahead of you.

04:48:07.840 --> 04:48:08.720
[Amit Varma]: Just enjoy.

04:48:08.720 --> 04:48:10.400
[Amit Varma]: And also, I don't think

04:48:10.400 --> 04:48:11.680
[Amit Varma]: one should think in,

04:48:11.680 --> 04:48:13.440
[Amit Varma]: like, that whole frame of left and right

04:48:13.440 --> 04:48:14.240
[Guest]: exasperates me.

04:48:14.240 --> 04:48:14.720
[Guest]: Absolutely.

04:48:14.720 --> 04:48:16.400
[Guest]: You know, my frame is freedom

04:48:16.400 --> 04:48:17.520
[Amit Varma]: versus non-freedom.

04:48:17.520 --> 04:48:19.600
[Amit Varma]: And everybody's against freedom in India.

04:48:19.600 --> 04:48:20.240
[Amit Varma]: So what can we do?

04:48:20.240 --> 04:48:21.520
[Amit Varma]: We can't do anything.

04:48:21.520 --> 04:48:23.200
[Amit Varma]: And the other part of what you said

04:48:23.200 --> 04:48:24.480
[Amit Varma]: that resonated with me

04:48:24.480 --> 04:48:25.280
[Amit Varma]: was when you said that

04:48:25.280 --> 04:48:26.560
[Amit Varma]: you have liberal friends

04:48:26.560 --> 04:48:27.760
[Amit Varma]: who agree with you,

04:48:27.760 --> 04:48:29.200
[Amit Varma]: but don't want to speak up

04:48:29.200 --> 04:48:31.040
[Unknown]: because solidarity for the cause.

04:48:31.040 --> 04:48:32.800
[Amit Varma]: And similarly, I remember

04:48:32.800 --> 04:48:33.760
[Amit Varma]: two or three years back,

04:48:33.760 --> 04:48:34.880
[Amit Varma]: I had a trans friend

04:48:34.880 --> 04:48:35.920
[Amit Varma]: who told me that she was

04:48:35.920 --> 04:48:37.040
[Amit Varma]: deeply uncomfortable

04:48:37.040 --> 04:48:38.400
[Amit Varma]: about JK Rowling being hounded

04:48:38.400 --> 04:48:39.440
[Amit Varma]: over what she said.

04:48:39.440 --> 04:48:40.880
[Amit Varma]: And her point was that, listen,

04:48:40.880 --> 04:48:41.840
[Amit Varma]: that debate on whether

04:48:41.840 --> 04:48:43.200
[Amit Varma]: biological sex is real or not

04:48:43.200 --> 04:48:44.080
[Amit Varma]: has nothing to do with

04:48:44.080 --> 04:48:45.520
[Amit Varma]: how trans people are treated.

04:48:45.520 --> 04:48:46.800
[Amit Varma]: Those are separate issues.

04:48:46.800 --> 04:48:48.400
[Amit Varma]: But she wouldn't say that in public.

04:48:48.400 --> 04:48:49.680
[Amit Varma]: And she said that, no, in public,

04:48:49.680 --> 04:48:51.440
[Amit Varma]: I have to kind of show solidarity

04:48:51.440 --> 04:48:52.720
[Amit Varma]: with the cause, the same kind of thing,

04:48:52.720 --> 04:48:54.240
[Amit Varma]: not in so many words.

04:48:54.240 --> 04:48:55.680
[Amit Varma]: And I feel that there is

04:48:56.240 --> 04:48:57.680
[Amit Varma]: also a danger in this

04:48:57.680 --> 04:48:58.880
[Amit Varma]: kind of tribal thinking.

04:48:58.880 --> 04:48:59.280
[Amit Varma]: It is.

04:48:59.280 --> 04:49:01.520
[Amit Varma]: That this is my tribe, good or bad,

04:49:01.520 --> 04:49:02.640
[Amit Varma]: kuch bhi ho jaye,

04:49:02.640 --> 04:49:04.080
[Amit Varma]: I'm going to stand by my tribe.

04:49:04.080 --> 04:49:05.600
[Amit Varma]: And I understand that at one level,

04:49:05.600 --> 04:49:07.680
[Amit Varma]: you, of course, don't want to be mobbed

04:49:07.680 --> 04:49:09.440
[Amit Varma]: or cancelled by your own people,

04:49:09.440 --> 04:49:11.680
[Amit Varma]: which can happen so much.

04:49:11.680 --> 04:49:13.760
[Amit Varma]: But it's a danger to watch out for,

04:49:13.760 --> 04:49:14.640
[Amit Varma]: because I think there are

04:49:14.640 --> 04:49:16.240
[Amit Varma]: many, many, many people,

04:49:16.240 --> 04:49:18.160
[Amit Varma]: perhaps even a silent majority,

04:49:18.160 --> 04:49:19.840
[Amit Varma]: which is not part of any tribe.

04:49:19.840 --> 04:49:21.040
[Amit Varma]: And you lose credibility

04:49:21.040 --> 04:49:22.640
[Amit Varma]: when you do this, you know?

04:49:22.640 --> 04:49:24.000
[Amit Varma]: So on the one hand, of course,

04:49:24.000 --> 04:49:25.280
[Amit Varma]: the wire is journalism,

04:49:25.280 --> 04:49:26.320
[Amit Varma]: even if there are flaws

04:49:26.320 --> 04:49:27.840
[Amit Varma]: and OpIndia is propaganda.

04:49:27.840 --> 04:49:28.240
[Amit Varma]: There's none.

04:49:28.240 --> 04:49:29.360
[Amit Varma]: There's no journalism there.

04:49:29.360 --> 04:49:30.400
[Amit Varma]: I don't think they even pretend.

04:49:30.400 --> 04:49:31.360
[Unknown]: They don't even pretend.

04:49:31.360 --> 04:49:31.600
[Unknown]: Yeah.

04:49:31.600 --> 04:49:32.160
[Amit Varma]: Yeah.

04:49:32.160 --> 04:49:34.000
[Amit Varma]: But in the eyes of a lot of people,

04:49:34.000 --> 04:49:36.240
[Amit Varma]: these are competing narrative battles.

04:49:36.240 --> 04:49:38.240
[Amit Varma]: And you, and this is, you know,

04:49:38.240 --> 04:49:40.480
[Amit Varma]: one reason I really respect AltNews

04:49:40.480 --> 04:49:42.480
[Amit Varma]: and Pratik Sinha and Mohammed Zubair,

04:49:42.480 --> 04:49:44.720
[Amit Varma]: because they don't only fact check the right.

04:49:44.720 --> 04:49:46.400
[Guest]: They fact check everybody.

04:49:46.400 --> 04:49:47.520
[Guest]: They do it rigorously.

04:49:47.520 --> 04:49:48.160
[Amit Varma]: Yes.

04:49:48.160 --> 04:49:50.800
[Amit Varma]: And, you know, just rigor is visible.

04:49:50.800 --> 04:49:51.280
[Guest]: Visible.

04:49:51.280 --> 04:49:51.600
[Guest]: Visible.

04:49:51.600 --> 04:49:53.520
[Guest]: You can see it and know what they're doing.

04:49:53.520 --> 04:49:53.680
[Guest]: Yeah.

04:49:53.680 --> 04:49:54.480
[Guest]: How they do it.

04:49:54.480 --> 04:49:56.560
[Guest]: As you know, equal opportunity offender.

04:49:56.560 --> 04:49:57.920
[Unknown]: As you know, one editor used to say,

04:49:58.640 --> 04:49:59.440
[Guest]: you see their work.

04:49:59.440 --> 04:50:00.560
[Guest]: The work speaks for itself.

04:50:01.200 --> 04:50:02.000
[Amit Varma]: Absolutely.

04:50:02.000 --> 04:50:06.160
[Amit Varma]: Now let's address a larger question

04:50:06.160 --> 04:50:07.680
[Amit Varma]: about Indian journalism,

04:50:08.400 --> 04:50:10.160
[Amit Varma]: where everything we have said

04:50:10.160 --> 04:50:13.280
[Amit Varma]: at one level seems pessimistic, right?

04:50:13.280 --> 04:50:14.880
[Amit Varma]: But then you have this lovely quote

04:50:14.880 --> 04:50:16.960
[Amit Varma]: by Raj Kamal Jha in one of the pieces

04:50:16.960 --> 04:50:18.720
[Amit Varma]: you wrote, where you quote him as saying,

04:50:18.720 --> 04:50:19.840
[Amit Varma]: quote, quote,

04:50:19.840 --> 04:50:21.600
[Amit Varma]: good journalism is not dying.

04:50:21.600 --> 04:50:23.440
[Amit Varma]: It is getting better and bigger.

04:50:23.440 --> 04:50:24.240
[Amit Varma]: It's just bad.

04:50:24.240 --> 04:50:26.400
[Amit Varma]: Journalism makes a lot more noise

04:50:26.400 --> 04:50:27.760
[Amit Varma]: than it used to do five years ago.

04:50:27.760 --> 04:50:28.240
[Amit Varma]: Absolutely.

04:50:28.240 --> 04:50:29.360
[Amit Varma]: And you've elaborated on that.

04:50:29.360 --> 04:50:31.120
[Amit Varma]: And it's a fantastic argument.

04:50:31.120 --> 04:50:32.160
[Amit Varma]: And, you know,

04:50:32.160 --> 04:50:33.680
[Amit Varma]: in a piece where you also talk about

04:50:33.680 --> 04:50:36.080
[Amit Varma]: is Indian media thriving or decaying

04:50:36.080 --> 04:50:38.080
[Amit Varma]: and you give the standard reasons

04:50:38.080 --> 04:50:40.080
[Amit Varma]: for why we would say it is decaying.

04:50:40.080 --> 04:50:41.440
[Amit Varma]: But then you say that, no, you know,

04:50:41.440 --> 04:50:43.120
[Amit Varma]: actually it is thriving also.

04:50:43.120 --> 04:50:44.160
[Amit Varma]: You can make that argument.

04:50:44.160 --> 04:50:45.520
[Guest]: So make it for us.

04:50:45.520 --> 04:50:46.400
[Guest]: The thriving argument.

04:50:46.400 --> 04:50:46.960
[Guest]: Yeah.

04:50:46.960 --> 04:50:48.400
[Guest]: So, I mean, the piece is there.

04:50:48.400 --> 04:50:49.440
[Guest]: So I hope people will read it.

04:50:49.440 --> 04:50:51.760
[Guest]: I'll give you a story.

04:50:52.480 --> 04:50:52.960
[Guest]: Again, you know,

04:50:52.960 --> 04:50:55.120
[Guest]: I love your abstract and concrete framework.

04:50:55.120 --> 04:50:55.600
[Guest]: Great.

04:50:55.600 --> 04:50:57.360
[Guest]: OK, and I don't think the story is here.

04:50:57.360 --> 04:50:58.640
[Guest]: So when I was reporting on COVID,

04:50:59.840 --> 04:51:02.080
[Guest]: I spoke to a journalist in Odisha.

04:51:02.080 --> 04:51:04.080
[Guest]: OK, he's a senior guy.

04:51:04.080 --> 04:51:05.040
[Guest]: He used to cover a district.

04:51:05.840 --> 04:51:07.200
[Guest]: And I was trying to do something

04:51:07.200 --> 04:51:07.920
[Guest]: with COVID deaths.

04:51:07.920 --> 04:51:09.280
[Guest]: The project didn't go anywhere.

04:51:09.280 --> 04:51:11.360
[Guest]: But I spoke to him and for information.

04:51:12.160 --> 04:51:14.480
[Guest]: I was and now this person

04:51:14.480 --> 04:51:16.880
[Guest]: who in that district was going

04:51:16.880 --> 04:51:20.560
[Guest]: and from inside the government, he had sources.

04:51:20.560 --> 04:51:22.080
[Guest]: He was getting out the death figures

04:51:22.080 --> 04:51:23.280
[Guest]: that the government was hiding.

04:51:23.280 --> 04:51:24.480
[Guest]: And every day he would publish

04:51:24.480 --> 04:51:25.840
[Guest]: on his Facebook page.

04:51:25.840 --> 04:51:28.400
[Guest]: And he had a WhatsApp kind of a newsletter,

04:51:28.400 --> 04:51:30.160
[Guest]: which and just focus on one district.

04:51:30.880 --> 04:51:33.600
[Guest]: OK, and he would send it to everyone.

04:51:33.600 --> 04:51:34.640
[Guest]: So on a day to day basis,

04:51:34.640 --> 04:51:36.720
[Guest]: the district administration was confused.

04:51:40.560 --> 04:51:42.240
[Guest]: No one will know who this person is.

04:51:44.000 --> 04:51:44.500
[Guest]: Right.

04:51:45.200 --> 04:51:46.160
[Guest]: They will not like, you know,

04:51:46.160 --> 04:51:47.920
[Guest]: when we say courageous journalist

04:51:47.920 --> 04:51:50.000
[Guest]: on Twitter, you know,

04:51:50.000 --> 04:51:50.880
[Guest]: his name will not be there.

04:51:53.680 --> 04:51:56.960
[Guest]: But this person is doing journalism

04:51:56.960 --> 04:51:58.640
[Guest]: in a Odisha district,

04:51:59.600 --> 04:52:02.560
[Guest]: which local people

04:52:03.520 --> 04:52:05.440
[Guest]: and the administration both care about.

04:52:06.640 --> 04:52:08.000
[Guest]: I didn't dream up of.

04:52:08.880 --> 04:52:10.560
[Guest]: There's a person I was talking to.

04:52:13.360 --> 04:52:15.200
[Guest]: Because they know the district better.

04:52:15.200 --> 04:52:16.160
[Guest]: So I called him.

04:52:16.160 --> 04:52:18.080
[Guest]: So he explained how to get information.

04:52:18.080 --> 04:52:18.960
[Guest]: Then he went further.

04:52:18.960 --> 04:52:19.360
[Guest]: He said, you know,

04:52:19.360 --> 04:52:20.480
[Guest]: I have a WhatsApp newsletter.

04:52:21.040 --> 04:52:22.000
[Guest]: I send it.

04:52:22.000 --> 04:52:22.720
[Guest]: He says, you know,

04:52:22.720 --> 04:52:24.640
[Guest]: I'm going around and I see a problem.

04:52:25.520 --> 04:52:26.000
[Guest]: That, you know,

04:52:26.000 --> 04:52:27.520
[Guest]: some project is stuck.

04:52:27.520 --> 04:52:28.960
[Guest]: He says, take my photo.

04:52:28.960 --> 04:52:30.480
[Guest]: I first send it to the officials.

04:52:30.480 --> 04:52:31.600
[Guest]: I send it to the district office.

04:52:32.240 --> 04:52:34.160
[Guest]: Look, this is it, I'm doing a story.

04:52:34.160 --> 04:52:35.440
[Guest]: So what they do sometimes

04:52:35.440 --> 04:52:37.280
[Guest]: is they tell him to wait,

04:52:37.280 --> 04:52:38.800
[Guest]: we are actually fixing it.

04:52:38.800 --> 04:52:40.560
[Guest]: Give me two days, don't inform me now.

04:52:40.560 --> 04:52:41.200
[Guest]: So he stops.

04:52:42.240 --> 04:52:42.960
[Guest]: OK, because he says,

04:52:42.960 --> 04:52:45.280
[Guest]: you know, I just want to solve the problem.

04:52:45.280 --> 04:52:46.960
[Guest]: And he says, if they do it in two days,

04:52:46.960 --> 04:52:47.760
[Guest]: then I'll do the story.

04:52:47.760 --> 04:52:49.360
[Guest]: They solved this problem.

04:52:49.360 --> 04:52:50.080
[Guest]: If they don't,

04:52:50.080 --> 04:52:52.160
[Guest]: then I tell them that the administration didn't.

04:52:52.720 --> 04:52:53.520
[Guest]: This problem is happening here.

04:52:53.520 --> 04:52:54.720
[Guest]: They are not doing anything.

04:52:54.720 --> 04:52:55.520
[Guest]: He says, I go.

04:52:55.520 --> 04:52:56.880
[Guest]: I say, which files are stuck?

04:52:57.520 --> 04:52:58.480
[Guest]: Then I see sometimes,

04:52:58.480 --> 04:52:59.920
[Guest]: OK, these files are stuck.

04:52:59.920 --> 04:53:01.040
[Guest]: I talk to the state office.

04:53:01.040 --> 04:53:04.320
[Guest]: So if I find out that a problem

04:53:04.960 --> 04:53:06.640
[Guest]: that was a district problem,

04:53:06.640 --> 04:53:07.520
[Guest]: the files are stuck in it.

04:53:07.520 --> 04:53:09.200
[Guest]: So I'll send it and broadcast it.

04:53:09.200 --> 04:53:10.080
[Guest]: And then, you know,

04:53:10.080 --> 04:53:11.200
[Guest]: the government moves.

04:53:11.200 --> 04:53:13.040
[Guest]: Amit, when I heard that story,

04:53:13.040 --> 04:53:14.160
[Guest]: I was so inspired

04:53:14.880 --> 04:53:16.400
[Guest]: because we have this notion

04:53:17.040 --> 04:53:18.240
[Guest]: that everything in this country

04:53:18.240 --> 04:53:19.120
[Guest]: has to be about one man.

04:53:19.840 --> 04:53:20.560
[Guest]: Mr. Modi.

04:53:21.120 --> 04:53:21.620
[Guest]: No.

04:53:22.880 --> 04:53:23.840
[Guest]: Isn't this journalism?

04:53:25.120 --> 04:53:26.240
[Amit Varma]: Fantastic journalism.

04:53:26.240 --> 04:53:27.120
[Guest]: Fantastic journalism.

04:53:27.120 --> 04:53:29.600
[Guest]: And that's what I'm saying that,

04:53:29.600 --> 04:53:30.160
[Guest]: you know, there are,

04:53:30.160 --> 04:53:32.320
[Guest]: if you start going beyond

04:53:32.320 --> 04:53:33.280
[Guest]: this world of Twitter,

04:53:34.160 --> 04:53:35.120
[Guest]: you know, beyond this

04:53:35.120 --> 04:53:36.800
[Guest]: English language journalism

04:53:36.800 --> 04:53:37.680
[Guest]: and you start seeing,

04:53:37.680 --> 04:53:38.720
[Guest]: OK, what are people doing?

04:53:39.760 --> 04:53:40.260
[Guest]: Right.

04:53:40.260 --> 04:53:41.780
[Guest]: What he is doing.

04:53:41.780 --> 04:53:43.460
[Guest]: And this, I think, I mean,

04:53:43.460 --> 04:53:44.660
[Guest]: I don't have a lot of answers,

04:53:44.660 --> 04:53:46.180
[Guest]: but I think one of the things

04:53:46.180 --> 04:53:47.460
[Guest]: you can imagine about the future

04:53:47.460 --> 04:53:48.500
[Guest]: is that accountability

04:53:48.500 --> 04:53:49.460
[Guest]: will be decentralized.

04:53:50.660 --> 04:53:51.060
[Guest]: Right.

04:53:51.060 --> 04:53:52.020
[Guest]: That you don't need

04:53:52.660 --> 04:53:53.620
[Guest]: a Hindustan Times

04:53:53.620 --> 04:53:54.580
[Guest]: to go and talk about

04:53:54.580 --> 04:53:56.100
[Guest]: every district and government.

04:53:56.100 --> 04:53:57.060
[Guest]: Ultimately, it's about,

04:53:57.620 --> 04:53:59.220
[Guest]: you know, the state and the citizens

04:53:59.220 --> 04:53:59.940
[Guest]: in a way, if you think

04:53:59.940 --> 04:54:00.980
[Guest]: about political journalism.

04:54:00.980 --> 04:54:02.900
[Guest]: But the state is not just the center.

04:54:02.900 --> 04:54:04.100
[Guest]: It's happening at all these layers.

04:54:04.900 --> 04:54:06.500
[Guest]: So I'm saying that is one example

04:54:06.500 --> 04:54:07.700
[Guest]: where you gives me hope

04:54:08.500 --> 04:54:09.860
[Guest]: that, you know, people are thinking,

04:54:09.860 --> 04:54:11.460
[Guest]: doing stuff outside the limelight.

04:54:12.180 --> 04:54:13.940
[Guest]: Then I told you this example.

04:54:13.940 --> 04:54:14.900
[Guest]: I have seen firsthand

04:54:15.460 --> 04:54:16.740
[Guest]: examples inside newsrooms,

04:54:17.460 --> 04:54:19.060
[Guest]: the kind of battles people fight

04:54:19.700 --> 04:54:21.300
[Guest]: to get a story in the paper.

04:54:21.300 --> 04:54:22.100
[Guest]: When you see that,

04:54:22.100 --> 04:54:23.540
[Guest]: when you talk to your colleagues,

04:54:23.540 --> 04:54:24.660
[Guest]: it gives me a lot of hope

04:54:25.300 --> 04:54:28.020
[Guest]: that despite living

04:54:28.020 --> 04:54:29.220
[Guest]: in those moral conundrums.

04:54:30.100 --> 04:54:30.500
[Guest]: Right.

04:54:30.500 --> 04:54:31.860
[Guest]: They are sticking around

04:54:31.860 --> 04:54:32.980
[Guest]: to make to make sure

04:54:34.660 --> 04:54:35.700
[Guest]: critical things go.

04:54:35.700 --> 04:54:36.740
[Guest]: And I'm not saying that critical

04:54:36.740 --> 04:54:37.860
[Guest]: thing is the whole point

04:54:37.860 --> 04:54:38.660
[Guest]: of journalism, but I'm saying

04:54:38.660 --> 04:54:39.940
[Guest]: that that's an important part.

04:54:39.940 --> 04:54:41.300
[Guest]: People stick around.

04:54:41.300 --> 04:54:42.020
[Guest]: Right.

04:54:42.020 --> 04:54:44.900
[Guest]: And the piece that I wrote,

04:54:44.900 --> 04:54:45.780
[Guest]: this is example, I said,

04:54:45.780 --> 04:54:47.940
[Guest]: look at just Denning Bhaskar.

04:54:47.940 --> 04:54:49.220
[Guest]: Then this was Denning Bhaskar, right?

04:54:49.220 --> 04:54:51.860
[Guest]: The paper that covered

04:54:51.860 --> 04:54:53.220
[Guest]: the COVID deaths.

04:54:54.820 --> 04:54:56.100
[Guest]: I'm forgetting if that was someone

04:54:56.100 --> 04:54:56.660
[Guest]: you look at it.

04:54:56.660 --> 04:54:57.780
[Guest]: I mean, in general,

04:54:57.780 --> 04:54:59.140
[Guest]: you would not imagine

04:54:59.140 --> 04:55:00.500
[Guest]: that paper to be so critical

04:55:00.500 --> 04:55:01.380
[Guest]: of the government.

04:55:01.380 --> 04:55:02.900
[Guest]: But you know, when there is

04:55:02.900 --> 04:55:04.180
[Guest]: was no scope for propaganda

04:55:04.180 --> 04:55:04.900
[Guest]: in the sense that

04:55:06.580 --> 04:55:07.700
[Guest]: it's hard to lie

04:55:07.700 --> 04:55:08.820
[Guest]: that there is no tragedy.

04:55:09.620 --> 04:55:09.860
[Guest]: Right.

04:55:10.580 --> 04:55:11.540
[Guest]: How do you cover it up?

04:55:11.540 --> 04:55:12.260
[Guest]: At that time,

04:55:12.820 --> 04:55:13.700
[Guest]: this paper sent

04:55:14.820 --> 04:55:16.660
[Guest]: 30 reporters across Ganges

04:55:16.660 --> 04:55:18.180
[Guest]: to just go and see.

04:55:18.180 --> 04:55:20.100
[Guest]: And they click their photographs.

04:55:20.100 --> 04:55:21.140
[Guest]: You told the story.

04:55:22.020 --> 04:55:22.820
[Guest]: And, you know,

04:55:22.820 --> 04:55:23.860
[Guest]: when you get that story

04:55:23.860 --> 04:55:25.380
[Guest]: in a big paper,

04:55:25.380 --> 04:55:26.260
[Guest]: it makes an impact

04:55:26.260 --> 04:55:27.540
[Guest]: because it makes people think

04:55:28.580 --> 04:55:29.540
[Guest]: that what is happening

04:55:29.540 --> 04:55:33.700
[Guest]: to gap about death count.

04:55:33.700 --> 04:55:35.140
[Guest]: That's a story that

04:55:35.140 --> 04:55:36.420
[Guest]: the dead bodies in the river

04:55:36.420 --> 04:55:39.060
[Guest]: unaccounted for, right?

04:55:39.940 --> 04:55:41.380
[Guest]: So the paper did it, right?

04:55:41.380 --> 04:55:42.500
[Guest]: What happens after that?

04:55:42.500 --> 04:55:43.860
[Guest]: So I wrote this piece

04:55:43.860 --> 04:55:45.700
[Guest]: for this journalism conference.

04:55:45.700 --> 04:55:46.260
[Guest]: They asked me,

04:55:46.820 --> 04:55:47.220
[Guest]: you know,

04:55:47.220 --> 04:55:48.820
[Guest]: the day I filed the piece,

04:55:48.820 --> 04:55:49.540
[Guest]: a week after that,

04:55:49.540 --> 04:55:50.980
[Guest]: there were reads in Bhaskar's office,

04:55:50.980 --> 04:55:52.580
[Guest]: raid in Bhaskar's office, right?

04:55:52.580 --> 04:55:53.860
[Guest]: Again, to a signal.

04:55:53.860 --> 04:55:56.340
[Guest]: Now it's a pattern, right?

04:55:56.340 --> 04:55:57.860
[Guest]: So what you see is that,

04:55:57.860 --> 04:55:58.740
[Guest]: you know, when people say

04:55:58.740 --> 04:56:00.020
[Guest]: journalists are sold out,

04:56:00.900 --> 04:56:02.820
[Guest]: they're not sold out, right?

04:56:02.820 --> 04:56:03.460
[Guest]: There are problems,

04:56:03.460 --> 04:56:04.260
[Guest]: but I'm saying that

04:56:04.260 --> 04:56:06.020
[Guest]: time and again, time and again,

04:56:06.020 --> 04:56:07.700
[Guest]: you see someone somewhere

04:56:09.220 --> 04:56:10.340
[Guest]: pushing the bar

04:56:10.340 --> 04:56:11.140
[Guest]: to make sure that

04:56:11.140 --> 04:56:12.260
[Guest]: the information goes out.

04:56:12.260 --> 04:56:14.180
[Guest]: Amit, I know from private experience,

04:56:14.180 --> 04:56:16.340
[Guest]: journalists having access to information,

04:56:16.340 --> 04:56:17.140
[Guest]: which for some reason

04:56:17.140 --> 04:56:18.660
[Guest]: their newsroom is not publishing.

04:56:18.660 --> 04:56:20.020
[Guest]: They just give their story

04:56:20.020 --> 04:56:20.740
[Guest]: to someone else

04:56:20.740 --> 04:56:22.020
[Guest]: where it can be published.

04:56:22.020 --> 04:56:23.140
[Guest]: And I don't think it's a new thing.

04:56:23.140 --> 04:56:23.860
[Guest]: It has been,

04:56:24.420 --> 04:56:25.860
[Guest]: I think I remember Shikhar Gupta

04:56:26.580 --> 04:56:27.700
[Guest]: talking something about

04:56:27.700 --> 04:56:28.900
[Guest]: something at the Indian Express

04:56:28.900 --> 04:56:29.860
[Guest]: and the Hindu,

04:56:29.860 --> 04:56:30.500
[Guest]: you know,

04:56:30.500 --> 04:56:32.180
[Guest]: it may like they were competitors,

04:56:32.180 --> 04:56:34.260
[Guest]: but they also change information

04:56:34.260 --> 04:56:35.060
[Guest]: back in the day.

04:56:35.060 --> 04:56:36.260
[Guest]: So, but these things

04:56:36.260 --> 04:56:37.700
[Guest]: are not visible outside.

04:56:38.340 --> 04:56:39.220
[Guest]: So I'm saying

04:56:39.220 --> 04:56:40.500
[Guest]: this is what gives me hope

04:56:41.140 --> 04:56:42.980
[Guest]: that on a day-to-day basis,

04:56:42.980 --> 04:56:44.020
[Guest]: you see these efforts.

04:56:44.580 --> 04:56:45.620
[Guest]: So at a systemic level,

04:56:45.620 --> 04:56:47.700
[Guest]: while everything kind of seems broken,

04:56:47.700 --> 04:56:49.220
[Guest]: when you start connecting these dots,

04:56:51.380 --> 04:56:52.100
[Guest]: I mean,

04:56:52.100 --> 04:56:53.300
[Guest]: that's what gives me hope.

04:56:53.300 --> 04:56:55.140
[Guest]: And one thing I really want to plug here

04:56:55.140 --> 04:56:57.460
[Guest]: is that forget just newsrooms,

04:56:57.460 --> 04:56:59.380
[Guest]: the civil society, right?

04:56:59.380 --> 04:57:00.980
[Guest]: And they also contribute a lot

04:57:00.980 --> 04:57:02.340
[Guest]: in journalism.

04:57:02.340 --> 04:57:03.380
[Guest]: I'll give you an example

04:57:03.380 --> 04:57:04.900
[Guest]: that was personal to me.

04:57:04.900 --> 04:57:06.260
[Guest]: So in my newsletter,

04:57:06.260 --> 04:57:07.220
[Guest]: which I started,

04:57:07.220 --> 04:57:08.740
[Guest]: I wrote that polling story

04:57:08.740 --> 04:57:09.540
[Amit Varma]: on forecasting

04:57:09.540 --> 04:57:10.740
[Guest]: where I created this index

04:57:10.740 --> 04:57:11.860
[Guest]: to rank forecasters.

04:57:12.580 --> 04:57:14.180
[Guest]: One of those forecasters

04:57:14.180 --> 04:57:15.300
[Guest]: sent me a legal notice

04:57:15.940 --> 04:57:18.180
[Guest]: because they were,

04:57:19.140 --> 04:57:20.820
[Guest]: they didn't look good in my ranking.

04:57:20.820 --> 04:57:21.940
[Guest]: So it's a defamation notice.

04:57:21.940 --> 04:57:22.980
[Guest]: And I mean,

04:57:22.980 --> 04:57:24.260
[Guest]: I am running this newsletter

04:57:24.260 --> 04:57:25.060
[Guest]: as a one person.

04:57:25.060 --> 04:57:25.940
[Guest]: There's no institution.

04:57:25.940 --> 04:57:27.060
[Guest]: So the day I got a notice

04:57:27.060 --> 04:57:28.100
[Guest]: on my email,

04:57:28.100 --> 04:57:29.060
[Guest]: you know,

04:57:29.060 --> 04:57:30.740
[Guest]: it was 7.30 PM in the evening.

04:57:30.740 --> 04:57:32.020
[Guest]: I was writing some code

04:57:32.020 --> 04:57:33.140
[Guest]: or something else.

04:57:33.140 --> 04:57:34.260
[Guest]: And I didn't know what to do.

04:57:35.300 --> 04:57:35.620
[Guest]: Right?

04:57:35.620 --> 04:57:36.980
[Guest]: Like you have this legal notice

04:57:36.980 --> 04:57:38.580
[Guest]: reply in 48 hours.

04:57:38.580 --> 04:57:40.020
[Guest]: I spoke to a couple of journalist friends

04:57:40.020 --> 04:57:40.740
[Guest]: and they said, you know,

04:57:41.460 --> 04:57:43.060
[Guest]: why don't you message Apar Gupta

04:57:43.060 --> 04:57:44.260
[Guest]: from Internet Freedom Foundation?

04:57:44.900 --> 04:57:45.540
[Guest]: And I was looking

04:57:45.540 --> 04:57:46.580
[Guest]: and I had spoken to Apar

04:57:46.580 --> 04:57:48.100
[Guest]: a couple of times as a reporter.

04:57:48.100 --> 04:57:49.300
[Guest]: I text him that was,

04:57:50.180 --> 04:57:51.300
[Guest]: he instantly called me.

04:57:51.940 --> 04:57:52.500
[Guest]: Okay.

04:57:52.500 --> 04:57:53.140
[Guest]: And he said,

04:57:54.580 --> 04:57:55.700
[Guest]: don't worry, we will help you.

04:57:56.980 --> 04:57:57.480
[Guest]: Okay.

04:57:58.420 --> 04:57:59.620
[Guest]: And do you like,

04:57:59.620 --> 04:58:00.020
[Guest]: you know,

04:58:00.020 --> 04:58:01.140
[Guest]: that day I felt

04:58:01.140 --> 04:58:01.780
[Guest]: that evening

04:58:02.340 --> 04:58:02.840
[Guest]: that

04:58:04.020 --> 04:58:04.740
[Guest]: these bullies,

04:58:05.700 --> 04:58:06.200
[Guest]: right?

04:58:07.780 --> 04:58:08.340
[Guest]: They can bully,

04:58:08.340 --> 04:58:10.020
[Guest]: but I have a support system,

04:58:10.740 --> 04:58:10.980
[Guest]: right?

04:58:10.980 --> 04:58:12.340
[Guest]: Which comes from organizations

04:58:12.340 --> 04:58:14.100
[Guest]: like the Internet Freedom Foundation.

04:58:14.100 --> 04:58:14.980
[Guest]: And then I asked,

04:58:14.980 --> 04:58:15.700
[Guest]: okay, what is it?

04:58:15.700 --> 04:58:16.500
[Guest]: Told me they have a thing

04:58:16.500 --> 04:58:17.700
[Guest]: called Digital Patrakar Clinic.

04:58:17.700 --> 04:58:18.420
[Unknown]: Do you know about it?

04:58:18.420 --> 04:58:18.820
[Unknown]: No.

04:58:18.820 --> 04:58:20.020
[Guest]: So what they have done

04:58:20.020 --> 04:58:21.540
[Guest]: to support independent journalists

04:58:21.540 --> 04:58:22.740
[Guest]: who can't afford,

04:58:22.740 --> 04:58:23.380
[Guest]: who don't have,

04:58:23.940 --> 04:58:24.180
[Guest]: you know,

04:58:24.180 --> 04:58:25.700
[Guest]: newsrooms have lawyers.

04:58:25.700 --> 04:58:26.740
[Guest]: Someone doing

04:58:26.740 --> 04:58:27.780
[Guest]: reporting in a newsletter

04:58:27.780 --> 04:58:28.820
[Guest]: does not have a lawyer.

04:58:28.820 --> 04:58:29.940
[Guest]: So they help people like us.

04:58:30.580 --> 04:58:32.020
[Guest]: So that if someone tries to

04:58:32.900 --> 04:58:33.460
[Guest]: bully us,

04:58:34.100 --> 04:58:36.180
[Guest]: they help you end to end.

04:58:36.180 --> 04:58:36.900
[Guest]: So he told me

04:58:37.540 --> 04:58:39.140
[Guest]: that first of all,

04:58:39.140 --> 04:58:39.700
[Guest]: don't worry.

04:58:40.420 --> 04:58:42.100
[Guest]: This 48 hour thing is bullshit.

04:58:42.100 --> 04:58:43.380
[Guest]: We will help you file a response.

04:58:44.340 --> 04:58:45.380
[Guest]: If it goes to court,

04:58:46.580 --> 04:58:47.460
[Guest]: we will help you

04:58:47.460 --> 04:58:48.900
[Guest]: with the court proceedings.

04:58:48.900 --> 04:58:49.780
[Guest]: Okay.

04:58:49.780 --> 04:58:51.380
[Guest]: And everything is pro bono.

04:58:51.380 --> 04:58:52.020
[Guest]: So don't worry.

04:58:53.140 --> 04:58:54.180
[Guest]: We'll help.

04:58:54.180 --> 04:58:54.900
[Guest]: I slept

04:58:55.700 --> 04:58:56.260
[Guest]: that night.

04:58:56.260 --> 04:58:57.380
[Guest]: I had a comfortable sleep

04:58:57.380 --> 04:58:58.500
[Guest]: because I know that,

04:58:58.500 --> 04:58:58.980
[Guest]: you know,

04:58:59.460 --> 04:59:00.180
[Guest]: there are people

04:59:00.180 --> 04:59:01.140
[Guest]: who will support you.

04:59:01.780 --> 04:59:02.660
[Guest]: And they did.

04:59:02.660 --> 04:59:03.860
[Guest]: They filed the response.

04:59:03.860 --> 04:59:05.460
[Guest]: Their lawyers spoke to me

04:59:05.460 --> 04:59:06.820
[Guest]: and nothing like

04:59:06.820 --> 04:59:08.100
[Guest]: they didn't ask for anything.

04:59:08.100 --> 04:59:09.060
[Guest]: And I,

04:59:09.060 --> 04:59:10.020
[Guest]: like I was off Twitter

04:59:10.020 --> 04:59:10.980
[Guest]: at the time, etc.

04:59:10.980 --> 04:59:12.100
[Guest]: So I haven't even

04:59:12.100 --> 04:59:13.540
[Guest]: publicly written about it.

04:59:13.540 --> 04:59:14.580
[Guest]: So they don't even get

04:59:15.460 --> 04:59:17.380
[Guest]: like credit in any way.

04:59:17.380 --> 04:59:18.340
[Guest]: Like, and like, who cares?

04:59:18.340 --> 04:59:19.380
[Guest]: Like, it's just,

04:59:19.380 --> 04:59:20.420
[Guest]: they just help one reporter.

04:59:20.420 --> 04:59:21.940
[Guest]: But you know how it helps?

04:59:21.940 --> 04:59:23.060
[Guest]: It gives me confidence

04:59:23.060 --> 04:59:23.700
[Guest]: that yes,

04:59:24.980 --> 04:59:26.500
[Guest]: tomorrow if I do a story,

04:59:26.500 --> 04:59:28.340
[Guest]: which I want to tell

04:59:28.340 --> 04:59:29.300
[Guest]: and someone gets offended,

04:59:30.180 --> 04:59:31.460
[Guest]: there are people out there

04:59:31.460 --> 04:59:33.300
[Guest]: who will come and stand with you.

04:59:33.860 --> 04:59:34.660
[Guest]: People like, you know,

04:59:35.700 --> 04:59:37.540
[Unknown]: Apargupta and his team.

04:59:37.540 --> 04:59:38.660
[Unknown]: Isn't that brilliant?

04:59:39.540 --> 04:59:41.460
[Guest]: That you have this support system.

04:59:41.460 --> 04:59:42.580
[Guest]: So this gives me hope

04:59:43.220 --> 04:59:43.720
[Guest]: that,

04:59:44.420 --> 04:59:45.220
[Guest]: yes, there is a problem.

04:59:45.940 --> 04:59:47.060
[Guest]: But again, this is not a,

04:59:47.060 --> 04:59:47.540
[Guest]: that's why I say,

04:59:47.540 --> 04:59:48.180
[Guest]: it's not a,

04:59:48.180 --> 04:59:48.820
[Guest]: in my head,

04:59:49.460 --> 04:59:50.500
[Guest]: fight of one journalist

04:59:50.500 --> 04:59:51.380
[Guest]: or one organization.

04:59:52.660 --> 04:59:54.020
[Guest]: Point is the powerful people

04:59:54.820 --> 04:59:55.780
[Guest]: want to control

04:59:55.780 --> 04:59:58.020
[Guest]: want to control the flow of information.

04:59:58.020 --> 04:59:58.820
[Guest]: That is the problem

04:59:59.700 --> 05:00:00.500
[Guest]: at a macro level.

05:00:01.540 --> 05:00:03.700
[Guest]: And as someone who believes in freedom,

05:00:03.700 --> 05:00:05.620
[Guest]: not a particular political party or be

05:00:05.620 --> 05:00:07.700
[Guest]: just freedom of speech,

05:00:07.700 --> 05:00:08.500
[Guest]: freedom of the press.

05:00:09.460 --> 05:00:10.660
[Guest]: It's a fight that

05:00:11.220 --> 05:00:12.580
[Guest]: people who are not in power

05:00:12.580 --> 05:00:13.620
[Guest]: have to collectively fight

05:00:13.620 --> 05:00:15.220
[Guest]: to make sure that those

05:00:15.220 --> 05:00:17.540
[Guest]: information flows are broken.

05:00:17.540 --> 05:00:18.040
[Guest]: Like,

05:00:18.580 --> 05:00:20.100
[Guest]: information should not be suppressed.

05:00:20.100 --> 05:00:20.900
[Guest]: Amplification is,

05:00:22.580 --> 05:00:23.060
[Guest]: you know,

05:00:23.060 --> 05:00:24.100
[Guest]: so that's,

05:00:24.100 --> 05:00:26.420
[Guest]: if you take all of that in consideration,

05:00:26.420 --> 05:00:27.220
[Guest]: right?

05:00:27.220 --> 05:00:29.300
[Guest]: I don't like on a day-to-day basis,

05:00:29.300 --> 05:00:29.860
[Guest]: you know,

05:00:29.860 --> 05:00:31.140
[Guest]: I care about the press.

05:00:31.140 --> 05:00:32.180
[Guest]: I worry about it,

05:00:32.180 --> 05:00:33.540
[Guest]: but I'm very hopeful.

05:00:33.540 --> 05:00:34.820
[Guest]: And you talk to young reporters,

05:00:35.540 --> 05:00:36.740
[Guest]: you know, they are like,

05:00:36.740 --> 05:00:37.620
[Guest]: they're doing good work.

05:00:37.620 --> 05:00:38.500
[Guest]: You see, I mean,

05:00:38.500 --> 05:00:39.380
[Guest]: on a day-to-day basis,

05:00:39.380 --> 05:00:40.900
[Guest]: don't you see great stories being broken

05:00:41.780 --> 05:00:42.740
[Guest]: on an everyday basis?

05:00:42.740 --> 05:00:43.860
[Guest]: You know, someone,

05:00:43.860 --> 05:00:44.900
[Guest]: there are stories I won't read

05:00:44.900 --> 05:00:45.860
[Guest]: because I'm not interested,

05:00:46.420 --> 05:00:48.340
[Guest]: but across the board,

05:00:48.340 --> 05:00:49.860
[Guest]: so much good journalism is happening.

05:00:49.860 --> 05:00:50.660
[Guest]: How do you ignore it?

05:00:51.300 --> 05:00:51.860
[Guest]: So you say,

05:00:51.860 --> 05:00:52.580
[Guest]: Godi media is here,

05:00:52.580 --> 05:00:53.620
[Guest]: all the journalists are here,

05:00:53.620 --> 05:00:55.140
[Guest]: and then you see all of that.

05:00:55.140 --> 05:00:57.060
[Guest]: So I think that's my long answer

05:00:57.060 --> 05:00:59.300
[Guest]: to what makes me very hopeful

05:00:59.300 --> 05:01:01.220
[Guest]: about future of Indian journalism,

05:01:01.220 --> 05:01:02.820
[Guest]: that despite all the problems,

05:01:02.820 --> 05:01:04.020
[Guest]: if people are sticking around,

05:01:04.820 --> 05:01:06.340
[Guest]: that really inspires me.

05:01:06.340 --> 05:01:08.100
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, I love reading your essay on this.

05:01:08.100 --> 05:01:09.780
[Amit Varma]: And what was also a great point

05:01:09.780 --> 05:01:10.820
[Amit Varma]: you made in that

05:01:10.820 --> 05:01:12.020
[Amit Varma]: was how we need to think of

05:01:12.020 --> 05:01:13.860
[Amit Varma]: information production as a collective.

05:01:13.860 --> 05:01:14.360
[Amit Varma]: Exactly.

05:01:16.020 --> 05:01:18.020
[Amit Varma]: The point that you basically made in short

05:01:18.020 --> 05:01:18.900
[Amit Varma]: is that,

05:01:18.900 --> 05:01:19.700
[Amit Varma]: you know,

05:01:19.700 --> 05:01:20.740
[Amit Varma]: thought experiment,

05:01:20.740 --> 05:01:23.540
[Amit Varma]: that all journalism ceases to exist tomorrow.

05:01:23.540 --> 05:01:25.620
[Amit Varma]: The void in our lives will be incredible.

05:01:25.620 --> 05:01:27.220
[Amit Varma]: We won't know what the hell is going on.

05:01:27.220 --> 05:01:27.540
[Guest]: Exactly.

05:01:27.540 --> 05:01:27.940
[Amit Varma]: You know,

05:01:27.940 --> 05:01:29.620
[Amit Varma]: it is like a fish swimming in water,

05:01:29.620 --> 05:01:31.060
[Amit Varma]: and suddenly all the water is gone,

05:01:31.060 --> 05:01:31.860
[Amit Varma]: and you're like gasping

05:01:31.860 --> 05:01:33.140
[Amit Varma]: and like, what the fuck happened?

05:01:33.140 --> 05:01:34.420
[Amit Varma]: And it's exactly like that.

05:01:34.420 --> 05:01:34.740
[Unknown]: Yeah.

05:01:34.740 --> 05:01:35.940
[Amit Varma]: And the thing is,

05:01:35.940 --> 05:01:37.140
[Amit Varma]: we bemoan,

05:01:37.140 --> 05:01:38.180
[Amit Varma]: that, you know,

05:01:38.180 --> 05:01:39.620
[Amit Varma]: 99% news is coming,

05:01:39.620 --> 05:01:42.100
[Amit Varma]: but why isn't that 1% coming?

05:01:42.100 --> 05:01:42.900
[Amit Varma]: But sometimes,

05:01:42.900 --> 05:01:44.820
[Amit Varma]: as you've pointed out in the real world,

05:01:45.380 --> 05:01:47.140
[Amit Varma]: to get that 99% out,

05:01:47.140 --> 05:01:48.820
[Amit Varma]: some people choose to compromise on the 1%,

05:01:49.540 --> 05:01:51.540
[Guest]: and sometimes that 1% will come.

05:01:51.540 --> 05:01:52.660
[Guest]: Someone else will do that.

05:01:52.660 --> 05:01:53.060
[Guest]: Yes.

05:01:53.060 --> 05:01:53.860
[Guest]: It will come from somewhere else.

05:01:53.860 --> 05:01:55.300
[Amit Varma]: Civil society is there.

05:01:55.300 --> 05:01:56.980
[Amit Varma]: That gives me great hope also,

05:01:56.980 --> 05:01:59.060
[Amit Varma]: that civil society is there.

05:01:59.060 --> 05:02:00.100
[Amit Varma]: Like, I believe in people.

05:02:00.100 --> 05:02:01.700
[Amit Varma]: The reason I believe in economic freedom

05:02:01.700 --> 05:02:03.060
[Amit Varma]: is markets are one mechanism

05:02:03.060 --> 05:02:04.820
[Amit Varma]: for people to express themselves,

05:02:04.820 --> 05:02:06.340
[Amit Varma]: but there are other ways.

05:02:06.340 --> 05:02:06.980
[Unknown]: And, you know,

05:02:06.980 --> 05:02:09.700
[Amit Varma]: technology is empowering individuals,

05:02:09.700 --> 05:02:11.300
[Amit Varma]: and there will always be voices,

05:02:11.300 --> 05:02:12.820
[Amit Varma]: there will always be dissent.

05:02:12.820 --> 05:02:13.860
[Guest]: You can't shut everything down.

05:02:13.860 --> 05:02:14.820
[Guest]: You can't shut anything.

05:02:14.820 --> 05:02:15.380
[Guest]: In fact, you know,

05:02:15.380 --> 05:02:15.780
[Guest]: thank you for,

05:02:15.780 --> 05:02:16.900
[Guest]: I forgot almost this point,

05:02:16.900 --> 05:02:17.540
[Guest]: but you know this.

05:02:17.540 --> 05:02:17.940
[Guest]: So, you know,

05:02:17.940 --> 05:02:18.740
[Guest]: sometimes when I,

05:02:18.740 --> 05:02:19.940
[Guest]: I have a lot of times wonder that,

05:02:20.820 --> 05:02:22.180
[Guest]: this truth seeking,

05:02:22.180 --> 05:02:23.860
[Guest]: this journalism, does it matter?

05:02:23.860 --> 05:02:24.820
[Guest]: So, my answer to that is,

05:02:24.820 --> 05:02:26.100
[Guest]: if you don't get the answer,

05:02:26.100 --> 05:02:27.380
[Guest]: you know, it's a math problem.

05:02:27.380 --> 05:02:28.500
[Guest]: Go for the counterfactual.

05:02:28.500 --> 05:02:29.060
[Guest]: There's nothing.

05:02:29.860 --> 05:02:30.580
[Guest]: Then what happens?

05:02:30.580 --> 05:02:31.140
[Guest]: Then you realize,

05:02:31.140 --> 05:02:32.100
[Guest]: you know, this we want.

05:02:32.100 --> 05:02:34.100
[Guest]: I think anyone who says that

05:02:34.100 --> 05:02:35.300
[Guest]: mainstream media has a problem,

05:02:35.300 --> 05:02:36.260
[Guest]: I ask them this question,

05:02:36.260 --> 05:02:37.540
[Guest]: if we shut everything down,

05:02:37.540 --> 05:02:38.260
[Guest]: will things be better?

05:02:38.260 --> 05:02:38.900
[Guest]: No.

05:02:38.900 --> 05:02:40.260
[Guest]: So, on that note,

05:02:40.260 --> 05:02:41.780
[Guest]: there's this book I just want to recommend.

05:02:42.420 --> 05:02:43.300
[Guest]: Heard of this book,

05:02:43.300 --> 05:02:44.820
[Unknown]: Martin Guri, Revolt of the Public?

05:02:44.820 --> 05:02:46.340
[Unknown]: Yeah, yeah, of course, yeah.

05:02:46.340 --> 05:02:47.540
[Guest]: So, the frame, one like,

05:02:47.540 --> 05:02:48.180
[Guest]: it's a,

05:02:48.180 --> 05:02:49.540
[Guest]: that book is filled with arguments,

05:02:49.540 --> 05:02:50.900
[Guest]: but one thing that really struck me,

05:02:50.900 --> 05:02:52.340
[Guest]: he said that,

05:02:52.340 --> 05:02:53.780
[Guest]: the relationship between

05:02:54.420 --> 05:02:55.940
[Guest]: power and information

05:02:55.940 --> 05:02:56.740
[Guest]: is not linear.

05:02:57.700 --> 05:02:58.260
[Guest]: You know, you say,

05:02:58.260 --> 05:03:00.100
[Guest]: these online bloggers are dissenters

05:03:00.100 --> 05:03:01.300
[Guest]: and they will curb.

05:03:01.300 --> 05:03:01.860
[Guest]: He says, no.

05:03:02.900 --> 05:03:05.700
[Guest]: The powerful just want to control TV.

05:03:05.700 --> 05:03:06.260
[Guest]: No.

05:03:06.260 --> 05:03:08.420
[Guest]: He says that this is,

05:03:08.420 --> 05:03:09.700
[Guest]: you don't know how

05:03:09.700 --> 05:03:10.740
[Guest]: these two things intersect.

05:03:11.860 --> 05:03:13.300
[Guest]: What is exactly the relationship

05:03:13.300 --> 05:03:14.980
[Guest]: between information flow and power?

05:03:14.980 --> 05:03:15.780
[Guest]: What we know is that

05:03:15.780 --> 05:03:17.380
[Guest]: the powerful want to control.

05:03:17.380 --> 05:03:18.980
[Guest]: What they're not realizing

05:03:18.980 --> 05:03:21.300
[Guest]: is that you can control a TV channel.

05:03:21.300 --> 05:03:23.700
[Guest]: You can control a newspaper.

05:03:23.700 --> 05:03:25.540
[Guest]: You can put a blogger,

05:03:25.540 --> 05:03:26.980
[Guest]: a Mohammed Zubair in jail.

05:03:27.620 --> 05:03:28.980
[Guest]: You can't shut down

05:03:28.980 --> 05:03:29.940
[Guest]: the information sphere.

05:03:31.380 --> 05:03:35.300
[Guest]: Because we are at a time when,

05:03:35.300 --> 05:03:36.900
[Guest]: you know, that's a revolt of the public

05:03:36.900 --> 05:03:37.620
[Guest]: where he says that

05:03:38.260 --> 05:03:38.900
[Guest]: there was a time

05:03:38.900 --> 05:03:40.740
[Guest]: when everything was authority.

05:03:40.740 --> 05:03:42.340
[Guest]: So, a newspaper

05:03:42.340 --> 05:03:43.620
[Guest]: was in the game of authority.

05:03:43.620 --> 05:03:44.900
[Guest]: That, you know, it was,

05:03:45.540 --> 05:03:46.580
[Guest]: you close this newspaper,

05:03:46.580 --> 05:03:48.820
[Guest]: information flow is controlled.

05:03:48.820 --> 05:03:50.900
[Guest]: Now, we are out of that game.

05:03:51.620 --> 05:03:52.820
[Guest]: So, I think they,

05:03:52.820 --> 05:03:53.940
[Guest]: people in power,

05:03:53.940 --> 05:03:54.820
[Guest]: they also don't know

05:03:54.820 --> 05:03:56.900
[Guest]: that how much can you control?

05:03:57.540 --> 05:03:58.340
[Guest]: How much?

05:03:58.340 --> 05:03:59.220
[Guest]: So, you do your, you know,

05:03:59.220 --> 05:04:00.980
[Guest]: you flood the information sphere with shit

05:04:00.980 --> 05:04:02.180
[Guest]: so that people are confused.

05:04:02.180 --> 05:04:03.060
[Guest]: So, that's a strategy.

05:04:03.940 --> 05:04:06.260
[Guest]: But I don't think in today's time,

05:04:06.260 --> 05:04:07.620
[Guest]: if you want to do a story,

05:04:08.180 --> 05:04:10.340
[Guest]: truth or reporting,

05:04:10.340 --> 05:04:12.020
[Guest]: you can't stop it being published.

05:04:12.900 --> 05:04:13.860
[Guest]: That, I think, is something,

05:04:13.860 --> 05:04:15.300
[Guest]: a gift that technology has given us.

05:04:16.100 --> 05:04:17.460
[Guest]: And people are exploiting it

05:04:17.460 --> 05:04:19.620
[Guest]: all across the board.

05:04:19.620 --> 05:04:20.180
[Amit Varma]: So, you know,

05:04:20.180 --> 05:04:21.780
[Amit Varma]: we've spoken for almost five hours

05:04:21.780 --> 05:04:22.660
[Amit Varma]: and we haven't mentioned

05:04:22.660 --> 05:04:24.020
[Amit Varma]: data journalism yet,

05:04:24.020 --> 05:04:25.380
[Amit Varma]: which is, of course,

05:04:25.380 --> 05:04:26.340
[Amit Varma]: a pigeonholing term

05:04:26.340 --> 05:04:27.540
[Amit Varma]: that slightly irritates me.

05:04:27.540 --> 05:04:29.060
[Amit Varma]: Like, even when I, you know,

05:04:29.060 --> 05:04:30.660
[Amit Varma]: recorded with Rukmini, for example,

05:04:30.660 --> 05:04:31.540
[Amit Varma]: or, you know, Pramit,

05:04:31.540 --> 05:04:32.900
[Amit Varma]: I felt kind of guilty.

05:04:32.900 --> 05:04:34.740
[Amit Varma]: I said, I don't want to use this term

05:04:34.740 --> 05:04:35.620
[Amit Varma]: because these guys are just

05:04:35.620 --> 05:04:36.980
[Amit Varma]: proper journalists as are you.

05:04:36.980 --> 05:04:38.740
[Amit Varma]: And, you know, data is one tool

05:04:38.740 --> 05:04:39.780
[Amit Varma]: that you have among many

05:04:39.780 --> 05:04:40.980
[Amit Varma]: to tell a story.

05:04:40.980 --> 05:04:42.420
[Amit Varma]: So, tell me a little bit about

05:04:42.980 --> 05:04:43.540
[Amit Varma]: how you,

05:04:44.100 --> 05:04:45.220
[Amit Varma]: what is wrong with the way

05:04:45.220 --> 05:04:47.220
[Amit Varma]: people think of data journalism

05:04:47.220 --> 05:04:50.340
[Amit Varma]: and what are the appropriate ways

05:04:50.340 --> 05:04:51.860
[Amit Varma]: to think of data,

05:04:51.860 --> 05:04:53.700
[Amit Varma]: both for journalists and for readers?

05:04:53.700 --> 05:04:56.420
[Amit Varma]: Because when the term was new,

05:04:56.420 --> 05:04:57.940
[Amit Varma]: we used to watch Hans Rosling's

05:04:57.940 --> 05:04:59.620
[Amit Varma]: graphics, you know,

05:04:59.620 --> 05:05:01.700
[Amit Varma]: and for us, in our heads,

05:05:01.700 --> 05:05:03.220
[Amit Varma]: data journalism was all these

05:05:03.220 --> 05:05:05.860
[Amit Varma]: funky moving graphics and, you know,

05:05:05.860 --> 05:05:07.460
[Amit Varma]: but that's not it.

05:05:07.460 --> 05:05:08.500
[Amit Varma]: That's just one way of

05:05:08.500 --> 05:05:09.860
[Amit Varma]: packaging it, as it were.

05:05:09.860 --> 05:05:11.060
[Amit Varma]: But there's a lot more to that.

05:05:11.060 --> 05:05:13.060
[Amit Varma]: So, tell me a little bit about this.

05:05:13.060 --> 05:05:14.500
[Amit Varma]: I feel you have a lot of harassment

05:05:14.500 --> 05:05:15.700
[Amit Varma]: that you're happy to let out.

05:05:15.700 --> 05:05:17.860
[Guest]: So, first of all, I think

05:05:17.860 --> 05:05:19.140
[Guest]: Rukmini and Pramit are both,

05:05:19.140 --> 05:05:20.580
[Guest]: in a way, friends and mentors.

05:05:20.580 --> 05:05:21.780
[Guest]: Like, you know, Rukmini hired me

05:05:21.780 --> 05:05:22.580
[Amit Varma]: in journalism.

05:05:22.580 --> 05:05:23.860
