[Guest]: So, I mean, you have had the

05:05:51.380 --> 05:05:52.340
[Guest]: pros of the profession

05:05:52.340 --> 05:05:53.140
[Guest]: on your podcast.

05:05:53.140 --> 05:05:54.500
[Guest]: I mean, I learned from them.

05:05:55.220 --> 05:05:56.900
[Guest]: But still, I'll just tell you what.

05:05:56.900 --> 05:05:57.860
[Guest]: So, I think,

05:05:59.540 --> 05:06:00.820
[Guest]: when I came,

05:06:00.820 --> 05:06:02.020
[Guest]: when I got my first job

05:06:02.020 --> 05:06:03.220
[Guest]: as a data journalist,

05:06:05.060 --> 05:06:06.180
[Guest]: I used to probably tell that,

05:06:06.180 --> 05:06:07.780
[Guest]: you know, I use data to tell stories.

05:06:08.500 --> 05:06:09.000
[Guest]: Right.

05:06:09.700 --> 05:06:11.700
[Guest]: But then you realize that

05:06:11.700 --> 05:06:12.580
[Guest]: what a limited

05:06:12.580 --> 05:06:14.020
[Guest]: way to think about a story.

05:06:14.020 --> 05:06:14.520
[Guest]: Why?

05:06:16.020 --> 05:06:17.780
[Guest]: I think the frustrating part

05:06:17.780 --> 05:06:19.460
[Guest]: is not just graphics or whatever.

05:06:19.460 --> 05:06:20.100
[Guest]: It's just that

05:06:20.660 --> 05:06:21.860
[Guest]: you want to answer a question.

05:06:22.500 --> 05:06:23.540
[Guest]: You want to tell a story.

05:06:24.260 --> 05:06:26.900
[Guest]: And data is a very powerful way

05:06:27.620 --> 05:06:29.140
[Guest]: to answer a question.

05:06:29.140 --> 05:06:30.660
[Guest]: It's a scientific question.

05:06:30.660 --> 05:06:32.340
[Guest]: It could be a day-to-day question.

05:06:32.340 --> 05:06:33.620
[Guest]: It could be a fitness question.

05:06:33.620 --> 05:06:34.260
[Guest]: Right. It just,

05:06:34.260 --> 05:06:35.220
[Guest]: we were talking about

05:06:35.220 --> 05:06:36.500
[Guest]: glucose monitors the other day.

05:06:36.500 --> 05:06:37.000
[Guest]: Right.

05:06:37.860 --> 05:06:39.220
[Guest]: I'm saying it's a one way,

05:06:39.220 --> 05:06:40.580
[Guest]: but it's not the only way.

05:06:40.580 --> 05:06:42.900
[Guest]: So, I now think that

05:06:42.900 --> 05:06:43.540
[Guest]: you do journalism

05:06:43.540 --> 05:06:45.140
[Guest]: where you try to answer a question.

05:06:45.700 --> 05:06:46.900
[Guest]: And there are so many different ways

05:06:46.900 --> 05:06:48.660
[Guest]: you can interview people,

05:06:48.660 --> 05:06:49.540
[Guest]: you can find documents,

05:06:49.540 --> 05:06:50.900
[Guest]: and you can also do data.

05:06:50.900 --> 05:06:52.180
[Guest]: So, when you isolate

05:06:52.740 --> 05:06:54.500
[Guest]: and say, I do data journalism.

05:06:55.300 --> 05:06:55.800
[Guest]: Right.

05:06:57.220 --> 05:06:58.660
[Guest]: It's just meaningless.

05:06:58.660 --> 05:07:00.020
[Guest]: You do journalism,

05:07:00.020 --> 05:07:02.020
[Guest]: like all journalism should be data-backed

05:07:02.020 --> 05:07:02.820
[Guest]: when it can be.

05:07:03.620 --> 05:07:04.120
[Guest]: Right.

05:07:04.120 --> 05:07:05.460
[Guest]: When and there will be situations

05:07:05.460 --> 05:07:07.460
[Guest]: and there are like tons of questions

05:07:07.460 --> 05:07:08.660
[Guest]: where you don't have

05:07:08.660 --> 05:07:10.820
[Guest]: data-centric answers.

05:07:10.820 --> 05:07:12.660
[Guest]: So, you use your other toolkit.

05:07:12.660 --> 05:07:14.420
[Guest]: So, my short answer is this,

05:07:14.420 --> 05:07:16.660
[Guest]: that the framing is fundamentally

05:07:17.540 --> 05:07:19.060
[Guest]: bizarre because,

05:07:20.100 --> 05:07:20.600
[Guest]: like,

05:07:21.700 --> 05:07:23.380
[Guest]: are we making a distinction that

05:07:23.940 --> 05:07:25.540
[Guest]: some things are data journalism,

05:07:25.540 --> 05:07:27.460
[Guest]: the other journalism doesn't need data

05:07:28.020 --> 05:07:28.740
[Guest]: or evidence.

05:07:28.740 --> 05:07:29.240
[Guest]: No.

05:07:29.240 --> 05:07:30.740
[Guest]: Data is a good way to get evidence.

05:07:30.740 --> 05:07:31.540
[Guest]: So, that I think,

05:07:32.260 --> 05:07:33.620
[Guest]: and it hit me very early in my,

05:07:33.620 --> 05:07:35.460
[Guest]: like, in my career.

05:07:35.460 --> 05:07:36.020
[Guest]: So, I, you know,

05:07:36.020 --> 05:07:37.460
[Guest]: I don't even like to interview people.

05:07:37.460 --> 05:07:39.860
[Guest]: I, you know, I don't even like to introduce myself as a...

05:07:39.860 --> 05:07:40.980
[Guest]: So, if you see my profiles,

05:07:40.980 --> 05:07:42.180
[Guest]: I just say reporter.

05:07:42.180 --> 05:07:42.900
[Guest]: No data reporter,

05:07:42.900 --> 05:07:44.100
[Guest]: no data journalist,

05:07:44.100 --> 05:07:44.820
[Guest]: nothing.

05:07:44.820 --> 05:07:46.500
[Guest]: But it remains central to my work

05:07:46.500 --> 05:07:47.060
[Guest]: and how I think.

05:07:48.340 --> 05:07:48.820
[Amit Varma]: Yeah.

05:07:48.820 --> 05:07:50.180
[Amit Varma]: I think data should be

05:07:50.180 --> 05:07:52.740
[Amit Varma]: sort of central to all our worlds,

05:07:52.740 --> 05:07:53.300
[Amit Varma]: into, you know,

05:07:53.300 --> 05:07:54.340
[Amit Varma]: whether we're journalists or not,

05:07:54.340 --> 05:07:56.180
[Amit Varma]: just in terms of understanding the world,

05:07:56.180 --> 05:07:57.540
[Amit Varma]: understanding ourselves.

05:07:57.540 --> 05:07:59.060
[Amit Varma]: So, there are a ton of,

05:07:59.060 --> 05:08:00.420
[Amit Varma]: you know, journalism

05:08:00.420 --> 05:08:02.500
[Amit Varma]: and stats-related questions.

05:08:03.140 --> 05:08:04.500
[Amit Varma]: I still have noted down here,

05:08:04.500 --> 05:08:05.540
[Amit Varma]: which I was planning to ask you,

05:08:05.540 --> 05:08:06.980
[Amit Varma]: but I think we've sat here for a long time.

05:08:06.980 --> 05:08:09.300
[Amit Varma]: So, I'll sort of link all your posts

05:08:09.300 --> 05:08:10.420
[Amit Varma]: from the show notes

05:08:10.420 --> 05:08:11.620
[Amit Varma]: and let people get to them.

05:08:11.620 --> 05:08:12.820
[Amit Varma]: I want to, you know,

05:08:12.820 --> 05:08:14.500
[Amit Varma]: go back to the personal domain.

05:08:14.500 --> 05:08:17.300
[Amit Varma]: And when we had our first conversation in Udaipur,

05:08:17.300 --> 05:08:17.940
[Amit Varma]: we were,

05:08:17.940 --> 05:08:19.220
[Amit Varma]: I was telling you about

05:08:19.220 --> 05:08:20.580
[Amit Varma]: how my CGM,

05:08:20.580 --> 05:08:21.700
[Amit Varma]: continuous glucose monitor,

05:08:21.700 --> 05:08:22.580
[Amit Varma]: kind of changed my life.

05:08:22.580 --> 05:08:24.580
[Amit Varma]: And the long and the short story of it is that

05:08:25.140 --> 05:08:26.900
[Amit Varma]: I have come to realize

05:08:26.900 --> 05:08:29.140
[Amit Varma]: that people like us,

05:08:29.140 --> 05:08:29.640
[Amit Varma]: journalists,

05:08:30.260 --> 05:08:30.980
[Amit Varma]: intellectuals,

05:08:30.980 --> 05:08:31.540
[Amit Varma]: whatever,

05:08:31.540 --> 05:08:32.580
[Amit Varma]: people like us,

05:08:32.580 --> 05:08:34.340
[Amit Varma]: are trying to understand the world.

05:08:34.340 --> 05:08:35.940
[Amit Varma]: We are proud of the efforts we make

05:08:35.940 --> 05:08:37.380
[Amit Varma]: in trying to understand the world,

05:08:37.380 --> 05:08:38.420
[Amit Varma]: understand processes,

05:08:38.420 --> 05:08:39.300
[Amit Varma]: understand systems,

05:08:39.300 --> 05:08:40.020
[Amit Varma]: all of that.

05:08:40.020 --> 05:08:41.300
[Amit Varma]: But we don't adequately

05:08:41.300 --> 05:08:43.060
[Amit Varma]: understand our own bodies.

05:08:43.060 --> 05:08:44.980
[Amit Varma]: And my realization of this

05:08:44.980 --> 05:08:46.180
[Amit Varma]: came recently

05:08:46.180 --> 05:08:47.780
[Amit Varma]: when my good friend Ajay Shah

05:08:47.780 --> 05:08:48.900
[Amit Varma]: recommended that I use

05:08:48.900 --> 05:08:50.260
[Amit Varma]: a continuous glucose monitor

05:08:50.260 --> 05:08:52.580
[Amit Varma]: to see what is happening in my own body.

05:08:52.580 --> 05:08:53.940
[Amit Varma]: And I got that.

05:08:53.940 --> 05:08:55.540
[Amit Varma]: And the result shook me so much

05:08:55.540 --> 05:08:57.780
[Amit Varma]: that I changed my entire lifestyle

05:08:57.780 --> 05:08:59.540
[Amit Varma]: to great benefit, right?

05:08:59.540 --> 05:09:02.340
[Amit Varma]: And I realized that this,

05:09:02.340 --> 05:09:02.820
[Amit Varma]: you know,

05:09:02.820 --> 05:09:04.580
[Amit Varma]: what we earlier spoke about

05:09:04.580 --> 05:09:05.780
[Unknown]: the examined life

05:09:05.780 --> 05:09:07.060
[Unknown]: and unexamined life

05:09:07.060 --> 05:09:08.180
[Amit Varma]: is not worth living.

05:09:08.180 --> 05:09:09.940
[Amit Varma]: And I think a key part of that

05:09:09.940 --> 05:09:12.580
[Amit Varma]: is understanding our own bodies.

05:09:12.580 --> 05:09:13.860
[Amit Varma]: And over the next few months,

05:09:13.860 --> 05:09:15.860
[Amit Varma]: I intend to make more efforts

05:09:15.860 --> 05:09:16.980
[Amit Varma]: to kind of figure this out,

05:09:16.980 --> 05:09:18.500
[Amit Varma]: because I think I have been

05:09:18.500 --> 05:09:19.940
[Amit Varma]: incredibly sloppy

05:09:19.940 --> 05:09:20.980
[Amit Varma]: when it comes to health

05:09:20.980 --> 05:09:21.700
[Amit Varma]: and my own body

05:09:21.700 --> 05:09:22.740
[Amit Varma]: and understanding that.

05:09:22.740 --> 05:09:24.420
[Amit Varma]: And I think those are key to happiness

05:09:24.420 --> 05:09:25.620
[Amit Varma]: and in producing

05:09:25.620 --> 05:09:27.140
[Amit Varma]: the best version of myself.

05:09:27.140 --> 05:09:28.580
[Amit Varma]: And I noticed that

05:09:28.580 --> 05:09:29.620
[Amit Varma]: this is something that

05:09:29.620 --> 05:09:31.860
[Amit Varma]: you have also worked on

05:09:31.860 --> 05:09:33.780
[Unknown]: intensively over the last few years

05:09:33.780 --> 05:09:34.980
[Unknown]: in terms of how you have thought

05:09:34.980 --> 05:09:35.860
[Amit Varma]: about fitness,

05:09:35.860 --> 05:09:37.220
[Amit Varma]: how you've thought about

05:09:37.220 --> 05:09:39.620
[Amit Varma]: pretty much every aspect of your life.

05:09:39.620 --> 05:09:42.020
[Amit Varma]: So tell me a little bit more about this,

05:09:42.020 --> 05:09:43.460
[Amit Varma]: because I feel there's a lot for me

05:09:43.460 --> 05:09:44.180
[Amit Varma]: and my listeners

05:09:44.180 --> 05:09:45.300
[Amit Varma]: to learn from your journey.

05:09:46.580 --> 05:09:47.860
[Guest]: Just specifically about

05:09:48.820 --> 05:09:49.700
[Guest]: fitness and the role of

